<DIV2 N="1" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000029.tif">

<PB REF="00000031.tif" N="[3]">
<HEAD>I. DE ADUENTU.<MILESTONE N="1" UNIT="p"></HEAD>
<P><I>Ecce uenit rex occurramus obuiam saluatori nostro.</I> To dai is cumen &eth;e holie tid &thorn;at me clepe&eth; aduent. &thorn;anked be ure louerd ihesu crist &thorn;it<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> haue&eth; isend. And hit laste&eth; &thorn;re wuke fulle and sum del more. <I>Et significat tria tempora. ante legem. sub lege. sub gratia.</I> and bitocne&eth; &thorn;re time. On &thorn;e was bi-fore &thorn;e olde lage. &thorn;e o&eth;er was on &thorn;e holde lage. and &thorn;e &thorn;ridde was on &thorn;e newe lage. Men &thorn;e waren wunede<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> wunende.</NOTE> on elche of &thorn;ese &thorn;rie times wisten gerne after ure lauerd ihesu cristes tocume alse we do&eth;. &thorn;e ben on &thorn;esse &thorn;re wuken; &thorn;e ben cleped aduent. &thorn;at is seggen on englis ure louerd ihesu cristes tocume. <I>Aduentus autem duo sunt manifesti. et totidem occulti</I>. Ure louerd ihesu cristes tocumes; ben tweien openliche. &thorn;e fireste is gon. &thorn;o &thorn;e patriarkes and &thorn;e prophetes and o&eth;re men &thorn;e waren bi &thorn;o dages after wisseden. And &thorn;at o&eth;er tocume be&eth; on domes dai. and &thorn;at we abiden. And alle &thorn;o; &thorn;e habben ben se&eth;en ure louerd ihesu crist steh to heuene. And alle &thorn;o &thorn;e ben tocumen her after abide&eth; his tocume. And of &thorn;e firste tocume speke&eth; &thorn;e holi boc &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Ecce uenit rex et cetera.</I> here cume&eth; ure king. wule we fare togenes him. and him faire understonden. and heiliche wur&eth;ie <I>.s. cordis</I> 
<PB REF="00000033.tif" N="5"> <I>mundicia. oris modestia</I>. <MILESTONE N="2" UNIT="p"> <I>operis sanctimonia.</I> &thorn;at is fare to|genes him. noh[t] lichanliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>. ac on gode &thorn;anke. and under|stonden him on ure e&eth;ele bede. and wur&eth;supen him; on ure edie dede. Of &eth;e lateste to-cume spec&eth; &thorn;e holie boc on o&eth;er stede &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Ecce dominus ueniet et omnes sancti eius cum eo.</I> Ure louerd wile cume. and alle hise halegen mid him. &thorn;at be&eth; on domes dai. Tweien o&eth;er tocumes ben bo&eth;e iliche. <I>Altero uisitat quando mentium tenebras illuminat. uel caritatem cordibus infundit.</I> &THORN;at o&eth;er tocume is &thorn;ane he cume&eth; to men and turne&eth; his herte to forleten and hatien his senne. and to luuien god; and al his emcristen. and &thorn;is tocume we bidden &thorn;ane we singen. <I>Ueni domine uisitare nos in pace.</I> Cum louerd and biwind us on seihtnesse. <I>Altero uenit rapere quemque de miseriis huius uite.</I> &thorn;at o&eth;er digeliche tocume beo&eth;; &thorn;ane he cume&eth; to elch man sunderlupes. and do&eth; ut of &thorn;isse worelde. and of &thorn;is tocume spec&eth; ure helende seluen on &thorn;e holie godspelle. and muneged us alle to ben warre &thorn;arof; and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Uigilate quia nescitis diem neque horam.</I> &thorn;at is be&eth; wakiende. and forlete&eth; gure synne. &thorn;at ge ne ben ifunden on sunne. and swo forlorene. <I>Horum autem aduentum alius fuit misericordie; et ideo desiderabilis. alius erit iusticie; et ideo formidabilis. alius separationis; et horridus. alius gratie; et blandus.</I> Of ure louerd ihesu cristes openliche tocume. &thorn;e forme was of mildhertnesse. and alle bileffulle men &thorn;e waren &thorn;o; and &eth;ar biforen wissede swi&eth;e &eth;ar after. <MILESTONE N="3" UNIT="p">and &eth;uhte long er he come. and alesede hem eche dea&eth;e. &thorn;at o&eth;er openliche tocume. &thorn;at is te cumen &aacute; domes dai; be&eth; of rihtwisnesse. for &thorn;anne he wile &eth;ere gelden elch man his hwile mid swilch mede swo he ernede here. and &thorn;at tocume is swi&eth;e ei[s]liche. for &thorn;anne be&eth; noman siker; ar he ihere &thorn;at lufliche word of ure louerd ihesu cristes swete mu&eth;e. <I>Venite benedicti patris mei et cetera.</I> Cume&eth; ge ibletsede. and underfo&eth; eche lif. and blisse mid englen of heuene. &thorn;at is giarked si&eth;en &thorn;e biginninge of &thorn;es woreld. to &thorn;e o&eth;er wur&eth; iseid &thorn;at lo&eth;eliche word. and ateliche. and grisliche. &thorn;at is to synfulle. <I>Ite maledicti in ignem eternum.</I> Wite&eth; ge awariede gastes into &thorn;at eche fir on helle. and wunie&eth; 
<PB REF="00000035.tif" N="7"> &thorn;ar; &oacute; and &oacute; abuten ende. mid alle deflen. Eftsone ure helendes on tocume &thorn;inc&eth; dieliche and grisliche alle manne. Forwi; for &thorn;at he dele&eth; &thorn;e sowle; and &thorn;e lichame. &thorn;anne he wit of &thorn;isse woreld. His o&eth;er dieliche tocume is softe. and swi&eth;e milde. and licwur&eth;e alle &thorn;o; &thorn;e he to cume&eth;. for to aleomen hem of rihte bileue. and of so&eth; luue to him seluen. Swo cume he to us; for his muchele mildhertnesse. <I>Qui uiuit et Regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="2" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>II. DOMINICA SECUNDA IN ADUENTU.</HEAD>
<P><I>Hora est iam nos de sompno surgere et cetera.</I> &THORN;e lauerd sainte powel &thorn;e is heued lor&eth;eau of alle holie chirechen bihield &thorn;is wreche woreld. and sagh &thorn;at mast mannen ladden here lif on sunnen. and &thorn;at hem likede here lodliche sinnes. alse werie men is lief to slapen. <MILESTONE N="4" UNIT="p">and him &thorn;at sore reu. and &thorn;arfore &thorn;oghte &thorn;at he wolde alle synfulle men; munigin to rihtlachen here liflode. for to forleten and to beten heore synnes. and wrot &thorn;o a writ; and sende hit synfulle men. and &thorn;aron wi&eth; hem &thorn;us spec. and dude him seluen mid hem &thorn;aron; alse &thorn;eih he sunful ware. <I>Hora est iam nos. et cetera.</I> longe we habben lein on ure fule synnes. and swoldred &thorn;aron; alse slou man do&eth; on swete slape. Ac nu hit is time. &thorn;at we rise &thorn;a[r]of. and clensen us of ure fule synnes. and after &thorn;at ure lif laden on clennesse. and swo abiden ure helendes tocume. &thorn;at neihlache&eth; nu&eth;e fram dai to daie. and be&eth; on midewintres niht. &thorn;us he spec&eth; wi&eth; us on stede; in his holie write. and o&eth;er stede minege&eth; us. and wisse&thorn; us to leden ure lif on clennesse; and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Sobrie et iuste. et pie uiuamus in hoc seculo.</I> Wile we leden ure lif on &thorn;isse worelde me&eth;eliche togenes us suluen. &thorn;at we &thorn;enchen and que&eth;en. and do &thorn;at ure sowle and ure lichame be biheue. and forlaten al &thorn;at hem be&eth; unbiheue; alse &thorn;e wise clerc seide on 
<PB REF="00000037.tif" N="9"> his boc. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Si prodesse cupis tibi que sint commoda quere.</I> Gif &thorn;u gierne waxest<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>?read</I> waxen.</NOTE> on godnesse; sech after &thorn;ing &thorn;e &eth;e be&eth; biheue. Ure lif we lede&eth; richtliche togenes ure louerd ihesu crist. gif we forbere&eth; al &thorn;at; &thorn;at him is unqueme. and folge&eth; on &thorn;onke and on speche. and on dede; &thorn;at him is iqueme. <I>Qui placet ipse deo proximus esse potest.</I> &thorn;e man mai be <MILESTONE N="5" UNIT="p">god next. &thorn;e him be&eth; iqueme. Tegenes ure emcristene we sulle laden ure lif; edmodeliche on two wise. On is &thorn;at &thorn;e holie boc of spech&eth;. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Da egenti. succurre non habenti et in omni necessitate pro</I> <NOTE PLACE="marg">Originally proximo.</NOTE> <I>Christo subueni.</I> Gief &thorn;e nedfulle. help &thorn;e hauelease. and on alle wise bet &thorn;in emcristene nede. <I>Eximi</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">read <I>Proximi</I>.</NOTE> <I>nostri omnes quibus est unus dominus. una fides. unum baptisma.</I> Vre emcristene ben alle &thorn;o; &thorn;e here&eth; one louerd. and haue&eth; one bileue imene. and one fulcninge. On swilch liflode we mugen trustliche abiden ure louerd ihesu cristes tocume. and siker ben; &thorn;at he wile to us cume. and weren us mid [wi&eth;] ure dea&eth;liche liue. and wi&eth; eche wowe. and gieuen us eche wele mid him seluen on heuene. <I>Qui uiuit et Regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="3" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>III. DOMINICA TERTIA.</HEAD>
<P><I>Nox precessit dies autem appropinquabit.</I> Hure heiest lor&eth;eu after ure louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;at is ure louerd sainte powel. munege&eth; us to rihtlechen ur liflode. and wisse&eth; us on wilche wise. and sei&eth; &thorn;at we hauen riht &thorn;arto; and sei&eth; hwu &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Nox precessit. dies autem et cetera.</I> &ETH;e niht is for&eth;-gon; and dai neihleche&eth;. and for&thorn;i hit is riht &thorn;at we forleten. and forsaken nihtliche deden. &thorn;o ben &thorn;e werkes of &thorn;iesternesse. and scruden us mid wapnen of lihte. &thorn;at be&eth; so&eth;feste bileue. and of brihtnesse. swo &thorn;at we gon &aacute; dai 
<PB REF="00000039.tif" N="11"> bicumeliche. <I>Non in commessationibus et ebrietatibus non in cubilibus et inpudicitiis non in contentione et emulatione. sed in horum oppositis</I>. And noh[t] on derke wedes. ac her we seien eow of &thorn;ese derke wedes. wat &thorn;e holie apostle mene&eth;; &thorn;o he nemnede niht. <MILESTONE N="6" UNIT="p">and niehtes dede. and dai. and leochtes wapne. <I>Nox accipitur multis modis. sed hic pro infidelitate.</I> Niht bitocne&eth; her unbileue. &thorn;at is aiware aleid. and rihte leue arered gode&eth;onc. and na&eth;eles get is sume &thorn;arfore of unbileue ifild on one stede. and swo faste bunden. and swo biwunde &thorn;arinne. &thorn;at no prest. ne no bissop ne mai him chastien; ne mid forbode. ne mid scrifte. ne mid cursinge. and &thorn;at is li&eth;er custume. &thorn;at man leue&eth; get. and &thorn;at is after clepenge. and ascinge. and uncunne. and warienge. and handselne. and time. and hwate. and fele swilche deueles craftes. and &thorn;at wreche man. &thorn;at swilche &thorn;ing him mai letten; of &thorn;at &thorn;e god him haue&eth; munt. Ac alle &thorn;o &thorn;e leue&eth; &thorn;at swilch &thorn;ing hem muge fur&eth;rie o&eth;er letten; ben cursed of godes mu&eth;e. &thorn;e &eth;us sei&eth; on &thorn;e holie boc. <I>Maledictus homo qui confidit in homine.</I> Cursed be &thorn;e man &thorn;e leue&eth; upen hwate. Ac ich wile segen undernime&eth; hit. hwat make&eth; swilch letten. we rade&eth; on boc. &thorn;at elch man haue&eth; to fere on engel of heuene; on his rihthalf. &thorn;at him wisse&eth;. and munege&eth; eure to don god. and on his lifthalf an wereged gost. &thorn;at him aure tache&eth; to ufele. and &thorn;at is &thorn;e deuel. he make&eth; &thorn;e unbilefulle man to leuen swilche wigeles; swo ich ar embe spac. and &thorn;are mide he him bicher&eth;. and binime&eth; him heuene wele. and bringe&eth; him on helle wowe. crist us &thorn;arwi&eth; silde. and healde us rihte <MILESTONE N="7" UNIT="p">bileue. and elch man &thorn;e hit haue&eth;. and geue hine &thorn;o &thorn;e hit naue&eth; nocht. &ETH;e werc of &thorn;esternesse; &thorn;at ben alle heuie sennen. and swilche o&eth;re so &thorn;e apostle her nemde. alse ben oueretes. and untimeliche eten alehuse. and at ferme. and at feste. and masthwat at ilche la&eth;e&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> metisupe. For &thorn;ar man ne can his mu&eth;es me&eth;e. ne cunnen nele. ne his wombe met. and &thorn;eih he cunne of mete; he nele cunne of drinke. er he be swo iueid &thorn;at he falle defle to honde. &ETH;e &thorn;ridde is &thorn;at man sitte an euen at drinke. and ligge longe a moregen. and slawliche arise&eth;. and late to chireche go&eth;. &ETH;at feor&eth;e is unrihte luue. &thorn;at is 
<PB REF="00000041.tif" N="13"> hordom. and mid-liggunge &thorn;e men drigen bi-twenen hem; bute gef he ben lageliche bispusede &thorn;at is unriht and untimeliche. and mid unsel&eth;e; for hordom ne haue&eth; non time ne scule. ac is defles hersumpnesse. Ne for&eth;e gef man haue&eth; to done mid his rihte spuse on unsele. o&eth;er an untime &thorn;an man faste sal. o&eth;er halgen. he sinege&eth; gretliche. for &thorn;e holie boc hit forbet. &thorn;at fifte is chest and chew. and twifold speche and ilch fliting of worde. &ETH;at sixte is &thorn;at man egge&eth; his negebure to done o&eth;er to speken him harm. o&eth;er same. and haue&eth; ni&eth; elch wi&eth; o&eth;er. and make&eth; him to forlese his aihte. o&eth;er of his rihte. &thorn;ese ben &thorn;e six werkes of &thorn;esternesse. <MILESTONE N="8" UNIT="p">&thorn;e &thorn;e holie apostle for-bet so swi&eth;e. For elch man &thorn;e hem do&eth;; bute he hem forlete. and bete ar his ende dai; he sal forlesen eche liht. and blisse and lif. and hauen an helle eche pine. and &thorn;esternesse mid deflen. crist us &thorn;are wi&eth; silde gef is wille be. &ETH;e dai &thorn;e &thorn;e apostle of spec&eth; is ure rihte bileue. &thorn;at is ure sowle liht. &thorn;e wapnes of his lihte ben six werkes of brihtnesse. &thorn;e hatten &thorn;us. <I>Temperancia. Modica potio. Strenuitas. Continencia. Per inuicem oratio. Inuicem dilectio.</I> &ETH;et foremeste is riht medeme m&eacute;l. &thorn;e man &thorn;e hit me&eth;e&eth; riht. &thorn;e sune&eth; ale&eth; gestninge. and idel wil. and haue&eth; riht mel tid. and nutte&eth; timeliche metes. and geme&eth; his mu&eth;es me&eth;e. and of his wombe mete. &ETH;at oder is emliche drinke. naht for te quenchen his lu&eth;ere wil. ne his lust. &thorn;e miswune haue&eth; on broht; ac for to beten his &thorn;ur[s]tes nede. &ETH;e &eth;ridde is &thorn;at man be waker. and liht. and snel. and seli. and erliche rise. and gernliche seche chireche. &ETH;at feor&eth;e is. &thorn;at man &thorn;e spuse haue&eth;. his golliche deden wi&eth;-teo. swo hit be untime. and &thorn;o &thorn;e be&eth; unbispused; forleten mid alle. &ETH;at fifte is. &thorn;at elch man for o&eth;er bidde; alse for him seluen. &ETH;at sixte is. &thorn;at elch man luuie o&eth;er al swo alse him seluen. &thorn;eih he swo swi&eth;e ne muge. <I>Ista sex opera dicuntur et uestes et arma. Vestes; quia nos ornant apud deum. et homines. Arma; quia nos muniunt apud hostes.</I> &ETH;ese six werkes of brictnesse. ben cleped lihtes scrud. <MILESTONE N="9" UNIT="p">for &thorn;at hie sru&eth;e&eth; and huihted<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>or</I> hiuhted.</NOTE> togenes gode. and togenes manne elch &thorn;e hie do&eth;. and ec he ben nemned lichtes wapne. for elch man &thorn;e hes do&eth; were&eth; him 
<PB REF="00000043.tif" N="15"> seluen &thorn;armide wi&eth; mankinnes unwine. &ETH;e lauerd sainte poul &thorn;e us lare&eth; &thorn;us. and munege&eth; us to forleten &thorn;e six werkes of &thorn;esternesse. &thorn;e bilige to nihte. and to done &thorn;e six dede. &thorn;e ich later nemnede &thorn;e bilige to brihtnesse. he &thorn;ingie us to &thorn;e holie fader of heuene. &thorn;at he geue us mihte and streng&eth;e to forletene &thorn;esternesse. and to folgie brictnesse. <I>Qui uiuit et Regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="4" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>IV. CREDO.</HEAD>
<P><I>Tria sunt hominum saluti necessaria. scilicet fides. baptismus uite mundicia. De fide ait dominus in euangelio. Qui non crediderit condempnabitur. Et sapiens ait. Sine fide inpossibile est homini placere deo. De baptismo autem dicit dominus in euangelio. Nisi quis renatus fuerit ex aqua et spiritu sancto et cetera. De uite mundicia dicit dominus per prophetam. Lauamini mundi estote. Et in psalmo. Declina &aacute; malo et fac bonum. Et apostolus. Immundicia nec nominetur in uobis cupientibus igitur consequi salutem. Insinuandum est que sit fides catholica. et que sit debita baptismo custodia. et que dei mandatorum obseruantia .i. uite mundicia. Et primo que sit fidei doctrina in simboli serie contenta.</I> &ETH;re &thorn;ing ben &thorn;at elch man habben mot. &thorn;e wile his cristendom leden. &thorn;at on is rihte bileue. &thorn;at o&eth;er is fulohtninge. &thorn;e &eth;ridde &thorn;e faire liflode. and he nis naht fulliche cristene. &thorn;at is ani wane <MILESTONE N="10" UNIT="p">of &thorn;ese &thorn;rie. Of &thorn;e bileue spec&eth; ure louerd ihesu crist on &thorn;e holie godspelle. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. Qui non crediderit condempnabitur. &ETH;e man &thorn;e ne haue&eth; rihte bileue on him. he be&eth; dempd to &thorn;olie wowe mid deflen on helle. Of &thorn;e fulcninge he spec&eth; on o&eth;er stede. on &thorn;e godspelle. and sei&eth;. Nisi quis renatus fuerit ex aqua et cetera. Ne mai noman cume to godes riche. bute he be fulcned. 
<PB REF="00000045.tif" N="17"> Of clene liflade spec&eth; ysaias &thorn;e prophete &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Lauamini mundi estote.</I> wasse&eth; geu and wunie&eth; clene. and daui&eth; in &thorn;e salter boc. <I>A delicto meo munda me domine.</I> Clense me louerd of mine synnes. <I>Et alibi. Asperges me domine ysopo et cetera.</I> Bispreng me mid edmodnesse louerd &thorn;anne be ich clene. Ac for &thorn;at elch man be&eth; on fulcninge of alle synnen. and ogh to cunnen his bileue ar he fulcninge underfo. &thorn;arfore ic wile segen ow gure bileue. and gure bede. and tachen hit ew bi godes fultume. &ETH;e rihte bileue setten &thorn;e twolue apostles on write; ar hie ferden in to al middeneard to bodien cristendome. Ac elch of hem wrot his uers. and sainte peter he wrot &thorn;at formeste. and &thorn;e salme &thorn;e hie alle writen is cleped <I>credo</I>. After &thorn;e formeste word of &thorn;e salme. and ate biginninge of cristendom; elch man leornede <I>pater noster.</I> and <I>credo;</I> ar &thorn;an he fulcninge understoden. And &thorn;o waren manie childre dede fulehtlese and forlorene. and &thorn;arfore <MILESTONE N="11" UNIT="p">hit is iset lage bi ure drihtenes wissunge. &thorn;at me sal children fuluhtnie. and here godfaderes sullen for hem andswerie bifore &thorn;e prest ate fanstone. and ben here boreges togenes gode ate chireche dure; and inboreges ate fanstone. &thorn;at hie sulle cunne here bileue. and here bede; &thorn;at is &thorn;e <I>pater noster</I> and <I>credo.</I> &thorn;ane hie lernie mugen and ben bileffulle men and rihtwise. And &thorn;at ne mugen &thorn;e godfaderes naht don; bute hie here bileue cunnen. and nime to &thorn;e children muchele geme. Ne noman ne agh werne. &thorn;anne me him for nede &thorn;ar to bit. Alle cunne ower crede &thorn;aste ich wene. &thorn;eih ge alle nuten hwat hit bique&eth;e. Ac luste&eth; nu and undernime&eth; hit. and ich wille tachen eu bi godes fultume. &thorn;at ge sulle witen. and segge ou &thorn;e crede word after word. and &thorn;armid hwat elch word bitocne&eth;.</P>
<P><I>Credo in deum.</I> Ic bileue on god. <I>Patrem omnipotentem.</I> &thorn;ene almihti fader. <I>Creatorem celi et terre.</I> Suppende and wealdende of heuene and of eor&eth;. and of alle safte. &ETH;is word <I>credo</I> man mai understonden on &thorn;re wise. <I>Credo deo.</I> Ich leue gode. &thorn;at o&eth;er is. <I>Credo deum.</I> Ich ileue &thorn;at god is. &thorn;ese 
<PB REF="00000047.tif" N="19"> two &thorn;ing don alle he&eth;en men. Ac &thorn;e &eth;ridde ne do&eth; noman bute &thorn;e gode cristene. <I>Qui credit in deum.</I> &thorn;at is he &thorn;e bileue&eth; in god. and &thorn;arto moten fif &thorn;ing to bileuen in god. <I>Scilicet</I> <MILESTONE N="[12]" UNIT="p"> <I>eum dominum omnium recognoscere. super omnia obedire.</I> &thorn;at on is cnowen him to louerd ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;at o&eth;er is luuien him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;at &eth;ridde is hauen eie of him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;at feor&eth; is wur&eth;en him ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;at fifte is herien him ouer alle &thorn;ing. Man &thorn;e haue&eth; on him &thorn;os fif &thorn;inges; he haue&eth; on him rihte bileue. and gef him be&eth; oni &thorn;arof wane; he nis naht bilefful man. Nu ich eu habbe opened &thorn;es fif word. <I>Credo in deum patrem omnipotentem creatorem celi et terre.</I> Here&eth; nu &thorn;es o&eth;re. <I>Et in ihesum Christum filium eius unicum.</I> and ich bileue on &thorn;e helende crist. his onlepi sune. <I>Dominum nostrum.</I> Vre louerd he is cleped helende. for &thorn;at he manken alesede of &thorn;e dea&eth;liche atter. &thorn;e &thorn;e ealde deuel bleu uppen adam. and on his ofspreng. swo &thorn;at here fifealde mihte was altegeder attred. Ac ure louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;urh his holie fif wunden shedde his blod. and &thorn;at gef mankin to drinken. and &thorn;armide ut of hem &thorn;at dea&eth;liche atter. and mid his shorte dea&eth;e lesde hem ut of eche dea&eth;e. and mid his e&eth;eliche sore redde hem ut of eche sicnesse. and gef hem eche hele alle &thorn;o &thorn;e hit healde willen. and &thorn;eih alle men ben godes children. for &thorn;at he hem alle shop; and ches hem to sunes and to dohtres. na&eth;eles ure helende crist is his onlepi sune. noht after chesunge ac after strene for &thorn;an he him strende. alse &thorn;e sunne strene&eth; liht. &thorn;ane he tospret into al &thorn;esse wide worelde. and is &thorn;arfore cleped &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="[13]" UNIT="p">heuenliche fader sune. for &thorn;e fader is on &thorn;e sune on &thorn;rie wise. &thorn;at on is on westme. for &thorn;at he is muchel and mihti ouer alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;at o&eth;er is on wlite; for &thorn;at &thorn;e mone and &thorn;e sunne wundrie&eth; of faire. swo fair is ure louerd ihesu crist. and &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is on &thorn;ewe; for he is ful of alle godnesse. And &thorn;eih ure louerd ihesu crist bie alre manne<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> safte.</NOTE> louerd. na&eth;eles he nis naht alre manne louerd. &thorn;eih hie ben alle on his name turned. for hie ne heren him naht alle. nomo ne heren ure louerd ihesu crist bute &thorn;e rihtwise. and &thorn;e bileffulle. and &thorn;e godfrihte. for alle &thorn;e unrihtwise men &thorn;e grete synnes drigen; hersumie&eth; &thorn;e deuel. and &thorn;e hwile here louerd he bie&eth;. 
<PB REF="00000049.tif" N="21"> and &thorn;arfore h[i]e lie&eth; &thorn;an hie crist louerd clepie&eth;. and &thorn;e hwile ne helpe&eth; noht. &thorn;at hie singe&eth; <I>pater noster ne crede</I>. Ure louerd ihesu geue us rihte bileue. and alle &thorn;o nede habbe&eth; to ure liues ende. amen. <I>Qui conceptus est.</I> we habbe&eth; bigunnen to sege ou on englis hwat bitocne&eth; &thorn;e crede. &thorn;at elch cristeneman oh to cunnen. and habbe&eth; seid &thorn;arof tweien uers. and wile nu &thorn;e &thorn;ridde. Ich bileue on &thorn;e helende crist. &thorn;e &thorn;at holie maiden ure lafdie seinte marie on hire inno&eth;e understod of &thorn;e holie gost. noht of mannes strene ne on lichamliche luste. ac alswo gie on ower herte unde[r]stonden &thorn;e word of mi mu&eth; &thorn;e ich speke to eu. alswo &thorn;e engel hit seide &thorn;o he hire brohte &thorn;e blisfule ti&eth;inge. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Ecce concipies et cetera.</I> &thorn;u shalt understonde child on &thorn;ine inno&eth;e. and cnowen <MILESTONE N="14" UNIT="p">for cnauechild and clepen hit helende. and hit sal ben king on &thorn;e endelese kineriche. &thorn;o and|swerede ure lafdi sainte marie and seide. <I>Quomodo fiet istud quoniam uirum non cognosco?</I> whu shal &thorn;at wur&eth;e si&eth;&eth;en wap|man me ne [a]trine&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> trine&eth;.</NOTE>. and &thorn;e engel hire andswerede and seide. <I>Spiritus sanctus super ueniet in te et cetera.</I> &thorn;e holie gast wile cumen uppen &thorn;e. and godes mihte make &eth;e mid childe. and hwanne hit be&eth; iboren; men sullen clepen hit godes bern. &thorn;o andswerede &thorn;e lafdie sainte marie and seide. <I>Ecce ancilla domini fiat michi secundum uerbum tuum.</I> Ich am cristes maiden. alse &thorn;u hauest iseid; swo mote hit wur&eth;e. &thorn;us mildeliche andswerede &thorn;e milde quen of heuene and of eor&eth;e. and of alle safte. and &thorn;us bicam ure lafdi Sainte Marie mid childe. &thorn;onked be ure louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;o &eth;e time cam swo &thorn;at hire ne oc. ne ne smeart. ne hire mai&eth;hod ne was awemned. <I>Passus sub pontio pilato.</I> he was pined on pilates andwealde. <I>Crucifixus Mortuus</I>. His holie lichame was tospred on &thorn;e holie rode, and nailed &thorn;arto his fet; and his honden. and mid speres orde opened his swete side. and his heued heled mid &thorn;ornene crune. and on fele wise rewliche tuked. and &thorn;us he &thorn;rewede for to &thorn;at ilche time. &thorn;at he dea&eth; &thorn;olede. for to beten ure nede; he<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>originally</I> &thorn;e.</NOTE> ne hadde him selue nane. <I>Et sepultus.</I> And was his holie lichame leid in burieles in &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="[15]" UNIT="p">holie sepulcre. &thorn;at men sechen giet in ierusalem. <I>Descendit ad inferos.</I> and he ferde in to helle and 
<PB REF="00000051.tif" N="23"> brac helle gaten; and bond &thorn;e deuel .i. <I>abstulit ei quam exercu|erat potestatem. trahendi ad infernum animas &aacute; corporibus exutas</I>. formest he binam him alle &thorn;e mihte &thorn;e he hadde nutted fram<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. fran.</NOTE> &thorn;e biginninge of &thorn;e worelde. for to &thorn;e time cam &thorn;at he heregede helle. and nam<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. nan.</NOTE> ut mid him alle &thorn;e him hadden ar wel hersumed. <I>Tercia die resurrexit &aacute; mortuis</I>. On &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai he aros of dea&eth;e. and wunede mid his apostles. for to &thorn;e fower|tu&eth;e dai. noht alegate; ac stund-mele. <I>Ascendit ad celos</I>. &THORN;o he steah to heuene. swo &thorn;at his apostles and muchel o&eth;er folc mid eien bihielden hwu he upwende. <I>Sedet ad dextram dei patris omnipotentis.</I> and sit on rihthalf &thorn;es almihtie faderes. <I>Inde uenturus iudicatum uiuos et mortuos.</I> &ETH;anne he cume&eth; eft to demen &thorn;e quike and &thorn;e deade. and to geue &thorn;e gode eche lif and blisse on heuene. and &thorn;e iuele; eche wowe and pine on helle. bo&eth;e to same &thorn;e sowle and &thorn;e lichame. <I>Credo in spiritum sanctum.</I> Ich bileue on &thorn;e holie gost. &thorn;e is mid &thorn;e fader. and mid &thorn;e sune on mihti god. <I>Sanctam ecclesiam catholicam.</I> and ich leue. &thorn;at chireche is holi godes hus on eor&eth;e. and is cleped on boc kiriaca .<I>i. dominicalis</I> &thorn;at is on englis louerdlich hus. and is &thorn;erto nemned. for &thorn;e heuenliche kinges <MILESTONE N="16" UNIT="p">lichame is to setnesse &thorn;arinne. and &thorn;arfore men sullen aure &thorn;ider gon. and hem &thorn;ar bidden. and godes word heren. and lernie hwu hie sullen here lif laden on godes hersumpnesse. and hem swo gaderen on rihte bileue. &thorn;at hie ben on godes wunienge. &thorn;at he ben turned on one lauerd. to one bileue. to one fulcninge. <I>Sanctorum communionem</I> and ich ileue &thorn;at halgan ben on mode. and on rede. and habben ferrede on alle holinesse. <I>Remissionem peccatorum.</I> and ich leue &thorn;at &thorn;urh so&eth; scrifte synnes ben forgeuene. So&eth; scrifte understonde&eth; man. &thorn;anne he his muchele synnes mid alle for|lete&eth;. and sore bimurne&eth;. and shewe&eth; hem his messe preste. and bete&eth; hem alse he him wisse&eth;. <I>Carnis resurrectionem.</I> And ich leue &thorn;at mankin shal a domesdai risen of dea&eth;e. and elch man heren his dom bi eftemeste erdede. <I>Et uitam eternam amen.</I> and alle men shullen cume to libben echeliche. &thorn;e g&oacute;de on eche blisse and wele mid ure louerd ihesu crist on heuene. &thorn;e &uacute;uele on eche wowe and pine mid &thorn;e deuel o[n] helle. sowle and licam abuten ende.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="5" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000053.tif" N="25">
<HEAD>V. PATER NOSTER.</HEAD>
<P><I>Pater noster et cetera.</I> &ETH;u singest &thorn;e salm &thorn;e me clepe&eth; crede. &thorn;u seist &thorn;at on gode bileuest. and dost cnownesse &thorn;at he is &thorn;i louerd. ac &thorn;anne &thorn;u singest &thorn;e salm &thorn;at is cleped <I>pater noster.</I> <MILESTONE N="17" UNIT="p">After &thorn;e forme word of &thorn;e salme; abugest gode. and cnewlest togenes him. and biddest &thorn;at all his wille wur&eth;e. and menest to him &thorn;ine fele nede. and biddest &thorn;at he hem alle bete. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>[P]ater noster qui es in celis.</I> fader ure &thorn;u ert in heuene. &thorn;e holie &thorn;remnesse &thorn;e shop and biwalt alle shafte; we clepie&eth; ure fader for two &thorn;ing. on his for &thorn;o &thorn;e he us shop; and feide &thorn;e lemes to ure licame. and &thorn;e sowle &thorn;arto. &thorn;e sene to &thorn;e egen. &thorn;e hlust to &thorn;e earen. and to elche lime limpliche mihte. and swo digeliche hit al dihte; &thorn;at on elche feinge is hem on sene. and eft he us wile feie; &thorn;anne we shulen arisen of dea&eth;e. and for&thorn;i we clepe&eth; him fader for &thorn;at he us feide here. O&eth;er is &thorn;at he fet alle liuiende &thorn;ing. &thorn;e bi mete liuien. alle nutten openliche; and gres and trowen dieliche. Ac on of alle nutten &thorn;at is man. he fet on two wise. noht alle; ac sume. &ETH;o unriht|wise openliche mid licames bileue; and &thorn;e sowle mid hire bileue. and &thorn;eih he alle &thorn;ing &thorn;us fede; he nis na&eth;emo nemned heore alre manne<NOTE PLACE="marg">? fader.</NOTE> &thorn;eih hem alle fede. ac sunderlepes he is here fader mid wisse. &thorn;e on rihte bileue. and on so&eth;e luue understant his holie fles. and his holie blod. &thorn;at ben &thorn;e rihtwise. and &thorn;e bilea|fule. and &thorn;e godfrihte men; &thorn;e lade&eth; her lif alse me hem in chireche lere&eth;. and &thorn;o &thorn;e swo ne don; habben to fader &thorn;e deuel &thorn;e fet hem alle &thorn;o &thorn;e him folege&eth;. <MILESTONE N="18" UNIT="p">and on &thorn;e forme men; alle ueide er. and mid licames luste; alle unbilefulle men &thorn;e &thorn;o weren. and get ben. he fede&eth;. and is &thorn;arfore hore fader. <I>Sanctificetur nomen tuum.</I> bledsed be &thorn;i name on us. swo &thorn;at we on alle ure &thorn;anke. &thorn;e heien on alle ure worden. &thorn;e herien; on alle ure deden &thorn;e wur&eth;ien. and ouer alle &thorn;ing &thorn;e luuien. and swo 
<PB REF="00000055.tif" N="27"> ernien &thorn;at we habben moten of &thorn;ine holie name &thorn;e tocne imene. <I>Adueniat regnum tuum.</I> Cume &thorn;i rixlinge. To sume men cume&eth; ure louerd ihesu crist. and litle hwile mid hem bileue&eth; and si&eth;&eth;en him forlete&eth;. Swilche ben alle &thorn;o &thorn;e here&eth; godes word on lor spelle. and &thorn;enchen &thorn;at hie wille&eth; here synnes leten. and ne don. To sume men cume&eth; ure louerd ihesu crist. and bileue&eth; mid him. and na&eth;emo ne rixle&eth; noht on him. Swilche ben alle &thorn;o &thorn;e hauen here synnes forleten. and bi prestes wiss|inge hem gernliche bete&eth;. To sume men he cume&eth;. and bigin|ne&eth; on him to rixle on &thorn;is e&eth;eliche liue. and wille fulliche rixle on him eft on &thorn;e eche liue. ac swilche ben arue&eth; finde. nu abuuen eor&eth;e. and na&eth;eles manie be&eth; get. &thorn;o ben &thorn;e godfrihte &thorn;e clene ben of synnes. and lete&eth; unwur&eth; of alle woreld wunne. and luue&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. liue&eth;.</NOTE> rihtliche alle liuiende men. and ben hersume alle godes hese. and is &thorn;is woreld lo&eth;. and habbe&eth; longinge to heuene. and ne gierne&eth; to none &thorn;inge; bute after godes wille. <I>Fiat uoluntas tua sicut in celo</I> <MILESTONE N="19" UNIT="p"> <I>et in terra.</I> Wur&eth;e &thorn;i wil on eor&eth;e swo hit is on heuene. swo &thorn;at me &thorn;e quemen of here liflode on eor&eth;e. alse don &thorn;e engles on heuene. <I>Panem nostrum cotidianum da nobis hodie.</I> Gif us to dai ure daihwamliche bred. Al hit is cleped bred; &thorn;at is mannes bileue; ac na&eth;eles bred bitocne&eth; &thorn;re bileues. On is &thorn;e mete. &thorn;e &thorn;e lichame bruke&eth; and biliue&eth;. &ETH;at o&eth;er is godes word. &thorn;at is &thorn;e sowle fode. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is for mete &thorn;at ilch man agh mid him to leden. &thorn;an he sal of &thorn;esse liue faren. &thorn;at is cristes holie licame. &thorn;e giue&eth; alle men eche lif. and blisse in heuene. and gief we wise ben; we mugen mid one worde &thorn;ese &thorn;rie &thorn;ing bidden. and ben bene ti&eth;e. <I>Et dimitte nobis debita nostra.</I> And forgiue us ure gultes &thorn;e we hauen don. and ofte on idel &thorn;onke. on unnet speche. on iuele dede. and muchele mo si&eth;e &thorn;anne we segen mugen. <I>Sicut et nos dimit|timus debitoribus nostris.</I> And swo forgiue us ure gultes. swo we don hem here &thorn;e us agult habbe&eth;. Ne mai no man &thorn;ese word seggen &thorn;anne he godes milce bisec&eth;. gief he haue&eth; on his heorte onde. o&eth;er ni&eth;. o&eth;er hatiunge to his emcristene. &thorn;at he him seluen fram gode ne dele&eth;. Ac bidde&eth; &thorn;at godes wra&eth;&eth;e cume uppen his ogen heued. <I>Et ne nos inducas in temptationem.</I> 
<PB REF="00000057.tif" N="29"> Louerd shild us fram elche pine of helle. Elch pine is fremed on &thorn;re fold wise. On is &thorn;e defles tuihting and mislore, &thorn;at o&eth;er is mannes licunge. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is mannes wille. <MILESTONE N="20" UNIT="p">&thorn;ane he wile don. o&eth;er que&eth;en hwat him &thorn;anne lica&eth; after defles lore. &thorn;e egginge and &thorn;e likinge him bringe&eth; in to helle pine. &ETH;re &thorn;ing be&eth; &thorn;at mankin heuie&eth;. On is &thorn;e selue lust. o&eth;er is iuel lehtres. &ETH;e &thorn;ridde flesliche lustes. and &thorn;ese two &thorn;e ben leihter and lust; uulste&eth; &thorn;e &thorn;ridde &thorn;at is &thorn;e flesliche lust. &thorn;e mankinne for|lere&eth;. and al hit is bi &thorn;e deuel. &thorn;at men &thorn;us forlerede. Alse hit bi &thorn;e wimman and bi sheawere. hie bihalt hire sheawere. and cume&eth; hire shadewe &thorn;aronne. &thorn;e shadewe hire tache&eth;. hwu hie mai hire seluen wenlukest makien. for hie wule liken alle &thorn;e lechures &thorn;e on hire loke&eth;. and swo dragen hem to hire. Al swo cume&eth; &thorn;e deuel in to &thorn;e mannes herte &thorn;an he wile healde sunder|rune wi&eth; him. and &thorn;us que&eth;. &ETH;u ert wel don man. and &thorn;arto wur&eth;lich. Gef &thorn;u takest to huse &thorn;u best men &thorn;e unwur&eth;ure ac gef &thorn;u werest elche dai faire clo&eth;es. and best rum-handed to glewmen and to hores. &thorn;u shalt ben lef and wur&eth;. and liken alle men. To &thorn;e man &thorn;at is ni&eth;ful. he speke&eth; on his herte and &thorn;us que&eth;. Ful mai &thorn;e &thorn;inke &thorn;at forcu&eth;er haue&eth; faire weden. and &thorn;u unwreste. and he wereldes richeise and &thorn;u ware betre wur&eth;e. Wi&eth; &thorn;e hatiende man he spec&eth; on his herte. Nu shalt [&thorn;u hatien] &thorn;o &thorn;e iuel hauen don. and biremen him mid euel wordes. <MILESTONE N="21" UNIT="p">and maken him to forlesen his aihte. vnwreste &thorn;u best gef &thorn;u wreche ne secst. hwanne &thorn;u time siest. gief mihte &thorn;e &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>ne.</I></NOTE> atiere&eth;. To &thorn;e eiht-gradi men he rune&eth; on his herte and &thorn;us que&eth;. Gef &thorn;u best aihteles &thorn;u best unwur&eth;. and lo&eth;. ac gef &thorn;u hauest woreld wele. &thorn;u miht &thorn;arof wur&eth;liche fare. and swo loken &thorn;e &thorn;at &thorn;u best lef and wur&eth;. and miht for ure drihtenes luue fele almes dele. &thorn;eih &thorn;u hit mid unrihte bigete. o&eth;er on untime. Gif &thorn;arof for godes luue. &thorn;anne be&eth; &thorn;e synne forgiuen. gef &thorn;i prest nis clene man. &thorn;e shal &thorn;ine to&eth;inge understonden. del hit men &thorn;e muge bidde for &eth;e. To &thorn;e narewe herted man on his &thorn;onke he sei&eth;. witte wel hwat &thorn;u hauest. walte hwat &thorn;e tide. and cune sume me&eth;e &thorn;enne &thorn;u almesse makest. &ETH;u hauest e&eth;eliche bi aihte to helpen &thorn;ine kenne. wel wur&eth; wunne be of wur&eth;shipe swo 
<PB REF="00000059.tif" N="31"> hit be. On &thorn;e drunken men he rune&eth; mid his herte and sei&eth;. Esteliche eten. and drinken make&eth; &thorn;e man fair. and wurliche. and on manie mihte &thorn;at &thorn;u etest and drinkest and werest. &thorn;at &thorn;u hauest. and gef &thorn;u ani &thorn;ing spelest and leuest. &thorn;at &thorn;u fo[r]lest. On &thorn;e gole men he gel&eth; wi&eth; his herte. and &thorn;us que&eth;. Gef &thorn;e is lef &thorn;in hele. heald &thorn;in cunde. and &thorn;ine licames lust kel ilome. and naht on feawe ac on fele wise. &thorn;e wile falle wel to echen &thorn;is woreld. Gef &thorn;u strene wult haue; <MILESTONE N="[22]" UNIT="p">ne haue &thorn;u naht &thorn;in ogen wif. ac o&eth;er mannes imene. &thorn;eih lerdemen segen &thorn;at hit be muchel sunne &thorn;at man his licames lust drige. ofte &thorn;eih hie bispused ben. and don hit for strene. here liflode ligne&eth; hem seluen. for ne do&eth; hit none swo ofte se &thorn;e hodede. &thorn;e naue&eth; him selue naht on ac fele imene. and gef he &thorn;at hielde synne. he wolde &thorn;e dede wi&eth;|tien. &ETH;us deuel egge&eth; &aelig;lch man on his herte. and maca&eth; &thorn;at he wule do &thorn;at he him to teihte. <I>Set libera nos &aacute; malo</I>. Ac les us louerd of his egginge. and of alle iuele. <I>amen</I>. swo hit wur&eth;e.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="6" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>VI. IN DIE NATALIS DOMINI.</HEAD>
<P><I>Natus est nobis hodie saluator qui est Christus in ciuitate daui&eth;</I>. Gode ti&eth;inge and murie to heren. us telle&eth; &thorn;e louerd se[i]nte lucas; on &thorn;e holie godspelle. and sei&eth; &thorn;at on holie erndrake hem brohte fram heuene. to &thorn;e londe of ierusalem. and tealde &thorn;e herdes &thorn;e wakeden ouer here oref. biside &thorn;e burch belleem. luste&eth; nu and undernime&eth; hwu he se ti&eth;inge teald[e] word after word. On &thorn;e niht and on &thorn;e time. &thorn;e ure lafdi seinte marie kennede of holie lichame ure louerd ihesu crist. were herdes wakiende bi side &thorn;e buregh and wittende here oref. &ETH;o cam on angel of heuene to hem. and stod bisides hem. and godes brihtnesse bilihte hem. and hie waren swi&eth;e offurihte. and ofdredde. <I>Et ait angelus eis. Nolite timere.</I> and &thorn;e engel qua&eth; to hem ne be ge <MILESTONE N="23" UNIT="p">naht ofdredde. <I>[E]cce enim euangelizo uobis et cetera.</I> 
<PB REF="00000061.tif" N="33"> Ich ew bringe ti&eth;inge &thorn;e shule ben a folke to muchele blisse. Ne wot no man hwat blisse is; &thorn;e naure wowe ne bod. Ac swo &thorn;e wowe &thorn;inke&eth; biter. &thorn;e hwile &thorn;e he leste&eth;. swo &thorn;inc&eth; wele &thorn;e swettere &thorn;an hit cume&eth; &thorn;arafter. Al mankin was wunende on muchele wowe. sum on &thorn;isse worelde. and sum on helle pine. forte &thorn;at ilke time; &thorn;at ure louerd ihesu crist hem &thorn;arof a|redde. and turnede swo here wowe to wele. and here sor to muchele blisse. and of &thorn;esse blisse spec&eth; &thorn;e engel. and sewe&eth; &aacute; whilche wise. and &thorn;uregh hwam &thorn;is blisse cumen sholde. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Natus est nobis hodie et cetera.</I> Vs is boren to dai helende. &thorn;at is crist &thorn;e louerd on daui&eth;es burehg. <I>Hoc autem dixit. quia societas hominum erat ad impletura numerum ange|lorum.</I> &ETH;os word sede &thorn;e engel for &thorn;at man sholde fuluullen englene sete. &thorn;e was er iwaned; &thorn;o &thorn;e lucifer and his ferreden fellen ut &thorn;arof. and naht for englen unhele &thorn;e habbe&eth; eche hele. ac for mannen unhele. &thorn;e ben alle and hauen ben alle si&eth;en unlimpe cam uppen ure forme fader adam. alse ure drihten sei&eth; on &thorn;e holie godspelle. <I>Homo quidam descendebat ab ierusalem in ierico et incidit in latrones. et cetera.</I> Ure louerd ih[es]u crist sei&eth;. &thorn;at a man ferde fram iherusalem into ierico. and bicam uppe &thorn;eues. and hie <MILESTONE N="24" UNIT="p">him bireueden alle hise riche weden. and wundeden him swi&eth;e sore. and forleten him unne&eth;e liues. &THORN;is is seid bi adam. <I>Qui descendit &aacute; beatitudine c&aelig;li. in defectus huius mundi.</I> &ETH;at was adam &thorn;e ferde ut fram<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. fran.</NOTE> &thorn;e fulle edinesse of paradis. in to &thorn;esse wrecheliche hateringe of &thorn;isse worelde. and ledde after him neih &thorn;an al his ofspreng. <I>Et incidit in latrones</I> and bicam uppen utlagen. &thorn;at waren deflen. <I>Qui despolia|uerunt eum gratia immortalitatis innocencia</I>. &ETH;e bireueden him alle his riche weden. &thorn;at waren unerned giue. and unde&eth;licnesse. and lo&eth;lesnesse. Mid &thorn;ese &thorn;re weden ure louerd ihesu crist him hadde warned togenes &thorn;re fon. <I>Scilicet peccatum. dolorem. mortem.</I> togenes synne. and sor. and dea&eth;. <I>Et plagis impositis abiecerunt.</I> and si&eth;en<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. si&eth;er.</NOTE> hie hadden bireued him &thorn;us; swo hie for|wundeden him welneih to dea&eth;e. <I>Inferentes eis plagas .i. humanorum defectuum causas</I>. &thorn;e wundes &thorn;at hie on him makeden; ben &thorn;e manifeald synnes. &thorn;e hie on him brohten. &thorn;o &thorn;e hie 
<PB REF="00000063.tif" N="35"> openeden hi[s] earen to luste &thorn;e defles lore. and his eien to bihealden &thorn;e forbodene appel. and hef his honde hit to nimen. and mid &thorn;e nose &thorn;arto te smullen. and mid his mu&eth; &thorn;arof et. and &thorn;urh &thorn;es fifealde gultes. forleas &thorn;e fiffeald mihten &thorn;e god him gef &thorn;o &thorn;e he him shop. swo &thorn;at he ne &thorn;urte naure &thorn;olen hunger. ne &thorn;urst. ne woninge. ne chele. ne werinesse. <MILESTONE N="25" UNIT="p">ne elde. ne un|hel&eth;e. ne de&eth;. ac for &thorn;at he dide &thorn;ise synnes god wrac and binom him &thorn;ese mihtes alle: and he bicom unmihti. and wreche. and unhol. and his ofspring al. &thorn;rowude on synne. and on unmihte and on wowe and gemerliche pineden. &thorn;e wile &thorn;e hie here weren; and wuneden. hwile mid hunger. hwile mid &thorn;urste. hwile mid chele. hwile mid hete. hwile mid sorinesse. hwile mid werinesse. and ofte mid wurmene icheu. and mid elde. mid unhel&eth;e. mid o&eth;re wowe inohg. and ettan ende mid de&eth;e. and on swiche unhel&eth;e wisseden<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>or</I> willeden</NOTE> georne efter helende. and he com. &thorn;anked wur&eth;e him; to helen hem of heore synwunden. and to winden hem on &thorn;a wurhliche weden &thorn;e &thorn;e dieuel binom ure forme fader adam. &thorn;at wes. <I>Sstola</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in <I>MS</I>.</NOTE> <I>inmortalitatis.</I> &thorn;at is &thorn;e blisse of eche liue. and to giuende &thorn;e mihtes &thorn;e adam for|gremede us alle. <I>Scilicet gaudium plenum.</I> &thorn;at is &thorn;e uulle of endelese blisse. And alse he sende erendrake biforen him to cu&eth;en &thorn;at he cumen wolde. and &thorn;at were patriarkes and prophetes. and engles. ealse he sende erendrake &thorn;o he com. and &thorn;at wes &thorn;e engel &thorn;e ich er embe spec. &thorn;e cudde &thorn;e herdes &thorn;e biwak|eden here oref; bisides &thorn;e burehg bethleem &thorn;at &thorn;e helende was &thorn;erinne iboren. Ne was &thorn;e engel isend ne to kinge. ne to eorle. ne to barun. ne to none hege; ne oregele men on &thorn;e wurelde wi&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. &thorn;i&eth;.</NOTE> to spekende. ac to loge; <MILESTONE N="26" UNIT="p">and e&eth;eliche men alse heordes bu&eth;. ac for&thorn;i ich wile seggen giu nime&eth; geme &thorn;erto. and under|stonde&eth; it hwat &thorn;o heordes bitocne&eth;. and wat &thorn;e ni[h]t wecches. and hwat &thorn;at oref and alre erest hwat &thorn;e wilde deor &thorn;e &thorn;is oref wane&eth;. and wile bicachen it. and wile forstelen. and wile mid stre[n]g&eth;e binimen. Of &thorn;is deor spec&eth; seinte peter &thorn;us que&thorn;ende. <I>ADuersarius uester diabolus tamquam leo rugiens circuit que|rens quem deuoret</I>. Vre fo &thorn;at is &thorn;e deuel wuandre&eth; abuten us he te&eth; for&eth; geres hwile after fox. hwile after wulue. hwile 
<PB REF="00000065.tif" N="37"> after leun. hwile after o&eth;re. and on ech of hise deden is iefned to &thorn;e deore wuas geres he for&eth;teo&eth;. <I>GReges sunt. oues et boues. capre et porci</I>. &ETH;et oref &thorn;e &thorn;is deor wane&eth; be&eth; shep and re&eth;eren. and Get. and swin; and bitocne&eth; men. Sume men lede&eth; clene liflode. and ne do&eth; ne ne que&eth;e&eth; none manne lo&eth; ac luuige&eth; god. and go&eth; eche dai to chirche alse shep to uolde. and do&eth; gladliche here rihte to chirche and elmesse wreche men. and be&eth; cleped shepisse men. Sume men ne willen non unriht; ac winned wi&eth; &thorn;e eor&eth;e. and tiliget michel to o&eth;re mann&aelig;s bihof&thorn;e. and &thorn;ese men be&eth; icleped ru&eth;erihsse. men of &thorn;ese shepishse; and ru&eth;erishse men. spec&eth; &thorn;e prophete &thorn;us que|&thorn;inde. <I>Subiecisti sub pedibus eius. oues et boues.</I> &thorn;at is to seggen &thorn;e shepisse and &thorn;e netisse men be&eth; under cristes &thorn;ralshipe. Sume men leden here[lif] alse get; o&thorn;er buckes <I>Hoc animal pas|cit in altum et est libidinosum.</I> <MILESTONE N="27" UNIT="p">&ETH;is oref is swi&eth;e egerne. and feche&eth; his leswe. hwile uppen trewes. and hwile uppen cliues. and hwile in &thorn;e dales. and stinc&eth; fule for his golnesse. Swo ben alle oregel men. &thorn;e telle&eth; hem seluen heige. and drie&eth; hor|dom. and of &thorn;e hore fule stinke&eth;. and of swilche men sei&eth; ure louerd ihesu crist. <I>Statuet quidem hedos a sinistris. et mittet in ignem eternum.</I> A domes dai sulle buckes. and &thorn;e get. &thorn;o ben &thorn;e wapmen and &thorn;e wimmen &thorn;e hordom drien. stonden an ure louerd ihesu cristes lift hond. and hem sal senden into &thorn;at eche fur on helle mid alle deflen. Sume men lade&eth; here lif on etinge and on drinkinge alse swin. &thorn;e uulie&eth; and wrote&eth; and sneuie&eth; aure fule. and ful &thorn;ing muchel bruke&eth;. and &thorn;an hie fulle be&eth;. hie seche&eth; to &thorn;e fule floddri. and &thorn;aron walewe&eth;. Swo do&eth; &thorn;e fule man &thorn;e folege&eth; his wombes wil. and of unrihte bigete ofte fille&eth;. &thorn;ane he bere&eth; abuten here senibhakel. and &thorn;e est metes and drinkes ut spewe&eth;. and &thorn;an he fulle ben. bisulie&eth; hem on &thorn;e fule floddri of drunkennesse. and of hordom. and &thorn;arfore ben icleped swinisse men. and on hem wune&eth; &thorn;e deuel. bi ure louerd ihesu cristes leue alse &thorn;e holie godspel sei&eth;. <I>Dominus eiecit legiones demonum de homine quodam et rogauerunt demones. Mitte nos in gregem porcorum. Et ingressi precipitauerunt porcos in mare.</I> &ETH;e holie godspel sei&eth; &thorn;at ure drihten 
<PB REF="00000067.tif" N="39"> drof fele deules togedere ut of &aacute; man &thorn;e was of his wit. <MILESTONE N="28" UNIT="p">and him swuo helde. and &thorn;e deules beden ure louerd ihesu crist &thorn;at he hem sende into floc of swin and he swo dide. and &thorn;e swin urnen alse deulen hem driuen; into &thorn;e s&aelig;. and druncnede hem seluen. Swa giued ure drihten leue &thorn;e deule to ben on &thorn;e swinisshe man &thorn;e ihc er of spec and on hem to wuniende and hem to drenchende. and of here wit to bringinde. and to driuen fram unrihte to o&thorn;er. fram e&eth;eliche laste to michele. fram synne to synne fram iuele to iuele and ettan ende hem drenche&eth; on shameliche de&eth;e and mid hem to helle lede&eth;. &ETH;ese fower man|nisshe &thorn;e ich er inemd habbe. be&eth; &thorn;at erf &thorn;e &thorn;o herdes ouer wuakeden. and &thorn;e selue herdes be&eth; &thorn;e lor&thorn;ewes of holi chiriche. &thorn;e lesewe&eth; here orf alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth; <I>IN pascuis uberimis pascunt ea.</I> on swete leswe. &thorn;o bin &thorn;e gode word of holi boc &thorn;e be&eth; &thorn;e saules lustliche bileue. alse estliche etingge and dringk|inge is te lichames. <I>INers pastor aut sedet in ignorancia aut accubitat in negligencia aut iacet in uoluntate.</I> &ETH;e unwreste herde sit on unwisdomnesse. for he ne can is orf gemen. o&eth;er hlone&eth; and slepe&eth;. and synege&eth; on gemeleste alse he &thorn;at is recheles and non eige ne stand of louerde. o&eth;er li&eth; on li&thorn;ere wille. and feste slepe&eth; on his synne. &thorn;anne cume&eth; &thorn;e wilde deor &thorn;e ich er seide and &thorn;at orf wane&eth; <I>Set boni pastores uigilant. et noctis uigilias custodiunt supra greges suos et pro illis se se hostibus opponunt.</I> Ac &thorn;e gode herdes <MILESTONE N="29" UNIT="p">wakie&eth; on faire liflode ouer here orf; &thorn;e &thorn;ei leswue&eth; on halie larspelle. and wisse&eth; hem to understanden wat is uuel and wat is god. and munege&eth; hem ofte un&eth;ewes to forberen. and gode &thorn;eawes to folgen. <I>Vita presens caliginosa est tenebris peccatorum.</I> al &thorn;is lif &thorn;e we on liuen is to nihte iefned for &thorn;at it is swa &thorn;ester of ure ateliche synnes <I>Hvius noctis sunt iiii</I><SUP>or</SUP> <I>uigilie SEro .i. puericia. MEdia nox adolescencia. GAlli cantus uirilis etas. MAne senium.</I> on &thorn;is niht be&eth; fowuer niht wecches. Biforen euen &thorn;e bilimpe&eth; to children. Mid-niht &eth;e bilimpe&eth; to frumberdligges. hanecrau &thorn;e bilimpe&eth; &thorn;owuene men. morgewile to alde men. &ETH;ese herdes &thorn;e be&eth; lor&thorn;ewes. alse bisshupes. and prestes wakie&eth; biforen euen; &thorn;anne &thorn;e childre wuel &thorn;ewuen. On midniht he wakeged &thorn;anne 
<PB REF="00000069.tif" N="41"> he frumberdlinges binime&eth; un&eth;eawes and gode teche&eth;. to hane|crau he wakege&eth; &thorn;anne he &thorn;o ful &thorn;ogene turne&eth; to godes bihou&thorn;e. In morgewile he wakege&eth; &thorn;anne he halde men turne&eth; to ure louerdes cristes blisse. &ETH;us agen alle gode herdes to wakegen gostliche. for &thorn;us wakeden &thorn;o herdes &thorn;e ich er of spec. &thorn;o &thorn;e hem &thorn;e ti&eth;inge com. &thorn;at ure louerd ihesu crist was boren. <I>QVi est uerus samaritanus scilicet custos hominum.</I> &thorn;at is alre herdene herde. and alre lechene leche. &thorn;e com to helen &thorn;e wundes. &thorn;e &thorn;e deuel hadde on mancun broht. alse ge er herden. <I>Alligauit uulnera infundens uinum et oleum:</I> Alle synfulle men &thorn;e heued-synnes<MILESTONE N="30" UNIT="p"> don habbe&eth;. and nelle&eth; &thorn;erof no shrift nimen; he bihat hem eche fur on helle bete<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> bute.</NOTE> hie forleten beten and milce bidden. Alle &thorn;o &thorn;e here synnen forlete&eth; and bete&eth; he hele&eth; heRe synwunden mid fulcnege. and gife&eth; us his holi fleis to daiwamliche bred and his holi blot<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> blod.</NOTE> to drunche. and bit us &thorn;at we shule &thorn;is notien on &thorn;is longe wowe and on &thorn;is wreche worelde. and bihat us to mede eche hele on &thorn;e helendes worelde. <I>Quod qui promisit dignetur reddere nobis. AMEN.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="7" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>VII. [IN EPIPHANIA DOMINI.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Reges tharsis et insule munera offerent. Reges arabum et saba dona adducent</I>. Mid mede man mai ouer water faren And mid weldede of giue; frend wuerche. and mid bicumeliche loke; man him mai cu&eth;leche wid kinge. Swo &thorn;e wise &thorn;e be&eth; seli. and &thorn;e unwise ne wile; for he is unseli. &ETH;e unwise man. and forwened child; habbe&eth; bo&eth;e on lage for &thorn;at hie habben wille&eth; bo&eth;e here wil; &thorn;eh it bi unwrast, and be&eth; &thorn;erefore un|wur&eth;e eche manne &thorn;e wise man and &thorn;at wel-&thorn;eaud child. habbe&eth; bo&eth;e on lage. for &thorn;an ei&eth;er lete&eth; his agen wille. and folge&eth; his lar&eth;ewes. Swo we age&eth; to don ure lichames wille to forleten. and folgen ure helendes lore. and his faire forbisne bi ure mihte. 
<PB REF="00000071.tif" N="43"> <I>Legitur quod dominus aliquando sub mercede nautica transfre|tauit.</I> We finde&eth; on &thorn;e holie boc. &thorn;at ure helende &thorn;at is alre wateres herde. he ferde sumwile mid mede ouere water. Swo bihoued us &thorn;at we don. &thorn;e be&eth; on &thorn;is shipe; &thorn;at is holi chirche. <MILESTONE N="31" UNIT="p">In &thorn;is watere &thorn;at ich of speke; &thorn;at is &thorn;is wreche wuereld. and is mid storme faste bistonden. &thorn;o be&eth; ure fule synnes. and fele odre wosi&eth;es.</P>
<P><I>PRoferamus ergo ei de cordis nostri thesauro fidei sensum. et sacrificacio laudis honorificemus eum. ut sine periculo uehet nos trans seculi pontum.</I> Vnderstonde we on ure heorte his holie wordes. and for&thorn;e we him ure rihte bileue. and luue; for gersum. and herien him; and hegen on alle ure mihte. and cunnen gif he wile setten us ouer &thorn;at michele water; hole and sunde. and seien mid &thorn;e salmwrihte. <I>NOn me demergat tempestas a. nec. o</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> a.</NOTE>. <I>et cetera.</I> louerd ne &thorn;aue &thorn;u &thorn;at storm me duue. ne &thorn;at &thorn;e deuel me swelge. ne &thorn;at &thorn;e pit tune<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ouer me his mu&eth;. Woreldes richeise weche&eth; orgel on mannes heorte. and deu&eth; him on helle; alse storm do&eth; &thorn;at ship in &thorn;e watere. Wanrede weche&eth; on mannes heorte ortruwe &thorn;e deu&eth; him on helle alse storm do&eth; man on watere. wi&eth; &thorn;ese tweien stormes wolde &thorn;e wise ben borgen; &thorn;e sei&eth; &thorn;us. <I>Diuicias et paupertates ne dederis michi sed tantum uictui necessaria</I>. louerd ne gif &thorn;u me no&thorn;er ne woreld winne ne meseise ac mi bare bileue. &thorn;at deuel forswuelge&eth; &thorn;e man. hwanne he falle&eth; on fule synnes. &thorn;e pit tine&eth; his mu&eth; ouer &thorn;e man; &thorn;e li&eth; on fule synnen &thorn;e him wel like&eth; and ne wile hem forleten. crist shilde us alle &thorn;er wi&eth;. and gif ure ani is &thorn;us for|swolgen. and &thorn;us penned. clupe we to ure louerd ihesu crist &thorn;us seggende <I>DE profundis clamavi ad [te] domine domine exaudi uocem meam.</I> <MILESTONE N="32" UNIT="p">On diepe wosi&eth;es ich clupe to &thorn;e hlouerd. hlouerd her mine stefne. do we ec mid ure wel dede &thorn;ingen us wi&eth; ure helende. was fo we be&eth; &thorn;anne we togenes his hese flite&eth;. and &thorn;is wreche weorld folgi&eth;. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth; <I>AMicus mundi constituitur inimicus dei</I>. Ech &thorn;at is weorldes frend is ure drihtenes fo. and halt flit wi&eth; him; alle &thorn;e wile &thorn;e he &thorn;e weorld folge&eth;. for ure gult god man bicom and Ure eldre waiteden him to dea&eth;e. o&eth;er hadde &thorn;e gult; and ure hlouerd 
<PB REF="00000073.tif" N="45"> ihesu crist hit acorede. alse him self sei&eth;. <I>QVe non rapui ex|soluebam</I>. Ich geald &thorn;at ich noht ne nam. and swo he dude &thorn;o[n]cked wur&eth;e him. &thorn;urh mannes gemeleste and &thorn;urh mannes recheleste and &thorn;urh mannes unwraste wil and naht bi his agene wille &thorn;e dea&eth; him wes iwealde. And &thorn;us man makede him sulfen fo &thorn;er he fren[d]shipe sholde. ac ure hlouerd ihesu crist is swo mild heorted. heged and wur&eth;ed bie he. for wanne &thorn;e man forlete&eth; his synnen. and bete&eth;. and milce bidde&eth;; &thorn;anne is here foshipe turnd al to frendshipe Eftsone we &thorn;e be&eth; uncu&eth;e &thorn;e heuenliche kinge. for &thorn;at ure liflode him swi&eth;e mislike&eth;. alse ne wile noht cnowe bute &thorn;at &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> we.</NOTE> him be&eth; queme. wile we ne cu&eth;|leche&eth; us wid him mid bicumeliche loke. and folged bi ure mihte &thorn;e faire forbisne of &thorn;e &thorn;re kinges &thorn;e comen of estriche. and cu&eth;lecheden hem wi&eth; him; mid &thorn;refeld loc. <I>Avro. Thure. Mirra.</I> &thorn;at is gold. and recheles. and mirre. <I>Tres reges signi|ficant. iij</I><SUP>es</SUP>. <I>ordines in eccl[es]ia scilicet Uirginum.</I> <MILESTONE N="33" UNIT="p"><I>Coniuga|torum. Continentium.</I> &ETH;o &thorn;re kinges bitocne&eth; &thorn;re hodes of bilefulle men. on is meidhod. &thorn;at o&eth;er spushod. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde widewehod. elch man &thorn;e lede&eth; is lif rihtliche on an of &thorn;ese &thorn;re hodes he is cleped king. for &thorn;at he kenne&eth; eure to rihte. and for&thorn;i him bicume&eth; &thorn;at he offri &thorn;e heuenliche kinge. &thorn;e &thorn;re loc &thorn;e ich er nemde. &thorn;at is gold. and recheles. and mirre. <I>Avrum in tributum regi. Thus in sacrificium deo. Mirram in sepulturam homini.</I> Gold bicume&eth; to kinge. Recheles to gode. mirre to dea&eth;liche men. <I>Avrum significat orationis cordis mundiciam propter sui puritatem. Thus significat orationis deuocionem propter sui redolenciam. Mirra carnis affliccionem propter sui amaritudinem.</I> Gold for is clennesse bitocne&eth; clene &thorn;onc. Rechelis for his swetnesse bitocne&eth; inwardliche bede. Mirre for ure biternesse bitocne&eth; &thorn;e lichames pine. &thorn;at man his synne mide bete&eth;. Wille we mid &thorn;ese &thorn;re lokes cu&eth;lechen us wi&eth; alre kingene king. and mid swiche weldede cu&eth;&eth;en us wi&eth; him. and giuen to mede wi&eth; &thorn;an &thorn;e he us lede of &thorn;is water. &thorn;at is &thorn;is weorld wowe. and to eche blisse lede. <I>Qui viuit et regnat deus per omnia secula seculorum. AMEN.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="8" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000075.tif" N="47">
<HEAD>VIII. [IN PURIFICATIONE S. MARIE.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Optulerunt pro eo domino par turturum aut duos pullos colum|barum. et cetera.</I> To dai man mai iheren he &thorn;e wile wich &thorn;eau wes on &thorn;e olde lage mid wimmen on &thorn;re &thorn;inges. &thorn;at on is childbed. and &thorn;at o&eth;er chirchgang. and &thorn;e &thorn;ridde &thorn;e offring. of childbed spec&eth; &thorn;e halie <MILESTONE N="34" UNIT="p">boc &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>MVlier que peperit masculum octaua die circumcidit eum. et in tricesima secunda die deferet eum ad templum.</I> &ETH;anne wimman hadde cnaue child. on &thorn;e ehte&eth;e dai efter his bur&thorn;e; dide &thorn;e lage &thorn;at wes of his hlichame. and after &thorn;an; on &thorn;e two and &thorn;rittu&eth;e dai; gede to chirche. &thorn;at was &thorn;e fowerti&eth;e dai; after &thorn;es childes burde. and<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.? <I>read</I> er.</NOTE> &thorn;at dai hie ne com nauwer ute. ne no&eth;ing ne han[d]lede bute &thorn;ane mete &thorn;at hie hire self et. for &thorn;at men telden it ful al &thorn;at hie handlede; forte &thorn;at hie gede to chirche. &thorn;anne hie to chirche gede to &thorn;e temple in ierusalem hire ferede was bifunden alse hie frend hedde and brohte &thorn;at child mid hire in to &thorn;e temple. and offredde loc for him; alse hie aisie wes. gif hie was riche wim|man; a lomb. gif hie was bitwene two; two turtle briddes. gif hie was poure two duue briddes. Swich &thorn;eu wes bi &thorn;an dagen. and &thorn;is &thorn;eu folgede &thorn;e heuenliche quen ure lafdi. Seinte Marie. on childbedde. and on offringe and on chirche gonge. and we ogen ec to folgen hire faire forbisne and alse hie bar hire holie cunebern on heorte gostliche and on honde lichamliche. alse we ogen to heren ure hlouerd ihesu crist on ure heorte. <I>fide et dilec|cione.</I> &ETH;urh rihte bileue and so&thorn;e luue to gode and to manne. and on ure honde beren candele berninde. taper o&eth;er candele. ei&eth;er bitocne&eth; &thorn;is &thorn;eau. <I>IN Christo enim corpus et anima et diuinitas. et in candela cera exterius. luminulum interius.</I> <MILESTONE N="35" UNIT="p">[<I>I</I>]<I>gnis in ambobus.</I> On ure helendes lichame wi&eth;uten sene. &thorn;e holie saule wi&eth;inne unsene. and te michele wisdom on ei&eth;er. Alse wex on &thorn;e candele sene. &thorn;e wueke wi&eth;innen unsene. and &thorn;e fur on bo&eth;e. and for&thorn;i ech cristene oh to habben on honden 
<PB REF="00000077.tif" N="49"> to-dai in chirche; lege bernende. alse ure lefdi Seinte Marie hadde; and hire holie fereden. &thorn;is was &thorn;e lage bi holde dagen. and &thorn;es loc offrede ure lafdi seinte marie and &thorn;re loc offrede weren ure drihten &thorn;at is to understonden to eureche manne wet ech bitocne&eth; &thorn;at on is lomb &thorn;at o&eth;er is turtle &thorn;at &thorn;ridde is duue Vte we ure ech fo[n]den himself to offren &thorn;at on; of &thorn;ese &thorn;re lokes. and wat it bitocne&eth;. <I>Agnus quod est animal mansuetum. et significat innocenciam. que nescit cordis. nec oris. nec operis maliciam.</I> lomb is drih &thorn;ing and milde. and bitocne&eth; lo&eth;les|nesse. lo&eth;les is &thorn;e man &thorn;e ne do&eth; ne ne qua&eth;. ne &thorn;enc&eth; no &thorn;ing &thorn;at he &thorn;urue ben &thorn;e lo&thorn;ere ne &thorn;e unwur&eth;ere ne gode ne manne. <I>et hec oblacio perfectorum est.</I> Ac &thorn;is loc ne haue&eth; non to offren. bute &thorn;ese lif holie men of religiun. and for &thorn;is loc is &thorn;us arue&eth; winne. nime we &thorn;e turtles bitocninge &thorn;at is e&eth;winne. <I>Tvrtur significat castitatem.</I> Turtle ne wile habbe no make bute on. and after &thorn;at non. and for&thorn;i it bitocne&eth; <MILESTONE N="36" UNIT="p">&thorn;e clenesse. &thorn;e is bideled of &thorn;e hore; &thorn;at is cleped hordom. &thorn;at is alre horene hore. and ech man &thorn;at is ful &thorn;eroffe wapman o&eth;er wimman is hore; forte hie it for-leten and beten <I>Castitas autem distinguitur in uirginalem. coniugalem. vidualem</I>. Alle &thorn;o mugen offre clen|nesse &thorn;e libbe&eth; clenliche on maiden-hode. o&eth;er on spus-hod. o&eth;er on widewe-hod. and non o&eth;er. and ech man &thorn;e ne haue&eth; noht redi. lombbes lo&eth;lesnesse. ne turtles clennesse. habbe we hurend hure mildshipe of duue. alse ure drihten bit on &thorn;e godspelle and sei&eth;. <I>Estote simplices sicut columbe</I>. bu&eth; admode alse duue Q <I>Ve</I> nullum <I>ore. uel ungue ledit</I>. duue ne harme&eth; none fugele ne mid bile ne mid fote. and fede&eth; briddes &thorn;eh hie ne ben noht hire. and &eth;us ki&eth; &thorn;at hie is admod and unbaleful. and gif we ne mugen for&eth;en non of &thorn;ese &thorn;re; bidde we &thorn;enne &thorn;e heuenliche quen &thorn;at hie us &thorn;inge to hire holie kinebern. &thorn;at he us giue &thorn;e bitocninge. &thorn;at is imene turtlen and duues. &thorn;at is bireusinge; of ure fule sinnes. Utraque enim <I>auis habet gemitum pro cantu. quo significatur meror compunctionis.</I> Ei&eth;er turtles and duues habbet sorinesse for song. vte we folgen &thorn;at here song bitocne&eth;. and habben on ure heorte <MILESTONE N="37" UNIT="p">sori|nesse. and reu&eth;e of ure synnes. and &thorn;er mide dihten ure loc 
<PB REF="00000079.tif" N="51"> &thorn;e we on honde bere&eth;. &thorn;at we mid ure loke ben gode to queme. <I>Quod ipse prestare dignetur qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="9" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>IX. [IN SEPTUAGESIMA.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Qvomodo cantabimus canticum domini in terra aliena?</I> &thorn;e holie prophete dauid spec&eth; on &thorn;e sealmboc. and on &aacute; stede &thorn;eron munege&eth; sume of &thorn;e wordes &thorn;e weren speken bitwine two folkes. &thorn;at on was of ierusalem. and &thorn;at o&eth;er of babilonie. and &thorn;o word munege&eth; us to rihtlechen ure liflode. and nime&eth; for|bisne efter &thorn;e olde men &thorn;e &thorn;o weren and lif holie. Ierusalem. and babilonie be&eth; two burges. and flite&eth; eure. and winne&eth; bi|twinen hem. &thorn;at israelisshe folc was walkende toward ierusalem on swinche. and on drede. and on wanrede and &thorn;o wile was hersum godes hese. Ac efter &thorn;an &thorn;e hie weren wuniende in ierusalem. and weren hole and sunde. and sikere of here giue. and hadden &thorn;e fulle of wurldes richeisse. &thorn;o hie forleten godes lore. and folgeden here lichames wille. nameliche on two &thorn;igges. &thorn;at was mu&eth;es me&eth;e &thorn;at o&eth;er hordom. and &thorn;ermide brohten godes wra&eth;e uppen hem. and he nam stronge wrache &thorn;er-of. here&eth; nu wich. he let hise wi&eth;erfulle hine &thorn;o ben deules on helle bringen on &thorn;e kinges heorte of babilonie. &thorn;at he sholde fare to &thorn;e burh of ierusalem. and strugen it. and he gederede michel ferde mid alle. and sende in<MILESTONE N="38" UNIT="p"> to ierusalem. and com him self &thorn;erwi&eth; and bilai &thorn;e burh forte &thorn;at hit<NOTE PLACE="marg">? = he it.</NOTE> wan and struide hem &thorn;o. and al &thorn;e lond &thorn;er abuten. and nam &thorn;at folc and dide into bendes. and sende hie in to babilonie to &thorn;ralshipe. and on &thorn;ralshipe hie wuneden two and sixti wintre. and sume hund seuenti wintre fulle. and &thorn;at lond folc hem ouer-sette mid felefelde pine and mid swinche and michele wowe. and to eken o&thorn;er &thorn;o gremeden hem sore &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Hymnum cantate nobis d. c. s.</I> Singe&eth; us of &thorn;e loft songes of syon. &thorn;us sede &thorn;at folc of babilonie 
<PB REF="00000081.tif" N="53"> to &thorn;e folke of ierusalem. &thorn;at israelisse folc andswerede &thorn;us and sede. <I>Qvomodo cantabimus canticum domini interra aliena?</I> hu muge we singen godes loft song in uncu&eth;e londe? &thorn;e wile &thorn;e we weren on ure herde sikere. and sunde. and on alle richeise we sungen ofte ure drihtenes loft songes. ac nu we bu&eth; on &thorn;ralshipe and &thorn;olie&eth; meseise. we mugen michel e&eth;ere for&eth;en wepinge &thorn;ene song. and &thorn;us leten bileuen &thorn;e blisfulle songes. alle &thorn;e wile &eth;e hie wuneden on &thorn;ralshipe. &thorn;at was two and sixti wintre. &thorn;o com a king &thorn;e was cleped chirus. and wan babilonie. and makede frie &thorn;at israelisse folk. and let hem sume faren hom in to ierusalem. Nu age we alle and al cristene folc nime for|bisne after &thorn;at israelisshe folc. and leten alse fele dages alse hie diden geres. &thorn;at be&eth; two and sixti. &thorn;at we ne singe&eth; &thorn;o blisfulle songes. <I>Alleluia</I> and <I>te deum laudamus.</I> and swo fele dages be&eth; unen <MILESTONE N="39" UNIT="p">to estrene dai. for &thorn;at we be&eth; ec on &thorn;ralshipe. gostliche for ure gultes. alse hie weren lichamliche for here gultes and &thorn;is mai ech man understonden. &thorn;e wot wat bitocne&eth; &thorn;ese two burges. ierusalem and babilonie. <I>IErusalem enim interpretatur uisio pacis. et significat moraliter animam iusticie.</I> ierusalem bitoc|ne&eth; so&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">? siht.</NOTE> of sehtnesse. <I>Quoniam oculis contemplacionis semper intuetur saluatorem nostrum. qui deo patri reconciliauit genus humanum.</I> for he do&eth; alse holie write sei&eth;. <I>Oculi mei semperad dominum.</I> vre egen ben eure opene to biholde ure helende &thorn;e &thorn;urh is agen de&eth; makede &thorn;en heuenliche fader sehte mid mankin; &eth;onked wur&eth;e him. <I>Qve n. dicitur ciuitas eo quod humilitatis et paciencie ceterarumque uirtutum habitacio est; ut ciuitas ciuium.</I> &thorn;e saule is cleped burh for &thorn;e admodnesse and &eth;oleburdnesse. and swiche o&eth;re holie mihtes. &thorn;e wunie&eth; on hire alse folc inne burh. <I>Et in anima regnat spiritualis apetitus ut dux in urbe.</I> and on hire rixle&eth; &thorn;e gostliche wil; alse king on is burh. <I>Babilonia interpretatur confusio.</I> babilonie bitocne&eth; shame. <I>Et significat corpus subditum peccato.</I> and bitocne&eth; &thorn;e synfulle lichame. <I>Quod est confusum quoniam dominus spernit illud.</I> &thorn;e is riht attenshame. for &thorn;at he erne&eth; here. &thorn;at ure louerd ihesu crist him she[n]de&eth;. and wile shufe fro him a domes dai. biforen alle heueneware and her&eth;e ware. and ec helleware; &thorn;us 
<PB REF="00000083.tif" N="55"> que&eth;ende. <I>Ite maledicti in ignem</I> <MILESTONE N="40" UNIT="p"><I>eternum. et cetera.</I> wite&eth; ge awerhgede gostes in to helle. <I>Qvod eciam dicitur ciuitas quod uicia habitant in eo; ut in urbe ciues.</I> &thorn;e lichame is cleped burh. for &thorn;at &thorn;e fele lehtres. and fule lastes wunen &thorn;eronne alse folc inne burh. <I>Et in eo regnat carnalis appetitus ut dux in urbe sua.</I> and on him rixle&eth; lichamliche wil; alse eldrene man on his burh. <I>Et fecit gulam milicie sue principem.</I> and sette mu&eth;es mesure on his ferde. &thorn;at he gaderede. <I>scilicet carnalia desideria. que militant aduersus animam.</I> &thorn;o ben &thorn;e fule tuder|ende of flesliche lustes and fule sinnes. &thorn;e flited eure toganes &thorn;e wreche saule. and of &thorn;is flite spec&eth; &thorn;e apostel and sei&eth;. <I>Caro concupiscit aduersus spiritum. spiritus aduersus carnem.</I> &THORN;e lichame flite&eth; and winne&eth; togenes &thorn;e gostes wille. and &thorn;e saule agenes &thorn;e lichames wille. we auen forgult ure saules wille si&eth;e mid winter com hiderwardes and ouercumen it. and don us in to helle wite; for ure mu&eth;es mete on &thorn;re wise. on etinge to michel. on estmetes &thorn;e brede&eth; sinnes. and on ouerete; &thorn;e hem fede&eth; and on untimliche ete; &thorn;e hem for&eth;e&eth;. and on two wise on drinke untimeliche; and on ouerdede. and on swiche drinkeres cume&eth; godes curs. alse &thorn;e prophete sei&eth;. <I>UE nobis qui potentes estis ad bibendum.</I> Wo &thorn;o ilche &thorn;at ben mihti to drinken. on two wise men drinke&eth; golnesse. on untime. and on unl[u]ued stede. and ne ben naht like &thorn;erto<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> &thorn;eh.</NOTE> bute hie ben togedere bispusede. <MILESTONE N="41" UNIT="p">and alle &thorn;e wile &thorn;e hersumie&eth; &thorn;ese two &thorn;ing &thorn;e ich nu nemde; mu&eth;es me&eth;e and golnesse. ne muge we noht singe &thorn;e blisfulle songes; <I>alleluia.</I> ne <I>te deum laudamus.</I> ne <I>Gloria in excelsis</I> gode to quemnesse. Vte we &thorn;enne &thorn;is hersumien. and bireusen &thorn;at we auen don. and gon to shrifte &thorn;erof. and beten ech bi his mihte mid gode bedes. mid almes dede. bi ure shriftes rede. and al &thorn;ese two and sixti dages; forleten blisfulle songes. and plege. and leden clenliche ure lif; alse &thorn;e holie boc us lere&eth;. and &thorn;ermide lesen us ut of helle pine. <I>Quod ipse nobis prestare dignetur qui viuit.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="10" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000085.tif" N="57">
<HEAD>X. [DE CONFESSIONE.<NOTE PLACE="foot">This Homily seems imperfect.</NOTE>]</HEAD>
<P>Vnderstonde&eth; get an &thorn;i[n]g &thorn;at ich giu wile warnie fore. gif man be&eth; forwunded. he wile anon sechen after leches. and shewen him his wunden. and bi his wissinge leden is lif. forte &thorn;at he bie hol. alse we ogen to don. Ure saule is sore forwunded. for ech synne is &thorn;e saule wunde. and prest is saulene leche. and for&thorn;i we agen to cumen to ure preste er &thorn;anne we biginnen to festen. and of him understonden shrift. &thorn;e we shulen leden al &thorn;is leinten. on festing on elmes dede on gode bedes. on wecche. on swinke. on unwasshen weden. on smerte swinginge and on o&eth;re swiche gode dedes; elch man alse him bu&eth; lief to beten his fule synnes. for no man<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> mam.</NOTE> ne mai synnes beten er &thorn;anne he hem forlete. and shewe em <MILESTONE N="42" UNIT="p">his prest. and nime shrifte &thorn;eroffe. <I>TRibus de causis ieiunant [ie]iunantes. alius quidem ad purgacionem culpe scilicet peccator. alius uero ad custodiam iusticie scilicet iustus. alius ad augmentum glorie scilicet sanctus.</I> On &thorn;re wise faste&eth; man. &thorn;e wel faste&eth; here leinten. &thorn;e synfulle for to clensen him. &thorn;e rihtwise for to witiende his rihtwisnesse. and nehlechen to holinesse. &thorn;e holie man faste&eth; forto hegen his sete on heuene. and to eken his holinesse. and to egen his blisse. <I>[Q]vod melius patefacit; exemplar lotricum.</I> and &thorn;is us do&eth; to understonden &thorn;e forbisne of &thorn;e wasshestren. Sume bere&eth; sole clo&eth; to &thorn;e watere forto wasshen it clene. Swo faste&eth; &thorn;e sinfulle man his festing to clensen him seluen of his fule sinnen. Sume bere&eth; clene clo&eth; to watere to blechen him &thorn;at hit beo wit. Swo do&eth; &thorn;e rihtwise man for to quemen ure louerd ihesu crist. and for to habben eche lif mid him. Sum o&eth;er bere&eth; clene clo&eth;. and faire wit. Swo faste&eth; &thorn;e holie man for ben hegh on heuene. and nehg ure drihten. and for to habben &thorn;e fulle blisse mid him. <I>Sanctus indiget confirmacione. Ivstus autem conuersacione. Peccator uero penitudine. Confessione. Sanctificacione.</I> &THORN;e holie man is ned &thorn;at he festned on his 
<PB REF="00000087.tif" N="59"> holinesse. &thorn;e rihtwise &thorn;at he bileue on his rihtwisnesse &thorn;e sinfulle man is ned. &thorn;at he synne forlete and swi&eth;e bimurne and shewe hem his preste at shrifte. and after his wissinge hem bete. and &thorn;erfore we agen alle to ben shrifene of ure synnes her we bigin|nen <MILESTONE N="43" UNIT="p">to fasten. for no man ne mai his sinnes bete; er he habbe nume shrift &thorn;erof. Ure louerd ihesu crist leue us swo ure synnen to beten. and swich elmesse to wurchen. &thorn;at we mo ben on his riht hond on domes dai. <I>Quod ipse prestare dignetur qui viuit.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="11" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XI. IN CAPITE IEIUNIJ.</HEAD>
<P><I>Conuertimini ad me in toto corde uestro et cetera.</I> Non eor&eth;|liche fader ne moder ne haue&eth; swa milde heorte to hire liefe child. swo ure heuenliche fader haue&eth; to us; &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. and &thorn;at he ci&eth; on alle wise. and nameliche on &thorn;at &thorn;e he hus mineget ofte on his holie write bi his erendrake &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Conuertimini ad me et cetera.</I> Turne&eth; giu to me. feren it is &thorn;at we and ure heldrene habb&aelig;&eth; ben turnd fro him; eure si&eth;&eth;en &thorn;e deuel com on neddre liche to adam. and mid his hinder worde bicherde him; &thorn;at he forlet &thorn;at god him het don. and dide &thorn;at god him forbet. and on &thorn;ese wise turnde fro him. noht him &oacute;ne ac al his ofspring. alse &thorn;e holie boc sei&eth;. <I>Recessit &aacute; deo salutari suo</I>. forlet god his helende. forlet god his louerd. <I>Et abiit in consilio ympiorum.</I> and turnde on &thorn;e hinderfulle rede. <I>Et stetit in uia peccatorum.</I> and stod on &thorn;e weie of synnes. <I>Et sedit in ca. pestilencie.</I> and set on &thorn;e setle of unhele. and &thorn;eh ure drihten be mild heorted. &thorn;o &thorn;e him bidde&eth; he is no&eth;eles rihtwis togenes &thorn;o; &thorn;e his milce biseche&eth;. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Misericors dominus et iustus.</I> vre louerd is mild <MILESTONE N="[44]" UNIT="p">heorted. and rihtwis. for &thorn;urh his mild hertnesse he hadde maked adam louerd ouer &thorn;is middel|herd. and ec ouer paradis &thorn;e wile &thorn;e he wolde heren him. and &thorn;urh his rihtwisnesse. drof him ut of paradis. &thorn;o &thorn;e was turnd 
<PB REF="00000089.tif" N="61"> fro him. and makede him fleme &thorn;ere he hadde er louerd iben. and erming &thorn;er he was er king. Swo do&eth; to dai ech bishup. &thorn;e in his minister be&eth;. driue&eth; ut &thorn;o forsinegede men. &thorn;e habbe&eth; &thorn;o sinnes don; &thorn;e biligge&eth; to here shrifte. and shulen don here penitence; forte &thorn;ene &thorn;uresdai biforen estrene dai. and &thorn;enne he wile hem fecchen in to chirche. Swo ure louerd ihesu crist fette adam ut of helle. &thorn;o &thorn;e hedde his penitence enden. and swo he wile us ec. &thorn;anne we hauen ure penitence fulended. Adam was in helle in pine fuwerti hundred wintre. for his sinne. and we shulen ben fulle .xl. dages in penitence. for to beten ure sinnen. and &thorn;er after ben alesd of pine &thorn;urh &thorn;at holie husel &thorn;e we shulen &thorn;anne understonden. and gif we clenliche it understonde&eth;; &thorn;anne bie we turnd to him; and he to us alse him self sei&eth;. <I>Conuertimini ad me; et ego conuertar ad uos</I>. Turne&eth; giu to me; and ich wile turne me to giu. We turnen ofte to him; and fro him. for we be&eth; unstedefaste. At ure fulcninge biforen &thorn;e uantstone. we turnden fro ure fo to him. and biheten him festliche &thorn;at we wolden eure to him holden. <MILESTONE N="45" UNIT="p">and habbe&eth; logen ure hese. and eft sone ech at shrifte &thorn;at ilke bihote&eth;. Ac liste&eth; nu wich &thorn;reat dauid sette&eth; uppen us bute lesten ure bihese. and turnen to him anradliche. <I>Nisi conuersi fueritis gladium et cetera.</I> bute [we] turnen to gode anradliche he wile his swerd dragen; &thorn;at is his wrake. <I>Et aut in latere quassabit. aut in aice</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> acie.</NOTE> <I>findet. aut in mucrone comburet.</I> and he wile smite mid bredlinge swuerde and brisen. o&eth;er mid egge. and cleuen. o&eth;er mid orde. and pilten. and bernen. Vuele he us brise&eth;. gif he binime&eth; us ure agte. o&eth;er &thorn;urh fur. o&eth;er &thorn;urh &thorn;iefes. o&eth;er &thorn;urh roberie. o&eth;er &thorn;urh unrihte dom. o&eth;er &thorn;urh gemeleste. o&eth;er &thorn;urh o&eth;er unlimp. o&eth;er &thorn;urh orf qualm. o&eth;er &thorn;urh smerte gier. and gif he binime&eth; us ure sihte. o&eth;er ure liste. o&eth;er us croke&eth; on fote o&eth;er on honde. o&eth;er on alle ure limes binime&eth; us ure hele. and reuliche he us cleue&eth; gif he &thorn;urh ferliche de&eth;; saule fro &thorn;e lichame dele&eth;. alse ich drede &thorn;at he wile bute we turne to him &thorn;e erur. Grisliche he us mid orde pilted. and berne&eth;. gif he us sende&eth;. into helle saule. and lichame to wuniende on eche fur. Min red is &thorn;at we bergen us wi&eth; ech of &thorn;ese &thorn;re duntes. and don alse &thorn;itege<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;e witege.</NOTE> dauid us 
<PB REF="00000091.tif" N="63"> minege&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Declina &aacute; malo et fac bonum.</I> forbue iuel and do god. <I>Et apostolus. EMendemus in melius que ignoranter peccauimus. et cetera.</I> <MILESTONE N="[46]" UNIT="p">and seinte poul sei&eth;. turne we to gode. and beten. for &thorn;at we hauen agilt her biforen. <I>Per ignoranciam. Per negligenciam. Per inpotenciam. Per mali|uolenciam</I>. o&eth;er &thorn;urh nuteluste. o&eth;er &thorn;urh uniweald &thorn;e bu&eth; e&eth;|bete gif hie us sore riewe&eth;. o&eth;er recheluste &eth;e is erue&eth;er to betende. o&eth;er to bi&thorn;ohte &thorn;inge &thorn;e is swi&eth;e erue&eth;er to betende. bute hie &thorn;e more hem bimurne. and &thorn;e gernere milce bidde; and &thorn;e more pine &thorn;olien. Nu ge hauen herd &thorn;at ure drihten bit turnen to him. here&eth; nu &oacute; hu uele wise. <I>scilicet In toto corde. IN ieiunio. IN fletu et planctu.</I> On fuwuer wise us bihoue&eth; turnen to him; on heorte. on festene. on wope. on meninge. &thorn;e man turne&eth; to gode on sumdel of his heorte; &thorn;e sume of his sinnes forlete&eth;. and sume et-hele&eth;. ac swo ne bihoue&eth; us noht to don. &thorn;e man turne&eth; on al his heorte &thorn;e alle his synnes forlete&eth;. and swo we ben beden turnen. &thorn;at we ne athelde none on ure heorte. and nameliche no wra&eth;&eth;e ne onde. ne hatiginge.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> hatingge.</NOTE> ne habbe non to o&eth;er &thorn;eh he haue to us. On festing he bit us us turnen. <I>IEiunium corporis est abstinencia cibi et potus. Ieiunium mentis est abstinencia uicii</I>. Two kinne festing be&eth;. &thorn;e lichames festing; is wi&eth;tiging of estmetes. and oueretes. and untimliche etes. and untimliche drinke. alse &thorn;e holie loftsong sei&eth;. <I>CArnis terat superbiam potus cibique parcitas.</I> Me&eth;eliche eting. and drink|ing agen to temien &thorn;e lichames orguil. &thorn;e man &thorn;e faste&eth; his &thorn;onkes festing is widtigig of flashes <MILESTONE N="47" UNIT="p">lustes. and of o&eth;re fule lastes alse seinte poul sei&eth;. <I>Abstinete uos &aacute; carnalibus desideriis que militant aduersus animam.</I> Wi&eth;tie&eth; giu fro flesliche lustes &thorn;e winnen togenes &thorn;e saule. and of &thorn;is festing spec&eth; ure drihten &thorn;urh &thorn;e holie prophetes mu&eth;; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Hoc est ieiunium quod magis elegi. scilicet dissoluere colligaciones impietatis et soluere fasciculos deprimentes.</I> ei&eth;er que&eth; he ich wile. ac &thorn;at me is quemere &thorn;at unbinde&eth; &thorn;e bendes; of wi&eth;erfulnesse. and &thorn;o ouersemde burden. gif we wi&eth;eri&eth; on dede. and on speche. to|genes ure chirche. o&eth;er togenes ure emcristen. and &thorn;erto wunie&eth; us. &thorn;enne bie we bunden of wi&eth;erfulnesse. and gif beden hem bote. 
<PB REF="00000093.tif" N="65"> o&eth;er forgiuenesse beden; &thorn;anne unbunde we &thorn;e bendes; &thorn;e we her uppen hem bunden. and &thorn;at bit ure drihten. and gif man haue&eth; wi&eth; us agilt. woerdes. o&eth;er wurkes. we &thorn;at him forgiue&eth;. &thorn;anne unbinde we &thorn;e burden &thorn;e he hadde us mide ouersemd. &thorn;at &thorn;ridde &thorn;ing hwanne ure drihten us bit turnen to him; is wop &thorn;e we for ure synnes wepe&eth;. alse &eth;e holie prophete sei&eth;. <I>Lacrimis meis stratum meum rigabo</I>. Swo ich wile biwepe mine synnes. &thorn;at mi bed bie iwasshen mid mine teares. and gif hit is swo. me &thorn;ing&eth; ne brin&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">bring&eth;.</NOTE> no synful man quemere loc; &thorn;ene teares sheding for his sinnen. and wiste se[i]nte peter. and Seinte Marie mag|daleine &thorn;e mid wope wessen hem seluen of heued synnes. On &thorn;e feor&eth;e &thorn;inge. &thorn;at is meninge. god bad us turnen to him. and &thorn;at us bihoue&eth; <MILESTONE N="48" UNIT="p">to don; on &thorn;refeld wise. <I>Vos ipsos de peccatis reprehendo. [S]Acerdoti ea confitendo. dei misericordiam pro eis supplicando.</I> and is &thorn;at we agen to gabben us seluen for&thorn;at we synegeden. alse &thorn;e holie man iob sei&eth;. <I>Reprehendo me et ago penitenciam. in fauillo et cinere.</I> Ich haue syneged and gabbe me suluen &thorn;eroffe and pine me seluen on asshen. and on iselen. and we agen to dai understonden &thorn;ese pine. o&eth;er is &thorn;at we agen ure synnes menende to shewen hem &thorn;e preste. and bi his wiss|ingge beten hem sy&eth;&eth;en alse seint iacob sei&eth;. <I>Confitemini alter|utrum peccata uestra et cetera.</I> shewe&eth; giwer synnes &thorn;e preste. for al &thorn;at prest binde&eth; so&eth;liche bu&eth; ibunden and al &thorn;at he unbinde&eth; be&eth; unbunden. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is menende his synnes bifore gode. and milce &thorn;er of bidden. &thorn;is us bihoue&eth; &thorn;at we eche dai don. and mid alle ure limes ure synnes beten. alse seinte poul sei&eth;. <I>Sicut exibuistis membra uestra seruire inmu[n]dicie et iniquitati ad iniquitatem ita nunc exibete membra uestra seruire iusticie in sanctificacionem</I>. Alse ge hauen giwer lichame don to her|sumiende fule lustes; and unriht. alse do&eth; giwer lichame he&eth;en|for&eth; to hersumiende clennesse. and rihtwisnesse. and holinesse. &thorn;at ech lime synderlepes turne to gode and bete his gilt. <I>Oculus uidit uanitatem fleat nunc.</I> wepe &thorn;at ege for&thorn;at hit idel bihield. <I>Avris audiuit ociosa. conuersa audiat utilia</I>. eare luste unnitte speche. turne &thorn;erfro. and here godes word on holie lor|spelle. <I>PEs cucurrit ad malum.</I> fot gide to uni&eth;or; swike nu. 
<PB REF="00000095.tif" N="67"> <MILESTONE N="49" UNIT="p">and gon ofte to chirche. <I>Circa membra se tetigere illicite absti|neant.</I> &thorn;i shape dide. &thorn;at hit ne sholde. and &thorn;er hit ne sholde and &thorn;enne hit ne sholde. wi&eth;teo it nu. bi here mihte &thorn;eh hie bien to|gedere bispused. and gif hie ne be&eth; noht togedere bispused. forleten hit mid alle. <I>Manus effudit sanguinem. desinat et faciat elemo|sinam.</I> hand dide ofte harmes. swike nu. and do almesse. <I>Cor inuidit &amp; odiuit habeat pacem et dileccionem.</I> heorte hadde onde and hatiunge habbe nu sehtnesse. and luue to ech liues man. <I>Os peccauit manducando bibendo male loquendo.</I> Mu&eth; synegede on eting. on drinking. and on uuele speche. ete nu leinte mete. and enes o dai and euene fille. and drinke o tige atte mete. and noht &thorn;er after bute hit for unhele be. o&eth;er swinke. speke so&eth; and riht. and bidde gerne<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>In MS. a part of the last</I> e <I>has been cut off</I>.</NOTE> milce. &thorn;us bit ure drihten. &thorn;at we shulen to him turnen. and sei&eth; &thorn;at he wile to us. and mid us bileue. <I>Qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="12" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XII. [DOMINICA I] IN XLA.</HEAD>
<P><I>PReocupemus faciem domini. et in psalmis iubilemus ei</I>. &thorn;e holie prophete dauid minege&eth; us on &thorn;e sealmboc to beregen us &thorn;e wile &thorn;e we mugen. wi&eth; &thorn;e eiseliche shame. and mid te bitere grame &thorn;at alle synfulle men shule &thorn;olen on domes dai. &thorn;at ne haue noht here sinnes forleten. and bet; er &thorn;an al mankin. &thorn;e was. and wurh. and nu is; cumen to one mote. and ure louerd ihesu crist <MILESTONE N="50" UNIT="p">cume&eth; of heuene to hem. and shode&eth; &thorn;e gode fro &thorn;e iuele. <I>Et statuet oues a dextris; hedos autem a sinistris.</I> and shode&eth; &thorn;e rihtwise an his rihthalue and wur&eth;e&eth; hem. and here&eth;. for hie hauen him er wel quemed. and giue&eth; hem to medes eche lif. and blisse. and heuene mid him seluen; and sei&eth;. <I>Uenite benedicti patris et cetera.</I> cume&eth; ge blescede. and underfo&eth; &thorn;at riche &thorn;at giu is igarked fro &thorn;e biginnigge of &thorn;e worlde. Si&eth;en he sette&eth; &thorn;e synfulle on his lifthalf. and wite&eth; 
<PB REF="00000097.tif" N="69"> hem &thorn;at hie bi here lif dages ne wolden him quemen. and here agene synnes. on dede. and on speche. unhile&eth; hem seluen. and shameliche hem bigrede&eth;. and fule shende&eth;. biforen al heuene|ware. and eor&eth;eware. and helle ware. and &thorn;enne sende&eth; ure louerd ihesu crist hem mid saule. and mid lichame into helle. to wuniende on eche wowe. &eth;e &eth;e&eth;en for&eth; shal wexen alse he seide. Ite <I>maledicti</I>. et cetera. wite&eth; ge aweregede gostes in &thorn;at eche fur &thorn;at is garked to deuules and here fereden to wuniende eure. and &oacute; abuten ende. &thorn;us here agene sinnes hem shende&eth;. and hie ben of-gramede wi&eth; hem selfen. for &thorn;at hie nedden here synnes er bet. and wi&eth; &thorn;is michele shame boregen &thorn;e wile here bot dai laste. Ure bot dai is nu. and laste&eth; &thorn;e wile &thorn;e god wile. bete we gerne. and ben afterward &thorn;e edinesse &thorn;e &thorn;e salm boc of spec&eth; <MILESTONE N="51" UNIT="p">&thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Beati quorum remisse. et cetera.</I> Edie ben alle &thorn;o; &thorn;e here giltes ben atleten. and helid here sinnes. &thorn;at ben &thorn;o &thorn;e hem rihtleche&eth;. alse &thorn;e prophete dauid hem lerde. <I>Preocupemus f. d. in. con.</I> &thorn;enche we ure giltes er &thorn;e dom cume. and forleten ure synnes. and bimurnen hem sore. and shewen hem at shrifte. and beten hem swo &thorn;e prest us wisse&eth;. and beten swo mid bote al &thorn;at we er breken. &thorn;at god ne finde &thorn;anne on us no gilt unpined. &thorn;anne ne &thorn;arf us no&eth;er gramien. ne shamien. To forleten ure sinne us minege&eth; &thorn;e holie prophete ieremie. &eth;us que&eth;inde. <I>Derelinquat impius uiam suam et cetera.</I> Forlete &thorn;e iuele man his wei. and &thorn;e un|rihtwise his fele unnette speche. and turne to gode. Iuel is &thorn;at ne wile his agene saule helpen. and we ben mest alle. and ure wei &thorn;e we shule leten. is ure liflode &thorn;e we shule rihtleche. Unrihtwise we ben &thorn;anne we ne don ure helendes wille. &thorn;e lesde us of dea&eth;e. and gif&eth; us al &thorn;at we bi ben.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? habben.</NOTE> and eche lif bihote&eth;. and wile lesten alle &thorn;o &thorn;e him heren. and gif we don ure wille &thorn;e us teo&eth; eure to herme. and here iuel don and werse &thorn;enchen to don; &thorn;at is unriht. &thorn;e holie man iob &thorn;e non ne was his efning on eor&eth;e. he us giue&eth; fair forbisne to bireusen ure saule sor. &thorn;at is ure sinnes. &thorn;er he sei&eth;. <I>Dimitte me domine u. p. p. d. m. a</I>. &thorn;ole me louerd alitelwan &thorn;at ich bimurne mi sor; er ich wite to &thorn;e &thorn;estere wunienge. and &thorn;e holie boc sei&eth; on o&eth;er 
<PB REF="00000099.tif" N="71"> stede. <I>Qvacunque</I> <MILESTONE N="52" UNIT="p"><I>hora homo ingemiscit peccata sua remittun|tur ei.</I> alse wat swo &thorn;e man his sinne sore bimurne&eth; ure drihten le&eth;e&eth; &thorn;e sinne bendes. and blisse&eth; swo &thorn;e soule alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Secundum multitudinem dolorum m. in. c. m. et cetera.</I> alse fele sorinesses swo ich haue on min herte; for mine sinnes; mid alse fele frefringe &thorn;u hauest blissed min soule. and &thorn;anne we hauen ure sinnes forleten. and &thorn;us bimurnen us bihoue&eth; &thorn;at we don; alse &thorn;e holie prophete us minege&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Confite|mini domino quoniam bonus;</I> kneowe&eth; ure louerd for &thorn;at he is wel god. and swo mild heorted. and sein iacob sei&eth; on his pistle. <I>Confitemini alterutrum peccata uestra et cetera.</I> shewe&eth; giwer sinnes on o&eth;er stede. and awich o&eth;er stede age we hem to shewen. vre drihten us sei&eth; on &thorn;e godspelle. &thorn;e sein lucas makede. &thorn;er &thorn;e .x. li&eth;&eth;roweres clepeden biforen ure drihten. and seiden. <I>Iesu preceptor miserere nostri.</I> &thorn;u helend &thorn;e mid &thorn;ine wordes helest. alle &thorn;o &thorn;e wilt. haue milce of us. <I>Et dixit eis. Ite et ostendite uos sacerdotibus</I> and he andswerede hem alse he do&eth; us nu. go&eth; and shewe&eth; giu giuwer prest. prestes we shewed us &thorn;anne seien hem ure ateliche sinnes &thorn;e we hauen don. and que&eth;en. and &thorn;oht mid lestinde fule &thorn;onke and &thorn;anne we bien toward him. gif we hauen on ure &thorn;oht to shewen him ure sinnes. and forleten. and beten. we ben clensed of ure sinnes. gif we <MILESTONE N="53" UNIT="p">riht lesten &thorn;at we &thorn;ere bihoten &thorn;ere we shule tellen. alle ure gultes &thorn;at we ne hauen noht bct. and noht mid faire worde hihten. &thorn;o ateliche sinnes. and no &thorn;ing seien &thorn;ere &thorn;at les beo. and no &thorn;ing of &thorn;e so&eth;e forlete. ac shewen &thorn;ere openliche wich<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> &thorn;ich.</NOTE> he is. and gif hit was don on untime. o&eth;er on unluuede stede. o&eth;er mid unluued lete. o&eth;er on unluued wise. o&eth;er gif it was erfe&eth; to for&eth;en. and smeihliche bicharede. and gif we shewe&eth; &thorn;us ure sinnes. &thorn;enne muge we fulliche ben shrifene. ac fewe ben &thorn;at &thorn;us shewen heore sinnes. and &thorn;at is long on felefelde iuele lastes. and iuele &thorn;eawes. <I>Decem sunt que impediunt confessionem. scilicet hec. Obliuio. Ignorancia. Neggligencia. Verecundia. Timor. Diffidencia. Delicacia. Fiducia. Pertinacia. Desperacio.</I> Ten &thorn;ing ben &thorn;e letten men of here scrifte. Noht alle on. ac sum on. and sum o&eth;er. &thorn;at ben &thorn;ese and haten &thorn;us. forgetelnesse. nutelnesse. recheles. shamfestnesse. drede. 
<PB REF="00000101.tif" N="73"> Ortrowe. Trew&eth;eleas. [Softgerne] Trust. wilfulnesse. Misleue. &thorn;e man &thorn;e naue&eth;. luue ne eie to gode. he &thorn;enche&eth; selde o&eth;er naure of heuene wele; &thorn;e forgult mid his sunnes. and helle wowe. &thorn;e he erne&eth; mid his sunnes. and for &thorn;at gult he solde his sunnes at srifte sheawen. and for &thorn;i cume&eth; uppen him &thorn;at unlimp &thorn;e &thorn;e prophete wisste on se salmboke &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Adhereat lingua mea faucibus meis. et cetera.</I> Cleued be mi tunge to mine <MILESTONE N="54" UNIT="p">cheken gif ich forgete &thorn;e ierusalem. &thorn;anne man forgiet &thorn;at he seien sholde. &thorn;anne be&eth; his tunge alse hit cl[e]ued were. [Nutel|nesse] lete&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte &thorn;e ne wot neure hwanne he sinege&eth;. and swiche ben alle &thorn;o &thorn;e ne wilen listen lorspel. and &thorn;eron lernen wiche ben sinnen. and beregen hem. and &thorn;at bilimpe&eth; to god|cunnesse. and folegen &thorn;at. and &thorn;eroffe sei&eth; &thorn;e boc. <I>Nvllus uitare laborat quod ignorat.</I> no man ne fle&eth; &thorn;ing bute he wite. o&eth;er wene &thorn;at it him deren wille. Recheleste lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e &thorn;urh his misleue herberge&eth; &thorn;e fule gost on his heorte. &thorn;e him teche&eth; to folgen his fule lustes. and no wuerse of scrifte. and of hem &thorn;e holie boc spec&eth; and sei&eth;. <I>Peccator cum uenerit in profundum contempnit.</I> &thorn;anne &thorn;e sinfulle man beo&eth; bifallen on depe sinne. ne reche&eth; no &thorn;ing of scrifte. Shamfestnesse lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e ne wile his sinne seien &thorn;e preste. &thorn;e he ofte sinege&eth;. for him sholde shamen of him. and ne understant noht &thorn;at &thorn;e shame &thorn;e &thorn;e man haue&eth; of his sinne. &thorn;anne he hem prest shewe&eth;; hit is &thorn;e biginnigge of fremfulle sinbote. and &thorn;at wiste wel &thorn;e prophete &thorn;e &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Tota die uerecundia mea contra me est; et cetera</I> min shamfestnesse is to-genes me. and ouer|hele&eth; min bend ofte. Drede lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e ne dar his sinnes <MILESTONE N="55" UNIT="p">seien &thorn;e prest. leste hit uttere cume &thorn;at hie tweien witen. and swiche men blame&eth; &thorn;e prophete on &thorn;e sealm boc &thorn;er he sei&eth;. <I>[I]llic trepidauerunt timore u. n. e. t.</I> &thorn;er hem stod eie; &thorn;er hem ne sholde. &thorn;at is of idele &thorn;ing. and &thorn;er non; &thorn;er hem sholde michel eie stonde. &thorn;at is of gode. Ortrowe of agene mihte lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e &thorn;inche&eth; &thorn;at he ne mihte his sinne forlete. &thorn;eh he hem seide at shrifte. and forhete hem. <I>Sed hii sunt filii diffidencie de quibus dicit scriptura. Venit ira dei in filios diffidencie.</I> and swiche ben &thorn;e deules bernes &thorn;e aren 
<PB REF="00000103.tif" N="75"> cleped ortrowe for &thorn;at hie sinege swo michel. &thorn;at hie wenden to hauen forloren milce. and godes wra&eth;&eth;e cume&eth; ofte uppe &thorn;o; &thorn;e &thorn;at wenen. softgerne and ednesse lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e &thorn;in|che&eth; &thorn;at he ne mai &thorn;olen hunger. ne &thorn;irst ne o&eth;er pine to betende his sinnes. <I>vnde scriptura dicit. Delicati se nutriunt ad incendia gehenne.</I> &thorn;e softgerne fede&eth; hem seluen helle fur to honde. and to fote<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Originally</I> fode <I>but altered to</I> fote.</NOTE>. Trist to longe lif. lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrifte. &thorn;e sei&eth; to him seluen on his heorte. Ich nam noht giet sad of mine sinnes. and for&thorn;i; ne mai ich hie noht forlete. ac o&eth;er ich mai ben sed &thorn;eroff and &thorn;anne ich wille hem forleten. and nime shrift. and beten hem. <MILESTONE N="56" UNIT="p">ac &thorn;e holie boc blame&eth; &thorn;ese men &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>[D]eus promittit ueniam penitenti sed non crastinum diem peni|tencie differenti</I>. god bihet milce &thorn;o &thorn;e here sinnes forleten and beten. ac he ne bihet noht &thorn;e lif til &aacute;moregen; &thorn;o &thorn;e li&eth; on sinne ac sei&eth;. <I>Qva hora non putatis mors ueniet</I>; &THORN;anne &thorn;u lest wenst dea&eth; cume&eth; to fecchende &thorn;e. Willfulnesse lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrift. &thorn;at &thorn;inche&eth; uuel &thorn;at man him wile neden his sinnes to forleten. and fro &thorn;e deuel to gode turnen. and of hem sei&eth; &thorn;e holie boc. <I>Pertinaces in malo eliminat ecclesia.</I> holie chirche dele&eth; fro cristendom. &thorn;o &thorn;e wilfulle ben here sinnes to luuen. and lo&eth;e to forleten. Ortrowe of godes milce. lette&eth; &thorn;e mannes shrift. &thorn;e haue&eth; michel sineged. and nele lete<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>MS</I>. bete.</NOTE>. ne bete. ne milce bidde. for &thorn;at he wene&eth; &thorn;at god ne wile swo michel sinne forgiue; for none bote &thorn;at he for&eth;e muge. and of &thorn;is sei&eth; &thorn;e holie boc. <I>Qvi desperat iam iudicatus est.</I> &thorn;e man &thorn;e ortrowe&eth; godes mildhertnesse. he is idemd to eche wowe on helle. &thorn;erwi&eth; us wite ure louerd ihesu crist gif his wille beo. and berege us wi&eth; alle iuele customes. and giue us mihte ure sinnes to forleten. and prest shewen. and wise us. and filste hem to beten. swo &thorn;at us beo biheue; and him to queme. <I>Qui viuit et Regnat deus per omnia . . . . .</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="13" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000105.tif" N="77">
<HEAD>XIII. [DOMINICA II] <MILESTONE N="57" UNIT="p">IN QUADRAGESIMA.</HEAD>
<P><I>Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile. ecce nunc dies salutis. In his ergo diebus exibeamus nosmet ipsos sicut dei ministros. In multa paciencia. In ieiuniis. In uigiliis. In caritate non ficta. et cetera. Celestis medicus ut cognouit quod ope sua prius creati postmodo uariis languoribus peccatorum uexarentur. Scripto uisitans eos. hortatur eos ad medicinam confessionis. quia ut ait scriptura. Omnia in confessione creantur et ne pretenderent ad excusacionem temporis dicit. Ecce nunc tempus acceptabile ecce nunc dies salutis. Uidelicet aptum creacioni .i. satisfactioni .i. remissioni. et dietam</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> dictam.</NOTE> <I>proponit dicens. Viuite sicut dei ministri. et quia que parat medicamenta asperant. scilicet ferrum pacieris et ignem. Monet eos ad pacienciam dicens. In multa paciencia. Ferro quidem secatur superfluum ignis urendo curat in quo notantur. scilicet calor compunctionis. et feruor gemine dilectionis que curant et sanant omnem languorem peccati. et [de] compunc|tione quidem dicitur. quacunque hora ingemit homo peccatum; remittuntur ei. De dileccione dominus dicit. Ego diligentes me diligo. Sic ortatur nos</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. uos.</NOTE> <I>apostolus ut emendemus i[n] melius; que huc usque peccauimus. Ne diuina ulcio spacium penitencie preripiat nobis.</I> &THORN;e heuenliche leche seinte poul nime&eth; geme of ure saule sicnesse. &thorn;at ben ure sinnes &thorn;onged <MILESTONE N="58" UNIT="p">wur&eth;e him. and minege&eth; us bi his holie write. &thorn;e we reden to dai inne chirche. &thorn;at we shewen ure agene michele nede. and &thorn;e wile &thorn;e we mugen &thorn;enchen. and cumen festliche to ure saule leche and unhelen him ure saule wundes. &thorn;o ben ure fule synnes. and bidden &thorn;at he wisse us hu we mugen ure saule of hem clensen. and ure sor helien. and weche us of ure heuie slape. and rere us of ure fule lust bedde. &thorn;at we don alse &thorn;ing do&eth;. &thorn;e haue&eth; lein on swete. for|quichie&eth; &thorn;an here time cume&eth;. and &thorn;at is nu&eth;e for &thorn;is time is licwur&eth;e &thorn;arto; alse &thorn;e apostle sei&eth;. Eecce nunc tempus. Nu hit is god time to beloken &thorn;e sicnesse of &thorn;e sowle. <I>Ecce nunc</I> 
<PB REF="00000107.tif" N="79"> <I>dies salutis</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> falutis.</NOTE>. And &thorn;os fuerti dages ben bicumeliche to helen &thorn;e sowle. biseche we &thorn;anne &thorn;e sowle leche &thorn;at is &thorn;e prest. <I>Vt ferro prohibitacionis recindat &aacute; nobis exterius carnis et mentis uicia.</I> &thorn;at he us wissie to wi&eth;-tien of alle flesliche lustes &thorn;e derie&eth; ure sowle. and don uppen us swilch manifeald pine. &thorn;at mid here biter|nesse. driuen ut of ure &thorn;oght; &thorn;e fule lu[s]tes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Looks at first sight like</I> littes.</NOTE> &thorn;e heuien &thorn;e sowle. <I>In multa patientia. et cetera.</I> and ben swo &thorn;oleburde to-genes his wissinge to forleten &thorn;at he forbet. and don &thorn;at he bit. &thorn;at &thorn;e selue &thorn;oleburdnesse be ure swole<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>read</I> sowle.</NOTE> hele. alse ure drihten sei&eth;. <I>In patientia uestra possidebitis animas ues|tras.</I> <MILESTONE N="59" UNIT="p">On giwer &thorn;oleburdnesse; ge shulen wealden giwer saule. <I>Tanta est uirtus paciencie. quod quis eam exibendo animam suam s. ostendendo ita</I>. swo holie mihte is &thorn;oleburd|nesse. &thorn;at he &thorn;e hit ki&eth;; &thorn;er &thorn;urh haue&eth; his soule weald. ac swo ne haue&eth; he &thorn;e shewe&eth; &thorn;oleburdnesse. &thorn;e ne &thorn;ole&eth;. and forbere&eth; noht &aacute; misbode. and wolde him seluen wreke gif he mihte. and &thorn;erto ettle&eth; and abit his time. and ne&eth;eles ne mai him non harm don. he make&eth; lete of &thorn;oleburdnesse and ne&eth;eles ne haue&eth; non. and &thorn;er for ne haue&eth; his soule weald. for &thorn;at he lichamliche lustes and &eth;e fule lehtres him holden bunden on here &thorn;ralshipe. swo &thorn;at he ne mai his soule no &thorn;ing wealde. &THORN;e man haue&eth; and ki&eth; &thorn;oleburdnesse &thorn;e &thorn;ole&eth; and forbere&eth; and ne wile seche after wreche. and na&eth;emore haten him. &thorn;e him agilte&eth;. ne him iuel unnen. gif hit is man &thorn;at haue&eth; &thorn;is. and he halt uppen him. on speche and on dede. o&eth;er on ei&eth;er he be&eth; &thorn;oleburde and do&eth; alse he hit noht ne wite. and &thorn;eremide ouercume&eth; him. and his soule loke&eth; and eft hire swo walt. gif &thorn;e unfele man his wille folge&eth;. and mid felefolde wigeles<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> wigeses.</NOTE> te&eth; him to unwrenches. to stele. o&eth;er refloc. o&eth;er swikedom. o&eth;er drunkenesse. o&eth;er hordom. o&eth;er swiche. o&eth;re un&thorn;eawes. and lef mede bihote&eth; gif he wile his lore liste. and he nele. ac &eth;ole&eth; <MILESTONE N="60" UNIT="p">and forbere&eth;. and &thorn;ermide ouer|cume&eth; &thorn;e unfele. and his soule loke&eth;. and haue&eth; swo wald. gif lichames lust o&eth;er &thorn;ankes lust. te&eth; him to ani un&thorn;eau. and he nele ac &thorn;ole&eth; and forbere&eth;. &thorn;eh hit bie his lichame queme. ac flite&eth; to-genes his agen wille. alse &thorn;e wise bit &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Sperne uoluptates nocet empta dolore uoluptas</I>. Shune lustliche 
<PB REF="00000109.tif" N="81"> wil. for &thorn;at it dere&eth; swi&eth;e and be&eth; afterboht mid bitere sor. and &thorn;us ouercume&eth; alle hise fon; and &thorn;erfore haue&eth; his soule weald. for &thorn;enne be&eth; on him sene &thorn;at &thorn;e wise seide. <I>Qvem superare nequis pacienter uince ferendo</I>. &THORN;at &thorn;u mid strenc&eth;e ne miht ouercume. ouercum mid &thorn;oleburdnesse. and on ech swich flite; is man of &thorn;oleburdnesse abuuen at ende. Swo mote we flite to|genes ure fule lustes. al &thorn;e fuwerti dages. and ouercumen at ende hem. and alle &thorn;e &thorn;ing &thorn;at us to sunne te&eth;. <I>Quod ipse pre|stare dignetur qui uiuit et regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="14" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XIV. IN MEDIA XLA.</HEAD>
<P><I>Cvm inmundus spiritus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> spirituc.</NOTE> <I>exierit ab homine ambulat</I> (<I>uadit</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">uadit <I>is written over</I> ambulat <I>in MS.</I></NOTE>) <I>per loca arida querens requiem et non inueniens dicit. Reuer|tar in domum meam unde exiui. et ueniens; inuenit eam scopis mundatam et ornatam. Tunc uadit per loca arida querens requiem et non inueniens dicit. Reuertar in domum meam unde exiui et ueniens inuenit eam scopis mundatam et ornatam. Tunc uadit et sumit vii</I><SUP>tem</SUP> <I>alios</I> <MILESTONE N="61" UNIT="p"><I>spiritus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">MS. spirituc.</NOTE> <I>secum nequiores se; et in|gressi habitant ibi. et fiunt nouissima hominis illius peiora pri|oribus</I> &thorn;e louerd seint matheu spec&eth; on his holi godspel of &thorn;e grimliche wordes &thorn;e ure helende at sume time gaf to andswere &thorn;e unbilefde iudeuisshe men. &thorn;e ger[n]den of him fortocne<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> fortacne.</NOTE> and seiden. <I>Magister uolumus a te signum uidere</I>. Meister we wolden sen sum fortocne of &thorn;e. Warbi we mihten cnowen gif it so&eth; were &thorn;at &thorn;u seist; and leuen. and he hem gaf to andswere eifulle word. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Generacio mala et adultera signum querit. et non dabitur signum nisi signum ione prophete.</I> Iuelmennish and forhored mannish acse&eth; after fortocne of heuene. and hie ne shulen hauen bute eor&eth;liche. and he hem shewede fortocne bi ionan &thorn;e prophete. of his holie &thorn;rowegunge &thorn;e he wolde &thorn;olien to lesen al mankin of eche wowe. &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. and of his riseng. and of de&eth;e al mankin bringe to blisse. and si&eth;en blamede here un-bileue. and here unwreste liflode. and seide. 
<PB REF="00000111.tif" N="83"> <I>Viri niniuite surgent in iudicio cum generacione ista. et con|dempnabunt eam. quia penitenciam egerunt in predicatione ione.</I> On domes dai shal &thorn;at folc arisen on &thorn;e michele dome; and fordemen &thorn;is mannish. <I>Non equidem sentencie lacione. sed meri|torum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt.xii.41.]</NOTE> <I>comparacione.</I> Noht mid domkete<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> wordes. ac mid wured|luker wordes. for &thorn;at &thorn;e hie undernomen &thorn;e wise lore of ionan <MILESTONE N="62" UNIT="p">&thorn;e prophete. and lete here sinnes. and bi wissinge betten and milce beden. <I>Et ita facta est niniue speciosa que prius turpis existebat</I>. And swo war&eth; iturnd &thorn;at folc of ateliche to wen|liche. and was here ende betere &thorn;ene here biginninge. ac &thorn;is wi&eth;erfulle mannisshe &thorn;e fonde&eth; me hinderfulliche. and here&eth; mine wise word. and se&eth; mine wunderliche deden. and na&eth;emo me ne leue&eth;. ne here sinnes ne forlete&eth;. ne beten. ne to me abugen. ne milce bidden. and &thorn;erfore wur&eth; here ende werse &thorn;ene here biginninge. &thorn;us seide ure drihte. and we mugen seien to so&eth;e &thorn;at al to fele swiche men bien get. &thorn;e ne wilen noht here sinnes forleten ac &thorn;inche&eth; hem swete. ne ne wilen don none sin|bote. and his<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> here lichame unnit swo. hie gon to chirche noht for godes luue. ac for to biregen nehebores speche. hie giuen here tige&eth;e noht for to hauen heuene blisse. ac for to hauen h&eacute;re. &thorn;e hereword of eor&eth;liche richeise. hie giuen here elmesse noht for godes luue ac for neheboreden. o&eth;er for kinraden. o&eth;er for onur to hauen. o&eth;er ne mai elles for shame. o&eth;er for &thorn;onc to hauen. o&eth;er for hereword to hauen. Gif he cneule&eth; in chirche. and buge&eth; alle hise limes; &thorn;at is idel. &thorn;eh he him bidde mid <MILESTONE N="63" UNIT="p">his mu&eth;. he ne feche&eth; noht &thorn;e sore siches. onne&eth;erward his heorte. ne for reu&eth;e ne wepe&eth; none hote teres. of his egen. and &thorn;ese ben false cristene. and ben forcu&eth;ere &thorn;ene he&eth;ene men. and be&eth; here ende forcu&eth;ere &thorn;ene here biginnenge Sone &thorn;erafter seide ure drihten. <I>Regina austri surget in iudicio cum generacione ista. et condempnabit eam. quia uenit a finibus terre audire sapienciam salomonis. et ecce plus quam salomon hic.</I> &THORN;e so&eth;e quen shal a domes [dai]<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Matt.xii.42.]</NOTE> arisen; on &thorn;e michele mote. and fordemen &thorn;is frakede folc. For &thorn;at hie com fro &thorn;e wereldes Ende to heren salomones wisdom. and &thorn;is wi&eth;erfulle folc ne wile liste &eth;e lor&eth;ewes wisdom. &thorn;e tehte salemon. and alle wise witege here wisdom. and &thorn;erfore wur&eth; 
<PB REF="00000113.tif" N="85"> [h]ere ende werse &thorn;ene here biginninge. <I>Quatuor sunt genera hominum in seculo iuuencium. Alii enim habent bonum prin|cipium et finem. Alii autem malum principium et finem. Alii quidam malum principium et bonum finem. Alii prin|cipium et malum finem.</I> Fuwerkinne mannisshe liuen on &thorn;is woreld. Sume biginne&eth; on here guwu&eth;e clene lif leden. and helde&eth; for&eth; &thorn;erone; and feire enden. alse sein[t] iohan baptist. &thorn;e on his childhode bicom eremite and hield for&eth; &thorn;erone; and faire endede. and sein[t] martin &thorn;e bigan on his guwu&eth;e &thorn;e clene lif leden. and to bien almesful; and hield for&eth; &thorn;erone. <MILESTONE N="64" UNIT="p">and faire it endede. and sein[t] nicholas. &thorn;e on his chilhode wunede him to fasten. and &thorn;at wune heold to his liues ende. and o&eth;re manie &thorn;e swo ledden here lif. &thorn;at te biginninge was fair. and te middel fairere. and te ende alre fairest. Swo &thorn;at bi hem was so&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e wise seide <I>[P]rimo ne medium. medio ne discrepet primum</I> here lifes ende was bicumeliche. &thorn;e middel and &thorn;e biginnenge. Sume men biginnen erest to leden clene lif. and eft hit forleten. alse dide iudas scariot. and o&eth;re inoge. alse &thorn;e holie godspel sei&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ex hoc multi abierunt retro. et iam cum illo non ambulant.</I> Fele folgeden erest ure drihten. and eft him forleten. and bi hem was so&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e prophete seide. <I>Cepisti melius quam desinis</I>. &ETH;u bigunne betere &thorn;ene &thorn;u ende. <I>Item dissimilis que fuit. huic similis ille uiro</I>. Here ende was un|liche here biginnenge. Sume men leden erest iuel liflode. and turnen eft to god. and &thorn;eron sewe&eth; alse seinte poul. and Seinte Marie magdaleine. &thorn;e dide alse wise hire lerden. &thorn;anne hie wi&eth; hire speken &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Hinc te melioribus offer</I>. wi&eth;-te &thorn;e wi&eth; iuel wune. and wune &thorn;e he&eth;enfor&eth; to betere. Sume men leden unfele liflode. &thorn;at te biginninge be&eth; iuel; and swo leng &thorn;e werse. and te ende alre werest. alse &thorn;e iudeuisshe folc. &thorn;e ure helende wi&eth; spec; and seide. <I>Cum immundus spiritus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> spirituc.</NOTE> <I>exierit ab [homine] uadit et cetera.</I> &ETH;enne &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="65" UNIT="p">iuele gost fared<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ut of &thorn;e manne and weue&eth; wide. and wandre&eth; ouer al. fro drige stede to oder<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> sechende reste. <I>Explorat. enim corda fidelium que ideo dicuntur arida; quia sunt feruore sancti spiritus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> spirituc.</NOTE> <I>desiccata. et a mollicie fluxe cogitacionis purgata.</I> &ETH;e drige stedes &thorn;at &thorn;e fule 
<PB REF="00000115.tif" N="87"> gost wandre&eth; abuten sechende him reste. &thorn;at is &thorn;e bileffulle mannes heorte &thorn;e clene ben wasshen of &thorn;e embe&thorn;onke; of flesh|liche lustes. and drigen bi &thorn;e hete of so&eth;e luue to god and to men. Swiche hertes fonde&eth; &thorn;e fule gost; deies and nihtes. and cunne&eth; gif he mai &thorn;er-inne herbergen. and &thorn;enne he a none ne mai he sei&eth; to him seluen <I>Reuertar in domum meam unde exiui</I>. Ihc wile turnen agen to mine huse &thorn;e ich er ut of wende. <I>Et ueniens in[uenit] eam</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. ean.</NOTE> <I>uacuam scopis mundatam et ornatam.</I> And cume&eth; &thorn;erto and fint hit emti. and mid beseme clene swopen. and faire maked. &thorn;is iudeuisse folkes lage was. and get is. &thorn;at on &thorn;e ehtende dai after &thorn;e childes burde; &thorn;e frend shopen &thorn;e child name. and mid stone &thorn;e for &thorn;e nones was maked for to keruen &thorn;at fel biforen on his strenende lime. and &thorn;is lage sette ure drihten bi &thorn;e patriarche abraham. and bed him holden hit. and al his ofspring after him. and &thorn;at hem clensede of sinnes alse us do&eth; fulnenge. <I>[E]t habuit circumcisio eandem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? uirtutem <I>or</I> uim <I>omitted</I>.</NOTE> <I>iudei quam habet nunc baptismus delendo peccatum. sed non aperiendo celum.</I> and &thorn;e lage hadde &thorn;o alle &thorn;e mihtes &thorn;e haue&eth; nu fulluht. for &thorn;at clensede &thorn;e man of sinne; swo do&eth; nu fulluht. ac it ne openede <MILESTONE N="66" UNIT="p">hem noht &thorn;e blisse of heuene alse fulcneng do&eth; us. and &thorn;is lage fleme&eth; &thorn;e fule gost ut of &thorn;e child. and he wandrede wide weruende<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. wer|nende.</NOTE> longe sechende him o&eth;er stede. on bileffulle manne. and &thorn;e children weren clensed of sinnen. and &thorn;us bilefden for&eth; &thorn;at hie understonden wurldes wit and mannes munde. &THORN;anne com eft &thorn;e fule gost &thorn;e was er flemd ut of him. and fint it emti of iuele gostes. and clensed of fule sinnes. and diht mid lo&eth;les|nesse. <I>Et tunc uadit et alios sumit vii</I><SUP>te[m]</SUP> <I>spiritus nequiores se et ingressi habitant ibi.</I> and &thorn;anne ferde &thorn;e fule gost. and seuene o&eth;re gostes mid him forcu&eth;ere &thorn;en him self were. and bitrumede &thorn;at child. and waiteden hit on eche wise. and forteh|ten hit and biwunden it. and biwalden it al. swo &thorn;at it eft<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. est.</NOTE> bifel on his o&eth;er wune. &thorn;enne com &thorn;e fule gost ef[t] into his wunienge. and forte&eth; &thorn;at child; swo leng swo more to here wille. and &thorn;er fore was here ende werse &thorn;ane here biginnenge. &thorn;e seuen fule gostes &thorn;at ich nu embe was. waren &thorn;e seuen difles giltes; &thorn;at ure drihten drof ut of seinte marie magdaleine. and for&thorn;i weren 
<PB REF="00000117.tif" N="89"> here biginni[n]g of here liflode swich se he were. &thorn;e ende war&eth; fair. and god. and blisful. Swo wur&eth;e ure alre. &thorn;at wile ure drihten. <I>Qui viuit et Regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="15" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XV. DOMINICA PALMARUM.</HEAD>
<P><I>Turbe que precedebant dominum. et que sequebantur clamabant dicentes. osanna filio dauid; benedictus qui uenit in nomine domini.</I> It is custume &thorn;at ech chirchsocne go&eth; &thorn;is dai a procession. and &thorn;is wune haue&eth; &thorn;e biginnigge of &thorn;e holie procession. &thorn;e ure <MILESTONE N="67" UNIT="p">helende makede to ward te stede &thorn;er he wolde de&eth; &thorn;olen. <I>Et cum uenisset bethfage ad montem oliuarum. Mittens [duos] de discipulis iussit adduci asinam et sedit super eam.</I> &THORN;o &thorn;e com to bethfage Swo hatte &thorn;e &thorn;rop &thorn;e preste one wunien. bi sides ierusalem on &thorn;e fot of &thorn;e dune &thorn;e men clepen munt oliuete. &thorn;o sende tweien of hise diciples into &thorn;e bureh of ierusalem. and bed hem bringen &aacute; wig one te riden. no&eth;er stede. ne palefrei. ne fair mule. ac &thorn;eh he alre louerdes louerd. and alre kingene ki[n]g. na&thorn;eles he sende after &thorn;e alre unwur&thorn;este wig one to riden. and &thorn;at is asse. and gaf us forbisne of admodnesse on his dede. alse he do&eth; on o&eth;re stede on his speche &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Discite a me; quia mitis sum et humilis corde</I>. lerne&eth; of me for &thorn;at ich am milde and admod on herte. and &thorn;o tweien sander|bodes ferden and cudden in &thorn;e bureh. &thorn;at &thorn;e helende was &thorn;ider|ward. and funden an asse mid fole. and ledden hit to-genes him. and &thorn;e holie apostles leiden here clo&thorn;es &thorn;eruppe and ure helende rod &thorn;erone; into &thorn;e holie burh. and &thorn;at burh folc hihten &thorn;e hege strete and bihengen it mid palmes. and mid o&eth;re riche wedes. &thorn;er he wolde &thorn;urh faren to &thorn;e holi temple. and wenden ut togenes him. and beren on here honde blostme sum palm twig. and sum boh of oliue alse &thorn;e holie boc sei&eth;. <I>Occurrunt turbe cum floribus et palmis redemtori o[b]uiam. et cetera.</I> &ETH;et <MILESTONE N="68" UNIT="p">folc com togenes him. mid blostmen. and mid palmes. and understoden him mid procession. swo me ki[n]g shal. and &thorn;o &thorn;e ferden biforen him. and &eth;o &thorn;e after him comen. remden lude 
<PB REF="00000119.tif" N="91"> stefne &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>[O]sanna filio dauid benedictus qui uenit in nomine domini.</I> Silof daui&eth;es bern blesced bie he &thorn;e cume&eth; a godes name. and &thorn;o children &thorn;e weren biforen diden alse &thorn;e godspel sei&eth;. <I>Pueri hebreorum viam pro et cetera.</I> &THORN;e children briggeden &thorn;e wei biforen ure drihten. sume mid here clo&eth;es. and sume mid boges &thorn;e hie breken of<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> os.</NOTE> &thorn;e trewes and swo him brohten into &thorn;e holie temple. alse in his heor&eth;liche heg settle. &THORN;us makede ure helende his holie procession. fro betfage to ierusalem. and elhc cristene man make&eth; &thorn;is dai procession fro chirche to chirche. and eft agen. and bitocne&eth; &thorn;e holie pro|cession &thorn;e he makede &thorn;is dai. and &thorn;at mai ech man under|stonden. &thorn;e wot wat bitocne&eth; &thorn;ese tweie names. betfage. and ierusalem. <I>Betfage interpretatur domus bucce. uel buccarum siue maxillarum. et significat ecclesiam in qua bucce fun|guntur officio suo peccata confitendo ueniam postulando. deum laudando. Carnem christi manducando. et sanguinem eius bibendo. gratias agendo.</I> Betfage is cleped on englisse mu&eth;ene hus. and bitocne&eth; holie chirche. &thorn;at men noten inne here mu&eth;es wike. &thorn;anne hie seien here sinnes. and forgiuenesse bidden. and ure louerd ihesu christ herien. and bruken his fles and his blod. &thorn;at his<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> &thorn;e holi husel. and him <MILESTONE N="69" UNIT="p">&thorn;anken. <I>Ieru|salem interpretatur uisio pacis et item significat ecclesiam in qua pax uera uidetur dum passio christi recolitur. et pacis osculum datur.</I> Ierusalem is cleped so&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> siht.</NOTE> of sahtnesse. and bitocne&eth; holie chirche &thorn;er bileffulle men inne be&eth; sehte. &thorn;enne prest cristes &thorn;roweinge minege&eth;. and of &thorn;e calice understonde&eth; tocne of sehtnesse. &thorn;at is messe cos. and &thorn;e folc sent. and &thorn;ermide bitocne&eth; &thorn;at ure drihten is &thorn;ureh &thorn;e holie loc wi&eth; bileffulle men maked sehte. and &thorn;erfore chirche haue&eth; &thorn;e tocninge of bethphage &thorn;enne &thorn;e procession ut go&eth; of ierusalem. and eft &thorn;enne it in cume&eth;. Nime we &thorn;enne geme gif ure procession bi maked after ure helendes procession. On his procession ferde sume biforen him and makede his weie toward ierusalem. and sume briggeden &thorn;e asse mid here clo&eth;es. and sume mid boges &thorn;e hie breken of &thorn;e trewes. &ETH;o &thorn;e &thorn;e weie makeden biforen him. bien folkes lor&thorn;eawes. bisshopes and prestes. &thorn;e mid here wise lore 
<PB REF="00000121.tif" N="93"> ride&eth;. and maked godes weie in to mannes heorte. &ETH;o &thorn;e briggeden &thorn;e asse mid here clo&eth;es. ben &thorn;o &thorn;e wisse&eth; &thorn;e folc mid faire forbisne of here weldede. &ETH;o &thorn;e briggeden &thorn;e asse mid &thorn;e brokene boges. ben &thorn;o &thorn;e leren &thorn;e folc to understonden god noht mid weldede. ac mid wise speche. &thorn;o &thorn;e after him comen ben &thorn;o &thorn;e here lif [leden] alse here lor&eth;eawes hem lere&eth;. &thorn;o &thorn;e bisides weren on his riht half. ben &thorn;o &thorn;e clene lif leden to quemende gode; noht for hereworde. &thorn;o &thorn;e on his lift hond comen ben &thorn;o &thorn;e clenliche liuen <MILESTONE N="70" UNIT="p">noht forto quemende gode; ac for hereword to hauen. &ETH;e asse &thorn;e ure helende uppe set. ben &thorn;o forsinegede &thorn;e hauen al here &thorn;onc uppen eor&eth;liche richeise. and sinne hem is lo&eth; to leten. and unwill[i]che to bete. for hem &thorn;inche&eth; &thorn;at godes hese heuieliche seme&eth;. and na&eth;eles gif hie ful don hie shulen on heuene endelese mede fon. Ure louerd ihesu christ &thorn;e makede into ierusalem &thorn;is dai his holie procession. &thorn;e ech chirche to-dai minege&eth;. wisse and fulste us swo to folgen his holi eor[&thorn;]liche procession &thorn;at we mo<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ben on &thorn;e holie procession &thorn;e he wile maken a domes dai mid hise chosene; fro &thorn;e dome in to heuene. <I>Quod nobis prestet qui secula per omnia regnat</I>.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="16" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XVI. <I>IN DIE PASCHE.</I></HEAD>
<P><I>HEC est dies quam fecit dominus exultemus et letemur in ea.</I> &THORN;is dai haue&eth; ure drihten maked to gladien. and to blissen us &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. and giarked &thorn;at holie gestninge. &thorn;e he offe spec&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ecce prandium meum paratum.</I> Mi bord is maked. and us bidded<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> alle &thorn;erto &thorn;us seggende. <I>Venite prandium</I> Cume&eth; to borde and understonde&eth; bred. ac er &thorn;enne &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> we.</NOTE> holie bord bugen. and &thorn;at bred understonde do we alse &thorn;e apostel bad. seiende &thorn;us. <I>Probet autem se ipsum homo. et sic de pane illo edat et de calice bibat</I>. Proue ech man him seluen. and gif he fele&eth; &thorn;at he is wur&eth;e &thorn;er to; &thorn;enne understonde he &thorn;at husel. and drinke of &thorn;e calice. &thorn;e man hit understonde&eth; wur&eth;liche &thorn;e cume&eth; &thorn;erto on bicumeliche wise. and mid 
<PB REF="00000123.tif" N="95"> bicumeliche wede. and on bicumeliche time. On bicumeliche wise <MILESTONE N="71" UNIT="p">cume&eth; &thorn;e man &thorn;e Erest shewe&eth; preste his sinnes and forlete&eth; and bimurne&eth; and nime&eth; &thorn;erof god wissinge. and o&eth;er si&eth;e &thorn;e holie acxen uppen his heued. and &thorn;e six pinen &thorn;e &thorn;erto bilien. <I>scilicet vigilias. labores. saccum. inedia. sitim.</I> &thorn;at is wecche and swinch. harde clo&eth;es. smerte dintes. selde eten and lesse drinken. &THORN;ridde si&eth;e palm sunedeies procession. feor&eth;e si&eth;es shere&eth;uresdaies absolucio[n] &thorn;e li&eth;e &thorn;e sinne bendes. &thorn;e fifte si&eth;e crepe to cruche on lange fridai sixte si&eth;e on ester euen gon abuten &thorn;e fantston. &thorn;e bitocne&eth; &thorn;e holie sepulcre. and &thorn;e seue&eth;e si&eth;e &thorn;at holie bord bugen and &thorn;at bred bruken. bicumeliche wede ben tweire kinne. lichamliche and gostliche. &thorn;e lichamliche wedes ben manie kinnes. ac of hem ne speke ich noht ac do of &thorn;e gostliche. &thorn;e ben ec fele kinnes. and alle hie bien faire him &thorn;e &thorn;e husel underfo&eth;. ac two &thorn;eroffe ben swiche &thorn;at no man ne mai underfo. him seluen to hele bute he haue here o&eth;er on him. &thorn;e ben &thorn;us clepede. <I>Vestis innocencie. Vestis misericordie.</I> an is lo&eth;lesnesse o&eth;er sinbote. <I>Vestis innocencie restituitur in baptismo dicente sacerdote [A]ccipe uestem candidam et inmaculatam.</I> lo&eth;lesnesse understonde&eth; &thorn;e man at his folcninge. and &thorn;at bitocne&eth; &thorn;e crisme clo&eth;. &thorn;e &thorn;e prest biwinde&eth; &thorn;at child mide. and &thorn;us sei&eth;. Underfo shrud wit and clene. &thorn;is shrud haue&eth; ech man on him after his fulcninge. alle &thorn;e wile &thorn;e he him berege&eth; &thorn;at he ne do ne ne que&eth;e. ne ne &eth;enche no &thorn;ing for &thorn;at he bie unwur&eth;ere gode; <MILESTONE N="72" UNIT="p">ne lo&eth;ere men; &thorn;e iuele is soule; &THORN;is wede is wel bicumeliche and biheue ech man to hauen &thorn;enne he husel underfo&eth;. &ETH;et o&eth;er gostliche shrud ich embe spece; is mildhertnesse. &thorn;e is nemed ec; armhertnesse armheorted is &thorn;e man. &thorn;e swi&eth;ere reowe&eth; his sinne. and he hem forlet and bet. and milce bit. alse ure drihten bad seien &thorn;us. Miserere anime <I>tue</I> placens deo. haue reo&eth;e of &thorn;in ogen sovle. &thorn;enne likeste gode. Mildheorted be&eth; &thorn;e man &thorn;e reou&eth; his nehgebures unsel&eth;e. and like&eth; here alre sel&eth;e and of&thorn;in&eth; sore wrecche mannes wanrede. and freure&eth; hem mid his weldede. No man &thorn;e sineged haue&eth; ne mai wi&eth;uten &thorn;us<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS. Read</I> &thorn;ise.</NOTE> wedes holi husel under|fon; 
<PB REF="00000125.tif" N="97"> bute to eche harme his soule and lichame and ech man &thorn;e hit underfo&eth; wi&eth;uten ei&eth;er &thorn;ese wedes shal ben shameliche driuen ut of &thorn;is holi gestninge. and bunden togedere his honden. and his fet. and worpen in to &thorn;e ateliche pit of helle bi ure drihtenes word &thorn;e sei&eth; to swiche men. <I>Amice quomodo huc intrasti non habens uestem nupcialem et cetera</I> hwu come &thorn;u ider in mid unbicumeliche weden. &thorn;is dai is bicumelich time husel to underfon. <I>Quia hec dies quam fecit dominus. non quod magis hanc quam alias. sed quia maiora quam in aliis &aacute; morte resurgendo. et nos &aacute; morte resuscitando</I>. for &thorn;at &thorn;is makede ure drihten &thorn;e makede alle o&eth;re. ac he kidde o&eth;erluker his mihte. and mankin more milce dide on &thorn;is dai; &thorn;anne on ani o&eth;re. &ETH;o he aros of dea&eth;e rerde us mid him. <I>Vnde exultemus et letemur in ea</I>, he us fette ut of helle wowe. and &thorn;ermide us gledede. and gif we him folgie&eth; he gif&eth; us heuene wele and &thorn;ermide us blisse&eth; to dai &thorn;onked. wur&eth;e him. for&thorn;i &thorn;is dai is cleped estrene dai. &thorn;at is aristes dai. for &thorn;at &thorn;e he &thorn;is dai aros of dea&eth;e. and we alle don; <MILESTONE N="73" UNIT="p">&thorn;anne we holi husel undernimen. gif we ben &thorn;e togenes on clene liflode. and on rihte leue. and wi&eth; alle men sehte. Ure louerd &thorn;e us bit to &thorn;is gestninge. and bringe us to his holi fleis and to his holi blod and leue us hem to bruken. and &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Accipite et commedite ex hoc omnes hic est e. c. s. m. n. et cetera.</I> Understonde&eth; &thorn;is and bruke&eth; it alle. for it is mi lichame &thorn;e giu shal alle lesen. he bet us ec his holi blod &thorn;e shal ben shad giu to lesende and sei&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;ese two &thorn;ing bien ure bileue. <I>Caro mea uere est cibus et sanguis meus uere est potus.</I> Mi fleis is wis mete. and mi blod iwis drinke and after &thorn;at he sei&eth;. <I>Nisi manducaueritis carnem filii hominis et biberitis eius sangui|nem non habebitis uitam in uobis.</I> Ne muge hauen no lif on giu bute ge liuen bi mi fleis and bi mi blod. &thorn;at husel &thorn;e ge understonden; is his holi fleis and his blod. Erest it be&eth; ouelete and win. and &thorn;ureh &thorn;e holi word &thorn;e ure helende him self seide mid his holi mu&eth;; and efter him prest hem sei&eth; atte swimesse turne&eth; &thorn;e bred to fleis and &thorn;e win to blod. <I>Set in carne remanet forma color et sapor.</I> ac on &thorn;e holi fleis bileue&eth; &thorn;e 
<PB REF="00000127.tif" N="99"> shap and hiu. and smul of ouelete. and on &thorn;e holi blod hew and smul of win. More mihte do&eth; ure helende &thorn;enne &thorn;e holi word &thorn;e he &thorn;urh his mu&eth; spec. &thorn;anne he giue&eth; mannes cuinde. and Na&thorn;eles &thorn;anne man ete&eth; and drinke&eth; &thorn;ureh &thorn;e lichames cunde &thorn;at bred wur&eth; to fleis. and &thorn;e drinke to blod. for &thorn;i mai godes word turnen &thorn;e ouelete to fleis. and &thorn;at win to blod. and swo do&eth;. and &thorn;at is &thorn;e felefolde heste. &thorn;e is alre hestene heste &thorn;at alle cristene men agen to dai to noten. for &thorn;at &thorn;is dai is cleped estre dai &thorn;at is estene da. and te este is husel. and no man ne mai seien husel<NOTE PLACE="foot">A play upon the word <I>husel</I>, as if made up of <I>hu</I> = how, and <I>sel</I> = good: in ll. 8, 9, there is a similar play upon <I>estre</I> and <I>este</I>, and in ll. 34, 35, upon <I>estre, este</I>, and <I>ariste</I>.</NOTE>; wu god it is. <I>Quia est precium mundi.</I> for it is wur&eth; al &thorn;e wereld. and betere &thorn;ene <MILESTONE N="74" UNIT="p">al &thorn;e wereld. &thorn;is is &thorn;e holi manne &thorn;e ure drihten sende alse snow sle&eth;rende alse &thorn;e prophete sei&eth;. <I>Pluit ille manna ad manducandum et panem celi dedit eis. [P]anem angelorum manducauit homo.</I> he let hem reine manne<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. lxxviii. 25.]</NOTE> to bi-liue. and gef hem bred of heuene. and men eten englene [bred]. <I>Manna interpretatur. quid est hoc?</I> Manne bitocne&eth; wat is tis; and &thorn;o ure drihten sende &thorn;is mete fro heuene &thorn;e israelisse folke; it war&eth; on eches mu&eth; wat mete se he mest luuede. and bitocne&eth; holi husel; &thorn;e ech cristeman understont nu&eth;e. &thorn;e is &thorn;e manne hegeste sweteste este &thorn;e is of sinne clensed. o&eth;er bigunne to clensende. and alre bitere biterest eches mannes soule &thorn;e ne haue&eth; alle michele sinnes forleten. and bet. o&eth;er bigunnen alse &thorn;a<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> apostel sei&eth;. <I>Qui manducat corpus domini et bibit et cetera.</I> Ech &thorn;e understande&eth; &thorn;at holi husel unwur&eth;liche he understant him seluen eche pine. and endelese wowe. Nime we nu geme ure ech agen him seluen. gif we bien cumen on bicumeliche wise. &thorn;at is to so&eth; shrifte. to holi axen a palm sunedai; to procession. a shere&eth;ursdai to absoluciun. a lange|fridai to holi cruche. an ester euen to procession [abuten &thorn;e fanstone]. and gif we ben cumene mid bicumeliche wede. of lodlesnesse &thorn;at is clensinge. swo &thorn;at we hauen ure sinnes for|leten. and bi shriftes wissenge bet. o&eth;er bigunnen to beten. and milce bidden. &thorn;anne muge we bicumeliche to godes bord; bugen. and his bode wur&eth;liche bruken. and &thorn;ureh &thorn;e holi este cumen 
<PB REF="00000129.tif" N="101"> to Ariste<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Looks like</I> driste <I>in MS</I>.</NOTE>. <I>Quod nobis prestet qui hodie surrexit et uiuit cum deo patre in unitate spirituc sancti.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="17" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XVII. [DOMINICA I POST PASCHA.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Stetit ihesus in medio discipulorum suorum &amp; dixit eis. pax</I><MILESTONE N="75" UNIT="p"> <I>uobis. legitur in ewangelio quod dominus ante passionem sedit dum discipulos docuit inter passionem et resurrectionem iacuit et quieuit. post passionem uero stetit. pacem eis opt[a]uit.</I> we reden on &thorn;e holi godspel boc. &thorn;at ure helende &thorn;rowede on &thorn;e holi rode. and dea&eth; &thorn;olede. and mid his e&eth;eliche dea&eth;e lesde us of eche dea&eth;e. and on &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai aros of dea&eth;e. and arerde us mid him. and bihet us eche lif on blisse. gif we lede ure lif nu swo he us wisse&eth;. We nime geme of &thorn;re &thorn;ing on &thorn;is tale. on is &thorn;at biforen his &thorn;roweunge he sat ofte and tahte wisdom &thorn;an &thorn;e him folgeden. o&eth;er is &thorn;at bitwenen his &thorn;rowenge and his ariste he lai on his sepulcre and swiede. and for &thorn;at ben &thorn;e &thorn;re dage biforen estre cleped swidages. &ETH;e &thorn;ridde is &thorn;at he stod among hise diciples<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Originally</I> deciple.</NOTE>. and bed hem fri&eth; alse seint lucas sei&eth; on his godspelle &thorn;us quedinde. [S]tetit ihesus<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> ihe.</NOTE> et cetera. Ure louerd stod among his diciples; and bed hem fri&eth;. and sehtnesse. Fri&eth;; for &thorn;at he hadde maked hem fre; of &thorn;e deules &thorn;ralsipe. &thorn;e hie hadden and al ofspri[n]g one wuned. fro &thorn;e time &thorn;e adam ure forme fader gilte forte &thorn;at ure helende mid his dea&eth;e hem alesde. Sehtnesse; for &thorn;at &thorn;e he makede sehte &thorn;e heuen|liche fader wi&eth; ma[n]kin. and opene[de] togenes hem &thorn;e giate of paradis. &thorn;e &thorn;urh eue gilte wi&eth; hem was er tined. <I>His tribus Modis ponimur in huius exilii miseria quod alii sedent, alii iacent. alii stant.</I> On &thorn;ese &thorn;re wise we wuneden on &thorn;is wreche wereld. sume sitte&eth;. and sume lige&eth;. and sume we stonde&eth;. <MILESTONE N="76" UNIT="p">&ETH;anne we hauen ure sinnes forleten. and bireused. and bet. and ben huseled. we ben hege. ac alse wat se we sinegen. we ben fro hege to loge. and &thorn;eh us ure sinnes rewe. and imint hauen &thorn;at we hem wile forleten, na&eth;eles we sitte&eth; for&eth; &thorn;at we hem forleten. and beten alse ure drihten us minege&eth; bi &thorn;e prophete &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Surgite postquam sedistis q. m. p. d.</I> Arise&eth; 
<PB REF="00000131.tif" N="103"> &thorn;anne ge hauen seten. ac we ne mugen &thorn;at don; wi&eth;uten his elpe. seie we &thorn;anne to him. <I>Domine tu cognouisti sessionem meam et resurrectionem meam.</I> louerd &thorn;u wost wu ich habbe seten. and &thorn;at ich ne mai wi&eth;-uten &thorn;in elp risen. <I>Exurge domine adiuua me. i. fac me exurgere</I>. aris louerd; and elp me up. &ETH;us sit man on his sinne swo ich seid haue. and &thorn;us li&eth; swo ich nu seie wile. &ETH;anne man sinege&eth; gretliche. and him &thorn;inche&eth; &thorn;e sinne swete. and ne wile noht forleten hit. for &thorn;at it him on sume wise like&eth;. and &thorn;eh he hem forlete ne wile noht bi shriftes wissinge bete. he be&eth; ne&eth;er &thorn;anne he er was. alse fro sete to leire and demd to dea&eth;e. and &thorn;erto bunden. swo is &thorn;e man &thorn;e halt faste his sinne. he is demd fro heuene to helle. fro ure louerd ihesu christ to alle deules. fro eche liue; to eche pine. bote he &thorn;e bendes breke. and berege him mid bote. and alle &thorn;e wile &thorn;e he &thorn;us li&eth; on his sinne; &thorn;e rihte bileue and &thorn;e so&eth;e luue. &thorn;e he hah to hauen to gode; ben leirede. and slaine on his heorte and &thorn;er &thorn;urh he swike to undernimende alle holsum lore. <I>Et sic ihesus iacet in sepulcro cordis illius. et quiescit aput illum a doctrina usque in diem tercium scilicet mentis illuminacionem. Primus enim dies <MILESTONE N="77" UNIT="p">est lux boni operis. Secundus clarificacio sermonis. Tercius illuminacio mentis.</I> and on &thorn;at wise li&eth; ure helende on his heorte. alse on sepulcre. and swige&eth; of holsumnesse lore togenes him; forte &thorn;at on &thorn;en &thorn;ridde dai; &thorn;at is heorte be liht for &thorn;eh he do edie dede. &thorn;e is nemned to o&eth;er dai. bo&eth;e him helpe&eth; litel o&eth;er noht. bute he haue god &thorn;onk &thorn;e is euened to &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai. ac alse wat swo &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dage&eth;. &thorn;at be&eth; &thorn;anne his heorte understant &thorn;e liht of rihte bileue. and of so&eth;e luue. &thorn;enne rise&eth; ure helend on his heorte. and teche&eth; him holsum lore. and &thorn;us sei&eth;. <I>Cur iaces pronus in terra; Surge</I>. Wi list &thorn;u turnd on &thorn;e eor&eth;e; aris. &thorn;at is to seien hwi luuest &thorn;u &thorn;ine fule sunnes. forlet hem. and bireuse hem. and bet hem. and bide milce; &thorn;erof. and gif he &thorn;is lore understonde&eth;; he arist and stant. and ure helende stant on is<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> heorte. and bede&eth; him &thorn;anne fri&eth;. and sehtnesse and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Pax uobis.</I> fri&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">The author of this Homily gives us a bit of popular etymology: <I>peace</I> is 'fri&eth;' because it 'frie&eth;.'</NOTE>; for &thorn;at he ben &thorn;anne fried of &thorn;e deueles 
<PB REF="00000133.tif" N="105"> &thorn;ralshipe; alse ich er seide. Sehtnesse; for &thorn;at hie ben &thorn;enne sahtnede wi&eth; &thorn;e heuenliche fader. and is &thorn;e giate of paradis opened to-genes hem. <I>Per quam nos introducat. Qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="18" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XVIII. [DOMINICA IV POST PASCHA.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Omne datum optimum et omne donum perfectum desursum est; descendens a patre luminum.</I> Seint iacob &thorn;e holie apostel. &thorn;e ure drihten sette to lor&thorn;eawe. &thorn;e folc of ierusalem. he nam geme of &thorn;e wune; &thorn;e weren &thorn;o; and get bien mid mannen; fewe gode; and fele iuele. and bigan to turnen &thorn;e iuele to gode. mid his wise wordes. &thorn;e he wi&eth; hem spec mu&eth; wi&eth; mu&eth;e. &thorn;e hwile he wunede <MILESTONE N="78" UNIT="p">lichamliche among hem. and agen &thorn;e time &thorn;e ure drihten wolde him fechen fro &thorn;is wreche woreld to his blis|fulle riche; &thorn;o sette he on write &thorn;e wise word &thorn;e he spec. and &thorn;at writ sende into chirchen. and hit is cumen into &thorn;is holi minstre to dai. and biforen giu rad &thorn;eh ge it ne understonden. ac we wilen bi godes wissinge and bi his helpe. &thorn;erof cu&thorn;en giu &thorn;ese lit word. <I>Omne datum optimum et cetera.</I> Ech god giue and ful giue cume&eth; of heuene dunward. and ech idel. and unnit. and iuel; ne&eth;en uppard. &thorn;eh &thorn;e unbileffulle swo ne lete. ac lat &thorn;anne he haue&eth; sineged. on &thorn;onke o&eth;er on speche. o&eth;er on dede. Werpe&eth; &thorn;at gilt uppen ure drihten. and sei&eth;. gif god hit ne wolde; swo hit ne were. and o&eth;er while werpe&eth; it uppen sheppendes &thorn;e none ben. bute god self &thorn;e alle &thorn;ing shop; and sei&eth;. ne was me no bet shapen. and o&eth;er hwile uppen hwate. and sei&eth;. nahte ich no betere wate. and wile uppe &thorn;e deuel; and sei&eth;. he me drof &thorn;erto &thorn;e ne sholde. and lige&eth; eches wordes. for &thorn;eh &thorn;e deuel muge man bi-charre; he ne mai no man neden. and on &thorn;is wise werpe&eth; &thorn;e unbileffulle man his agen gilt uppe &thorn;e giltlese. <I>Omnis autem praua cogitacio in corde ascendit. tam innata quam illata vnde dicitur in ewangelio. Ut quid ascen|dunt cogitaciones in cordibus uestris.</I> ech unnit speche and &thorn;onc 
<PB REF="00000135.tif" N="107"> astigh&eth; in &thorn;e mannes heorte. be swo it beo. alse &thorn;is writ sei&eth;. <I>Vnus quisque traitur</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>tentatur in Vulgate.</I></NOTE> <I>&aacute; concupiscencia sua. abstractus. et illectus.</I> ech man beo&eth; bi sleht of<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. os.</NOTE> his agene <MILESTONE N="79" UNIT="p">lichames luste alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. [D]iabolus per sugestionem inmittet homini malam <I>cogitacionem</I>. &thorn;e deuel mid his for-tihtingt<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> tihtinge.</NOTE> bringe&eth; unnut &thorn;onc on mannes heorte. and te&eth; him swo to iuele speche and to werse dede. and on &thorn;is wis cume&eth; ech iuel &thorn;onc. and speche. and dede. ne&eth;en uppard. sam it haue angun of &thorn;e mannes lichames wille sam it haue &thorn;e biginning of the deules for|tuhting. and for to bileande &thorn;at no man werpe &thorn;e gilt of his sinne anuppen god; and &thorn;erfore seid seint iacob &thorn;os word. <I>Omne datum optimum et cetera.</I> ech god giue; and ful giue; cume&eth; of heuene send of lemene fader. <I>Datum aliud est bonum ut quod fouet corpus Aliud est melius ut quod ornat cor. Aliud est optimum ut quod sanctificat hominem.</I> &THORN;at godes giue is god &thorn;e fet and shrut &thorn;e lichame alse &thorn;e blostme &thorn;e cume&eth; of coren of eor&eth;e. and of treuwe. &thorn;e ben cleped werldes winne. and &thorn;at godes giue is betere. &thorn;e alime&eth; &thorn;e man of fiffolde mihte. his egen to sen his earen to listen his nose to runien<NOTE PLACE="marg">These two words are misplaced in the MS.</NOTE>. his mu&eth; to smellen<NOTE PLACE="marg">These two words are misplaced in the MS.</NOTE>. and his lichame al mid to fri&eth;ende and &thorn;at godes giue is best. &thorn;e clense&eth; &thorn;e man. of alle sinnes. and lese&eth; of helle; and to-genes him opene&eth; heuene. and &thorn;at is fulcning erest and si&eth;en husel. <I>Bonum autem aliud incoatum ut fides. Aliud pro|uectum ut spes. Aliud perfectum ut caritas.</I> Eft sone sum godes giue is bigunnen alse rihte leue. and fur&eth;re&eth; alse trust. and longenge to godes bihese and sum mid alle ful alse so&eth;luue to gode and to mannen. and swiche ben &thorn;e seuene. &thorn;e ben cleped <I>Carismatum dona. scilicet Sapiencie et intellectus et cetera. Item remissio peccatorum que datur in baptismo est datum optimum.</I> <MILESTONE N="80" UNIT="p"><I>Bonum uite eterne est donum perfectum.</I> Eftsone &thorn;e giuenesse of sinne is &thorn;e beste giue. and &thorn;ie giue he giue&eth; ech man in &thorn;e fulluht. &thorn;e giue of eche [lif] on blisse. is te fulle giue. and &thorn;eo giue he giue&eth; mid &thorn;e holi husel. &thorn;anne man it under|stonde&eth; rihtliche. and holsumliche. Swiche giues. and none iuele sende&eth; lemene fader; mankin. Leomene fader we clepe&eth; ure drihten for &thorn;an &thorn;e he sunne atend. &thorn;e steores of hire leome. 
<PB REF="00000137.tif" N="109"> and te mone of hire leome. and al &thorn;is middelherd aleme&eth;. and ure ihesu <I>christi</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. xpi.</NOTE> aleme&eth; &thorn;e selue sunne; &thorn;e alle o&eth;re &thorn;ing aleome&eth;. and ec &thorn;e man. <I>Lumine intellectus et fidei.</I> aleme&eth; of understondinesse. and of rihte bileue. <I>Angelorum autem et o. m.</I> and brin<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> brinneth.</NOTE> on englen and on mannen. &thorn;e hete of so&eth;e luve to him seluen. He sende us &thorn;e gode giue &thorn;e alle sinnes forgif&eth;. and &thorn;e fulle giue &thorn;e giue&eth; eche lif on blisse. <I>Qui viuit et Regnat per omnia [secula seculorum].</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="19" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XIX. IN ASCENSIONE DOMINI.</HEAD>
<P><I>Eleuatus est sol in celum et.</I> &THORN;e holi prophete abacuc. &thorn;e wunede on &thorn;is weorlde. and eft &thorn;erof wot. fele hundred wintre. er &thorn;e time &thorn;e ure drihten understod mannisshe. and was boren. so&eth; [god] and so&eth; man of &thorn;e holi maidenes inne&eth;e ure lafdi Seinte Marie. and na&eth;eles seh suterliche fele of &thorn;e wundren. &thorn;e ure helende dide si&eth;en; and on middenerd wrohte and &thorn;er|of spec. and nameliche of &thorn;at michele wunder &thorn;e he &thorn;is dai dide. and &thorn;erefore &thorn;ese word seide. <I>Eleuatus est sol et cetera.</I> &THORN;e sunne was efed into heuene. and te mone stod on hire stede. On &thorn;is tale is ure helend nemned sunne. for fuwer &thorn;ing. On is &thorn;at the sunne is on; and nanmo. o&eth;er is &thorn;at hie arist anes &aacute; da&iacute;. and eft sige&eth;. &THORN;e &thorn;ridde is. &thorn;at he &thorn;inke&eth; ful of liht <MILESTONE N="81" UNIT="p">for heo liht al &thorn;is middenerd<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. min|denerd.</NOTE> and te sterres<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. strerres.</NOTE> on heuene; and te mone. &thorn;at feor&eth;e is &thorn;at heo &thorn;inche&eth; ful of hete for &thorn;at hat alle &thorn;ing. &thorn;e on eor&eth;e wecse&eth;. alswo hure helende is almihtin god. and nis non o&eth;er bute he. <I>Vnde dicitur pater et filius et spiritus sanctus unus deus</I>. &THORN;e fader and &thorn;e sune and &thorn;e holigost ben on almihtin god. Eft-sone ure helende aros alse sunne. &thorn;o &thorn;e ure lafdi Seinte Marie hin<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> kennede of hire clene mei&eth;hode. alse &thorn;e holi minster boc sei&eth;. to &thorn;e heuenliche quen &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ex te ortus est sol iusticie christus dominus noster.</I> Of &thorn;e is arisen &thorn;e sunne of rihtwisnesse; &thorn;at is ure drihten christ. and he eft aseh alse sunne to-glade. &thorn;o &thorn;e iudeus him pineden on &thorn;e ho[li] 
<PB REF="00000139.tif" N="111"> rode to dea&eth;e. and his holi lichame was leid on &eth;e sepulcre alse seinte peter sei&eth;. <I>CHristus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> Xpc.</NOTE> <I>semel pro peccatis nostris mortuus est.</I> Ure helende crist &thorn;olede enes de&eth; for ure sinnes. &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. Eft-sone he is alse &thorn;e holi boc sei&eth;. <I>Fons luminis.</I> welle of liht. <I>et lux uera que illuminat omnem hominem uenientem in hunc mundum et omnia</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? cetera.</NOTE>. and he is &thorn;at so&eth;e liht; &thorn;e lihte&eth; ech man. of al &thorn;e liht &thorn;e he haue&eth; lichamliche wi&eth;uten. and gostliche wi&eth;-innen. and &thorn;e selue sunne; he lihtte&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> of al hire liht. Eft sone he is sendere of alle holie heten. alse him selfen sei&eth; on his godspel. <I>Ignem ueni mit[t]ere in terram quam uolo ut ardeat.</I> Ich com for to senden fur on eor&eth;e. and wile &thorn;at it berne. &ETH;e fur &thorn;e he embespec&eth;; is &thorn;e hete &thorn;e atent on mannes heorte. &thorn;e make&eth; him his sinnes swi&eth;e bimurnen. and luuen ure drihten more &thorn;ene him seluen. and his emcristene alse him seluen. &thorn;is sunne &thorn;at we of speken; &thorn;at is ure helende &thorn;e was &thorn;is dai heued on hegh. <I>Set cum sit supra omnem altitudinem que</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> quo.</NOTE> <I>potuit ascendere?</I> ac si&eth;&eth;en he is buuen <MILESTONE N="82" UNIT="p">alle hegnesse hwider sholde he stige. &thorn;e holi aposte[l] us sei&eth; hwu hit war&eth; and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Quod autem ascendit quid est nisi quia descendet primum in [i]nferiores partes terre.</I> Erest he steg neo&eth;er and si&eth;en on hegh. of neo&eth;erstienge spec&eth; dauid on &thorn;e salm boc. and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Inclinauit celos et descendit.</I> &ETH;e heuene abeh and dun asteh. <I>Et ascendit super cherubin et uolauit. et cetera.</I> and steh eft abuuen cherubin. and fro hwu [hegh] he to hwu loge steh; and eft agen seint ambrosius &thorn;at sei&eth; on his loft songe. &thorn;us que&eth;inde <I>Egressus eius a patre excursus usque ad inferos. et cetera.</I> he ferde fro &thorn;e fader; for &thorn;at he com ne&eth;er to helle. <I>Et in horum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <I>uia bibit de torrente mortis. propterea exaltauit caput</I> and on &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. cx. 7].</NOTE> longe weie &thorn;e he ferde fro heuene to helle he dranc of de&eth;es flode. and &thorn;arfore heuede si&eth;en up &thorn;at heued. alse seint ambrosie sei&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Recursus ad sedem dei.</I> he steh to heuen|liche heh settle. and wiche strides he makede dunward. and eft uppard; &thorn;at sei&eth; <I>sanctus</I> salomon &thorn;e wise. and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Ecce uenit saliens in montibus et transiliens colles.</I> here he cume&eth; stridende fro dune to dune. and ouer strit &thorn;e cnolles. <I>Septem igitur ut ita dicam saltus dedit. [D]e celo in uirginis uterum. Inde</I> 
<PB REF="00000141.tif" N="113"><I> in presepium. Inde in crucem. Inde in sepulcrum. Inde in infernum. INde in mundum. Et hinc in celum.</I> Seuen strides he makede. On of heuene into &thorn;e maidenes inne&eth;e. O&eth;er &thorn;enne in to &thorn;e stalle. &ETH;ridde in to &thorn;e holi rode. feor&eth;e; &thorn;anne in to &thorn;e sepulcre. fifte; into helle. Sixte; into &thorn;is Middenerd. &thorn;e seue&eth;e; eft into heuene. <MILESTONE N="83" UNIT="p">Ac &thorn;o he to helle com. &thorn;e engles &thorn;e mid him comen. clepeden to &thorn;e deuel and seiden. <I>Tollite portas principes uestras et e. p. e. et intrabit rex glorie.</I> ge maisterlinges of &thorn;esternesse opene&eth; giwer gaten. &thorn;e king of blisse wile faren<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. xxiv. 7.]</NOTE> herin. &ETH;e stefne herden &thorn;e witeies. &thorn;e &thorn;erinne weren and on of hem &thorn;at was. dauid andswerede &thorn;us. <I>Dominus fortis et potens dominus potens in prelio.</I> &thorn;e louerd &thorn;e is strong. and mihti and on fehte. and dide ure louerd alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Portas ereas con|triuit et uectes ferreos confregit. et dedit lumen his qui erant in penis tenebrarum. et ligauit satanan et captiuam ducit in captiui|tatem.</I> and ure helende brac &thorn;o &thorn;e irene herre and alto shiurede &thorn;e giaten. and in wende. &thorn;o was helle liht enes and nefre eft; of heuene liht. and bond te holde deuel. and herede helle of &thorn;o &thorn;e him hadden her er quemed. alse &thorn;e salm wrihte sei&eth;. <I>Eduxit</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. cvi. 14.]</NOTE> <I>eos de tenebris et umbra mortis et uincula eorum disripuit.</I> and he brac here bendes and ledde hem ut of &thorn;esternesse. and of dea&eth;es shadewe. and ros of de&eth;e. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde dai; &thorn;at is estrene dai. and wunede mid his diciples noht alegate; ac stundmele forte &thorn;e fuwerti&eth;e dai; &thorn;at is todai. and &thorn;o he dide alse &thorn;e holi boc sei&eth;. <I>Eleuatis manibus [suis benedixit eis. Et factum est dum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke xxiv. 50.]</NOTE> <I>bendiceret illis recessit ab eis et] ferebatur in celum et benedixit eis.</I> he heuede up his hond. and giaf hem his blescinge. and swo ferde to heuene alse dauid sei&eth;. <I>Ascendit deus in iubilo et dominus in uoce tubarum.</I> and ure drihten steh on wordlese songe. and on bemene stefne. <I>Iubilus est exultacio mentis. habita de eternis. que nec taceri potest nec lingua explicari.</I> Wordles song is &thorn;e herte michele blisse. &thorn;e heo haue&eth; of heuenliche &eth;inge. and ne mai &thorn;eroffe be stille. <MILESTONE N="84" UNIT="p">ne mid worde hem atellen. swiche ben &thorn;e songes &thorn;e me singe&eth; hege dages alse alleluia. and swiche o&eth;re. Swo dide &thorn;e apostles &thorn;o hie bihelden ure helende. &thorn;o he to heuene wende. and folgeden him mid egen &thorn;o hie mid lichame 
<PB REF="00000143.tif" N="115"> ne mihten. and of &thorn;at mihte swi&eth;e wundreden. and &thorn;erof weren swo bli&eth;e &thorn;at hie ne mihten mid worde here blisse tellen. <I>Etiam in sono tube prout regem decet ascendit</I>. On bemes steuene he. asteh to his hege home. alse me king understant &thorn;anne he to his home cume&eth;. &thorn;e bemes weren &thorn;e engles &thorn;e wi&eth; &thorn;e apostles stoden; mid snouwite shrude. and &thorn;us seiden to hem. <I>Hic est</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Acts i. 71.]</NOTE> <I>ihesus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> ihc.</NOTE> <I>qui assumptus est a vobis in [celum] sic [ueniet quem|admodum uidistes] eum euntem in celum. et cetera.</I> &thorn;e his faren fro giu into heuene he cume&eth; eft alswo ge him segen faren into heuene. &thorn;o folgede ure helende michel feord of englen. and of holie soules. &thorn;e he lesde ut of helle &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. and &thorn;o engles biforen him blewuen &thorn;e heuenliche beme. and swo kidden &thorn;at he king was cumen fro fehte. and hadde his andsete ouercumen. and &thorn;e bemene drem &thorn;e &thorn;e engles blewen. &thorn;e &thorn;ere comen biforen ure helende to heuene gaten; and &thorn;us que&eth;en to &thorn;e engles &thorn;e &thorn;er wi&eth;innen weren. <I>Tollite portas principes</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. xxiv. 7.]</NOTE> <I>uestras et elevamini porte eternales et intrabit rex glori&aelig;.</I> gie maisterlinges herwi&eth;-innen opene&eth; giure gaten, and ech gate untine&eth; giu seluen to-genes &thorn;e king of blisse &thorn;e wile faren herin. and hie &thorn;e &thorn;er-inne weren; &thorn;us andswereden. <I>Quis est iste rex glorie?</I> hwat is &thorn;is blissene king; and &thorn;o wi&eth;|uten seiden. <I>Dominus uirtutum ipse est rex glorie.</I> he &thorn;e is alre mihtene louerd he is alre blissene king. &ETH;e sunne <MILESTONE N="85" UNIT="p">&thorn;e ich of specce. &thorn;at is ure helende self; &thorn;e alle brihtnesse lihte&eth; of him seluen. he alihte to dai ure &thorn;onc of rihte bileue. and alse he atent alle holi heten. he atende todai ure herte &thorn;e twifelde hete. &thorn;at is &thorn;at we ure sinnes sore bi-murnen. and forleten and beten. and milce bidden. o&eth;er &thorn;at we hauen so&eth;e luue to him seluen. and to u[r]e emcristene. swo us longe to him alse diden hise apostles and teo hus to him; alse he hem dide and understonde mid on his riche. <I>Qui cum patre et spiritu sancto uiuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. AMEN.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="20" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000145.tif" N="117">
<HEAD>XX. IN DIE PENTECOSTE.</HEAD>
<P><I>Apparuerunt apostolis dispertite lingue tamquam ignis seditque supra singulos eorum spirituc sanctus.</I> &ETH;o &thorn;e ure louerd ihesu crist fundede lichamliche fro eor&eth;e to heuene. he forbed his apostles. and here holi ferreden &thorn;at hie neren noht sorie. &thorn;eh he hem forle[te] lichamliche and seide <I>Non turbetur cor uestrum neque formidet. Rogabo patrem et alium paracletum dabit vobis. et cum uenerit ille; docebit uobis omnem ueritatem.</I> Ne beo giuer heorte noht i&eth;reued ne ofdred. ich wile giu senden &thorn;e heuenliche frefringe wi&eth;-innen a lit dages. &thorn;e giu shal frefrin and techen alle so&eth;fastnesse and bringen ti&eth;inge of &thorn;ing &thorn;e beon to cumende. and &thorn;e faire bihese leste he &thorn;is dai. for &thorn;is dai is &thorn;e fiftuge&eth;e dai. after estrene dai. alse &thorn;e louerd seint lucas. seide on &thorn;e holie pistle. &thorn;e me ret to dai and ech holie chirche. and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Dum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? cum.</NOTE> <I>complerentur dies pe[n]tecoste erant omnes pariter discipuli in eodem loco et cetera.</I> On &thorn;e fiftu&eth;e dai. after estrene dai weren alle &thorn;e apostles. and here fereden gadered on one stede. sittinde and salmes singende. and god heriende. in &thorn;e temple of ierusalem. <I>Et factus est</I> <MILESTONE N="86" UNIT="p"><I>repente sonus tanquam aduenientis spiritus vehementis et repleuit totam donum ubi erant apostoli</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Acts ii. I.]</NOTE> <I>sedentes.</I> riht to-genes &thorn;e undrene alse &thorn;e holi songere sei&eth; on his loft songe. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Dum hora cuntis tercia; r. m. i. o. a. d. u. n.</I> &THORN;o com a dine of heuene. ase &thorn;eh it were to kidende &thorn;at &thorn;e holi gost com uppen &thorn;e apostles and filde ful &thorn;at hus &thorn;ere hie inne seten. <I>Et apparuerit illis dispertite lingue tanquam ignis seditque supra singulos eorum spiritus sanctus.</I> &ETH;o openede &thorn;e holi gost him seluen to isende bi &thorn;an &thorn;e hem &thorn;uhte shapen alse tunge fele twiselende. and on fires hewe and for &thorn;at hie him swich segen seint ambrosius shewed<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> &thorn;us; and sei&eth;. <I>Uerbis ut essent pro. et c. f.</I> &thorn;at is on englis he hem makede fundie on worde. For &thorn;eh it were ones londes speche on &thorn;e apostles mu&eth;es &thorn;e &thorn;ere speken; ech man &thorn;e hem herden were of wiche londe swo he were. for &thorn;ere weren men of eche londe &thorn;at is under heuene li&eth;e. 
<PB REF="00000147.tif" N="119"> hit &thorn;uhte here ech sunderlepes &thorn;at it was his londes speche. Swo &thorn;e holie gost hem fulde of him seluen and sette &thorn;e word on hem &thorn;e &thorn;ere speken. and skilede on hem &thorn;at hie herden. alse seint lucas sei&eth;. <I>Repleti sunt omnes spiritu sancto et ceperunt loqui prout spiritus sanctus dabat eloqui illis.</I> &THORN;us hie segen &thorn;e holi gost on tungene euene. and &thorn;erefore weren fundie on speche. alse ich nu seide. ec hie him segen on fures hewe al ich er seide. and weren &thorn;erof wallinde on so&eth;ere luue godes and mannen. swo &thorn;at hie luueden gode more &thorn;ene hem seluen. and ech cristene man alse hem seluen. <I>Ignis enim ut ait scriptura triplicem uim habet scilicet illuminandi. calefaciendi. consumendi. quam spiritus sanctus effecit in apostolis augendo fidei feruorem. caritati splendorem.</I> <MILESTONE N="87" UNIT="p"><I>et consumendo. irremittendo. siqua fuit in eis peccati macula.</I> Fir haue&eth; on him &thorn;re mihtes on to giuende hete. o&eth;er to giuende liht. &thorn;ridde to weldende elet to none &thorn;inge. &thorn;ese &thorn;re mihte notede &thorn;e holi gost on &thorn;e apostles. and &thorn;erefor com uppen hem on fires hewe alse ich er seide. and alihte hem of brihtere and of festere bileue &thorn;e hie hedden er. and maked<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> hem hattere on so&eth;e luue to gode and mannen, and welde here sinnes to none &thorn;inge, for gif anie hadden don he hem mid alle forgaf. &ETH;us &thorn;e holie apostles were gadered on ane stede. and &thorn;us &thorn;e holi gost com uppen hem and fulde hem of him seluen. and freurede hem of sorege. and tehte hem speken eches londes speche. and lihte hem of rihte bileue and makede hem hattere on so&eth;e [luue] to gode and to men. and clensede hem alle of &thorn;e hore of alle sinnes. Bidde we nu &thorn;e holigost &thorn;at he haue milce of us and gife us hige. and mihte. to forleten and bireusen and beten ure sinnes. and gedere ure alre herte to clene &thorn;onke alse he gaderede &thorn;e holie apostles. in &thorn;e temple. and hure lichames in &thorn;is holie minstre. &thorn;at he cume uppen us and wune in us. and freure us of alle sorege alse he hem dide. and lihte<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> bihte.</NOTE> on us rihte bileue. and make us wallende of so&eth;e luue and clene of alle sinnes. and giue us swo findige speche. &thorn;at &thorn;e fewe word &thorn;e we on ure bede seien be cu&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="foot">I think we ought to read <I>tu&eth;e</I> (cp. <I>ti&eth;e</I> on p. 125)=favourable, acceptable. In the MS. <I>c</I> and <I>t</I> are very similar; and in <I>cu&eth;e</I> the top of the <I>c</I> is longer than usual.</NOTE> alle halegen; &thorn;e wunie&eth; on heuene 
<PB REF="00000149.tif" N="121"> &thorn;at hie &thorn;ingen us to &thorn;e &thorn;remnesse. fader. and sune. and holi gost. &thorn;at he wisse and fulste fulien &thorn;er apostlene lore. and on here ferreden hauen eche lif and blisse mid him. <I>Qv[i] viuit et regnat in vniuersa secula seculorum deus.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="21" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXI. [SERMO IN PS. LIII. 1.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Dominus de celo prospexit super filios hominum vt videat si [est] intelligens aut requirens deum. [O]mnes declinauerunt simul inutiles facti [sunt] non [est] qui faciat bonum [non est] usque ad unum.</I> &ETH;e holi prophete dauid sei&eth; on ane stede on &thorn;e salm boc &thorn;e wordes &thorn;e ich her nu seide. &thorn;er he spec&eth; of &thorn;e mild|hertnesse &thorn;e ure louerd ihesu crist do&eth; men. and of &thorn;e wi&eth;erful|nesse &thorn;e men don togenes him. Mild-heorte he is togenes heom on two wise, alse him self sei&eth; on &thorn;e holi godspel. <I>Ueni uocare peccatores ad penitenciam et recip[er]e</I> <MILESTONE N="88" UNIT="p"><I>penitentes ad iustificacionem.</I> Ich com to clepen &thorn;o forsingede to sinbote. and under|stonden &thorn;o sinbetende on rih[t]wisnesse. and to lesen &thorn;e &thorn;rales of &thorn;ralshipe. and giuen hem freshipe. and on alle wise he freure&eth; &thorn;o forsinegede &thorn;e frefringe wilen understonden Ac togenes &thorn;is manifold mildhertnesse. men bien swo wi&eth;erfulle. &thorn;at swo he gerenluker<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> geten|luker.</NOTE> clepe&eth; hem to him. swo hie wi&eth;ere turne&eth; froward him. alse ich er sede. <I>Dominus de celo prospexit super filios hominum ut et cetera. Omnes declinaverunt simul.</I> Ure drihten &thorn;e is alre louerde louerd bihe<NOTE PLACE="marg">? beih.</NOTE> of heuene to mannen. and lokede gif here ani understoden o&eth;er bi-sohten him. and seh &thorn;at alle hie turnden fro him hem seluen to unbihefe and of hem alle ne was bute on &thorn;at dide anie gode dede. Alse he loke&eth; nu fro heuene to us. and se&eth; &thorn;at we ne understonden ne bisechen him noht swo us nied were. ac turnen fro his hese; to ure lichames wille. bute hit beo ani god friht<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Top of</I> f <I>has been erased and looks at first like a</I> t.</NOTE> man. <I>Intelligens quis homo est; qui seipsum agnoscit et deum credit.</I> &ETH;e man is understondinde &thorn;e him seluen cnowe&eth; and gode leue&eth;. <I>Ille se</I> <MILESTONE N="89" UNIT="p"><I>ipsum cognoscit qui considerat in speculo mentis quantus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <I>sit</I> 
<PB REF="00000151.tif" N="123"> <I>expositus miseriis. Vtpote natus in merore. Uiuens in labore Moriturus in dolore.</I> &THORN;e man cnowe&eth; him seluen &thorn;e &thorn;enche&eth; of wu medeme &thorn;inge he is shapen. and wu arue&eth;liche he her fare&eth;. and wu reuliche he he&eth;en wit. hider he cume&eth; on wowe and he&eth;en wit on wowe. and here wune&eth; on wanrede and &thorn;ole&eth; his unwille. hwile druie. and hwile wete. hwile chele. wile hete. hwile hunger. wile &thorn;urst. hwile chele<NOTE PLACE="marg">Repeated in MS. by mistake.</NOTE>. hwile unhele. hwile sori|nesse and wile werinesse. and hwile wurmene cheu and fele o&eth;re &thorn;e ich telle ne mai. and ne mai wi&eth;-uten helpe him seluen &thorn;er-wi&eth; werien. &thorn;us ahte ech of us him seluen to cnowen. <I>Ille autem intelligit deum. qui credit eum trinum et unum omnipo|tentem creatorem omnium.</I> &THORN;e man understant god. &thorn;e leue&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e heuenliche &thorn;remnesse. fader and sune. and holigost. is on almihti god. Shuppende. and wealdende. and dihtende of alle shafte. and &thorn;is leue shewe&eth; ech man &thorn;anne crede singe&eth;. &thorn;e man biseche&eth; god &thorn;e be&eth; is gultes cnowe. and his sinnes forlete&eth;. and sore bimurne&eth;. and bete&eth; bi his mihte. &thorn;at do&eth; ech man &thorn;enne he pater noster singe&eth;. bute his li&eth;ere liflode his bede lette. ac lit ben &thorn;at &thorn;us understonden and bishechen<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> god. and &thorn;o ben gode and &thorn;erefore mid him bileue&eth;. and alle o&eth;re don swo &thorn;e proph[et]e seid. <I>Omnes declinauerunt et cetera.</I> alle hie turnen fro gode to &thorn;e deuel bute on. <I>Quatuor sunt genera hominum. alii enim non intelligunt deum. requirunt tamen. et hii fatui. Alii intelligunt</I> <MILESTONE N="90" UNIT="p"><I>et non requirunt et hii impii. Alii nec intelligunt nec requirunt. et hii mortui. Alii et intelligunt et requirunt et hii boni et de is dictum est. Nullum genus hominum facit bonum nisi unum.</I> Fuwer kinnes men ben. &thorn;at an ne under|stant god. and na&eth;eles bisheche&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> him. and &thorn;at is unwiti mennisse. o&eth;er is &thorn;at leue&eth; god. and ne biseche&eth; him noht. &thorn;at is &thorn;at orelese mennisse. &thorn;e ne haue&eth; ore of him seluen. &ETH;e &eth;ridde ne do&eth; no&eth;er. ne understant ne biseche&eth; god. &thorn;at mannisse is &thorn;uertut forlore soule and lichame. &thorn;at feor&eth;e do&eth;. ei&eth;er understant and biseche&eth; him. &thorn;at is &thorn;at gode menisshe. and &thorn;at he understant and mid him athalt. and giue&eth; eche lif on blisse. &thorn;e ilke louerd &thorn;e ich offe speke. &THORN;e &thorn;us loke&eth; of heuene to men mid his milde egen. and se&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e wi&eth;erie&eth; to-genes him. alse don &thorn;o &thorn;e ne 
<PB REF="00000153.tif" N="125"> understonden. o&eth;er bisechen and cnowe&eth; wo ben hersume his hese. He bise to us. and giue us hige and mihte him to under|stonde. and wisse us and filste us him to bishechen mid admod &thorn;onc. and mid e&eth;ele worde and edie. and ti&eth;e us bene gif his wille beo. <I>Qui uiuit et regnat deus per omnia secula seculorum. Amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="22" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXII. DE SANCTO IOHANNE BAPTISTA.</HEAD>
<P><I>Ego uox clamantis in deserto parate uiam domini rectas facite semitas eius.</I> &THORN;e louerd seint lucas giu trinne&eth; on his godspel &thorn;e wunderlich hider kume. and &thorn;e erue&eth;liche herbiwist. and &thorn;e wunderliche he&eth;en si&eth;. of ure louerd seint iohan baptiste.<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke iii. 4.]</NOTE>
and &thorn;er he spec&eth; of his hider cume. he sei&eth; &thorn;at ure drihten sende his heg engel gabriel to on old man; &thorn;at <MILESTONE N="91" UNIT="p">was holi prophete. and ec bisshup. and het zacharie. and sende him to seien &thorn;at he sholde strene an holie child and clepen hit iohan. and seide wich lif hit sholde leden. and on his burde michel folc blisse. and bifore gode ben michel and mihti. &THORN;o understod &thorn;e holi man &thorn;at he was of michel elde. and his woreldes make was teames atold. and unberinde. and for &thorn;ese &thorn;re &thorn;ing let hit unleflich. and ne lefde hit noht; &thorn;at &thorn;e engel him seide. and &thorn;us qua&eth;. <I>Vnde hoc sciam.</I> hwu mai ich &thorn;is wite &thorn;o seide &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke i. 18, 20].</NOTE> engel. <I>Qvia non credidisti uerbis meis. ecce eris tacens et non poteris loqui usque ad diem natiuitatis eius.</I> For &thorn;u art unlef mine worde. &thorn;u shalt beo dumb forte &thorn;at child beo boren. and &thorn;erbi wite &thorn;at ich so&eth; seie. &thorn;us bicom &thorn;e holi man dumb; and on his spuse &thorn;is holi child strende. On the sixte mone&eth; &thorn;arafter was &thorn;at holi maiden ure lafdi seinte marie liht mid &thorn;e holi child ure louerd ih[es]u crist and com to hire moge Seinte elizabet &thorn;e ich er embe was &thorn;e bar on hire wombe Seinte Iohan baptiste. and alse wat se &thorn;at holi meide mid worde grette &thorn;e holie spuse; &thorn;o war&eth; so&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e engel hadde er bi &thorn;is child seid. <I>Spiritu sancto replebitur adhuc ex utero matris sue</I> &thorn;at child sholde on his 
<PB REF="00000155.tif" N="127"> moder wombe ben fild of &thorn;e holi gost alse it was. <I>Et pro|phetalis spirituc filii illuminauit spiritum matris et prophetauit uterque. hic gaudio illa uerbo.</I> for &thorn;at &thorn;e &thorn;is childes witige gost lihte &thorn;e moder gost; of witienge. swo &thorn;at hie witegede bo&eth;e of ure louerd ihesu cristes to cume. and of &thorn;e moder ure lafdi seinte marie. &thorn;at child on his blisse for hit floxede. and pleide to-genes hire. and te moder on hire worde &thorn;us seide. <I>Vnde</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke i. 43.]</NOTE> <MILESTONE N="92" UNIT="p"><I>hoc michi. ut ueniat; mater domini mei ad me.</I> We&eth;en is me cumen &thorn;at mi louerdes moder cume&eth; to me? &ETH;o &thorn;is child was boren. and him was name geuen<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> giuen.</NOTE> &thorn;o com &thorn;e fader his speche. and witegede &thorn;e childes arue&eth;liche herbiwist. and &thorn;us que&eth; <I>Tu puer propheta altissimi vocaberis preibis enim</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luke i. 76.]</NOTE> <I>ante faciem domini parare vias ejus.</I> &THORN;is child shal hoten godes prophete. and fare bifore godes neb. and maken his weies. and hit swo war&eth;. for &thorn;at alse wat se he was &thorn;ogen on wintre. and on wastme and hadde michel of wereld &thorn;inge. &thorn;o nam he geme of mannes liflode. and cnew &thorn;at here dedes weren iuele. and here speche unnutte. and fleg here ferede. for he nolde noht folgen here forbisne ne on speche ne on dede. and &thorn;erfore ferde into weste wilderne alse Seinte ambrosii sei&eth; on his loft|songe. <I>Antra deserti teneris s. c. tur. fugiens p. n. l. s. m. u. f. posses</I>. On his guwe&eth;e he fleh fro folke to weste. for &thorn;at he ne wolde. noh[t] mid lihte wordes filen his liflode. and for he was send into &thorn;e weste to maken &thorn;ere godes weies; &thorn;erefore he makede his wunienge in &thorn;e wilderne. and sta&eth;elede his liflode on fode. and on shrude. swo &thorn;at he wa[s] bicumelich to his wuninge and ec to his wike. alse hit sei&eth; on &thorn;e loft songe. <I>Prebuit hirtum tegimen camelus. a. s. tro. b. c. l. h. s. p. m. locustis.</I> Weste was his wunienge. and stark haire of oluente his wede. wilde hunie and languste his mete. and water was his drinke. &ETH;o sprong &thorn;e word of his holi liflode wide into &thorn;e londe and bigan &thorn;at folc sechen to his wunienge. for to sen his holi liflode. and to here his wise lore and wenden &thorn;o for his michele wisdom; &thorn;at hit crist self <MILESTONE N="93" UNIT="p">were. and he bigan &thorn;o to maken alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Instruendo ad fidem. inuitando ad baptismum. vocando ad penitenciam.</I> tehte hem rihte bileue. bed hem to fulcninge. 
<PB REF="00000157.tif" N="129"> and clepede hem to shrifte. &thorn;at is to reusende. and to forleten. and to beten here sinnes. for &thorn;at is shrift. &ETH;o wolden &thorn;e bisshupes. and &thorn;e o&eth;re lerede &thorn;e wuneden in &thorn;e lond; witen hwat he ware. for &thorn;at hie wenden &thorn;at hit were crist self. and senden here erendrakes to him &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Tu quis es?</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[John i. 19|23.]</NOTE> hwat art tu? <I>[E]t respondit. [N]on sum ego Christus</I>. Ne ami noht crist? and hie seiden. Artu helias. nai he seide. and hie seiden. artu prophete? nai he seide. nan &thorn;ere prophete &thorn;e ge wenen. <I>[E]t dixerunt. Quis igitur es. ut responsum demus eis qui miserunt nos?</I> Seiden hie wich andswere shule we giuen hem &thorn;e senden us to &thorn;e; and he answerede. &thorn;us que&eth;inde <I>Ego uox clamantis in [deserto] parate uiam domini rectas facite semitas ejus.</I> Ich am his steuene &thorn;e reme&eth; in &thorn;is westerne. and &thorn;us que&eth;inde. Make&eth; &thorn;e louerdes weies. and rihte&eth; his pe&eth;es. <I>Et enim uox ordine nature antecedit uerbum. sic. iohannes ordine temporum antecedit christum, Vnde dicitur hic dei uox ille uerbum.</I> liste&eth; nu wat tis westerne is. and wi ure drihten grede&eth; &thorn;er onne. <I>Populus qui malo opere dereliquid deum factorem suum. et inutili uerbo recessit &aacute; deo salutari suo. est descertus.</I> al &thorn;at folc &thorn;at &thorn;urh unnutte speche and iuele speche. and iue[le]dede. turne&eth; fro gode. and forlete&eth; his hersumnesse. is cleped westren. for &thorn;at &thorn;e he ne wune&eth; noht on hem; ne he on him; for &thorn;i is &thorn;is westren for-grouwen. mid brimbles. and mid &thorn;ornes and mid iuele wiedes. &thorn;at is to seien. &thorn;at folc is forgilt wi&eth; god. on <MILESTONE N="94" UNIT="p">unnitte speche. and on iuele dede. and on idel &thorn;onc. <I>Clamat ergo dominus ad nos per predicatores tanquam surdos et longe positos.</I> and for-&thorn;i grede&eth; ure drihten to us; alse to deue men. and fer fro him wunien. Deue we ben o&eth;er &thorn;icke liste. &thorn;anne we heren speke godes word. and nime&eth; &thorn;er to litel geme. o&eth;er non. fer fro ure drihten we ben. &thorn;eh we gon to chirche. and giuen rihte ti&eth;inge. and singen ure bede. and dele&eth; almes more for to hauen eor&eth;liche winne &thorn;ene heuenliche wele. ac turne we to ure drihten on rihte bileue. and nehtleche him on clene liflode. and maken us wei to him. on so&eth;e luue to gode and to mannen. <I>Est enim dilectio dei et proximi regia uia qua</I> 
<PB REF="00000159.tif" N="131"> <I>eundum est ad uitam.</I> for &thorn;at so&eth;e luue lede&eth; alle rihtwise men to eche blisse; &thorn;e luue&eth; god more &thorn;ane him seluen. and ech cristene man alse him seluen. ac &thorn;at is arue&eth; for&thorn;e ani eor&eth;lich man. and &thorn;erfore do we alse seint iohan baptiste us minege&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Rectas facite semitas dei nostri.</I> Make&eth; rihte godes pe&eth;es. <I>Semite dei quibus facile peruenitur ad eum sunt opera bona.</I> Godes pa&eth;es ben ure gode dedes. on elmes. and on o&eth;re &thorn;inge &thorn;e us shule leden to eche liue. <I>Que si fecerimus pro celestibus declinabimus ad terram. Si autem pro fauore populi. ad sinistram diuertemus.</I> Gif we don ure gode dedes for to hauen &thorn;is weorldes sel&eth;e. o&eth;er mannes hereword to mede. &thorn;enne make we godes weies wronge. and ne ben noht toward heuene. ac gif [we] don. and que&eth;en. and &eth;enchen wel for &thorn;at we god luuen. and us longe&eth; to him. and we &thorn;eron [h]alden to ure lifes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> lilfef.</NOTE> <MILESTONE N="95" UNIT="p">ende. &thorn;enne beo we on rihte weie. &thorn;e lede&eth; us to eche life. alse dide &thorn;e louerd <I>Seint</I> iohan baptiste. alse ich er sede. &ETH;e wun|derliche com into &thorn;is wreche woreld and her-one arue&eth;liche wunede. and her-offe at his ende wurliche wende. for he was bihaueded on herodes prisone. for he nolde noht turnen ut of &thorn;e hege weie. ne of &thorn;e rihte pa&eth;es. &thorn;e he minegede mankin to makiende. and was &thorn;er-one werchende. and farende. for to &thorn;at he [com] to &eth;e ende &thorn;at is eche lif. <I>ad quam nos ducat. qui u[i]uit.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="23" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXIII. DE SANCTO IOHANNE BAPTISTA.</HEAD>
<P><I>INter natos mulierum non surrexit maior iohanne baptista.</I> Un-ligel man selde lige&eth;. and so&eth;-sagel man sei&eth; ofte so&eth;. and he &thorn;e neure ne lihgh ne lige ne wile. ne ne mai. &thorn;at is ure helende. he sei&eth; eure so&eth; and &thorn;erefore is so&eth; &thorn;at he seide bi &thorn;e louerd Seint iohan baptiste &thorn;us que&eth;inde. INter <I>natos</I> Mulie|rum et cetera of alle &thorn;e bernes. &thorn;e ben boren of wifes bosem. nis non more &thorn;enne iohan &thorn;e fulcnere. &ETH;e forme man &thorn;e com in &thorn;is 
<PB REF="00000161.tif" N="133"> midden-erd &thorn;at was adam. ure alre fader he was more. <I>Quia inmortalis fuit. donec peccauit</I> for &thorn;at he was undea&eth;lich forte he sinede. and eure beo mihte gif he him wite wolde. ac he ne was boren of wifes bosme. ne ne hadde fader ne moder. <I>Set dominus fecit eum de uirgine terra.</I> ac ure drihten him shop of eor&eth;e &thorn;at was unfiled. Eftsone ure helend &thorn;at is sheppende and wealdende of alle shafte is more &thorn;ene Seint iohan baptiste ac he was strened of &thorn;e heuenliche fader. er &thorn;anne &thorn;e heuene o&eth;er eor&eth;e shapen were. and ne was of wifes bosme boren. and was of &thorn;e holi meydenes ure lefdi Seinte Marie. Ysaac. &thorn;at &thorn;e lif holi wimman sarra on hire elde kennede. and te lif holi man abraham. on his elde strende. <MILESTONE N="96" UNIT="p">alse ure drihten hadde er &thorn;an &thorn;an iseid. &thorn;at he sholde he ne was noht more ne for&eth;e swo michel asume wise swo seint iohan baptiste Ne non o&eth;er of wifes bosme boren. and &thorn;at is sene on &thorn;re &thorn;i[n]g of him. on his hider|cume. o&eth;er [his] he[r] biwist. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde his he&eth;ensi&eth;. <I>[A]duentus eius in mundum fuit mirabilis. Status eius in mundo difficilis multimoda afflictione carnis. Exitus eius de mundo triumphalis quia dum facinora uiriliter obstitit. et hostem uicit. et mortem perdidit et uitam inuenit.</I> his hidercume was ful of wundren. &thorn;e ure drihten wrohten; to wur&eth;ende mid sein[t] iohan baptiste &thorn;e forme wunder was; &thorn;at &thorn;o &thorn;e god fundede of heuene to eor&eth;e to fonden<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> fongen.</NOTE> mennisshe. of &thorn;e holie meidenes inne&eth;e ure lafdi Seinte Marie. &ETH;o spec &thorn;e heuenliche fader to &thorn;e sune heuenliche of seint iohan and efnede him to engel &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ecce mitto angelum meum qui preparabit uiam tuam ante faciem tuam.</I> here ich sende min engel biforen &thorn;ine nebbe &thorn;e shal ruden &thorn;ine weie to-fore &thorn;e. <I>Et reuera fuit angelus non naturaliter sed officialiter.</I> and he was iwis godes engel noht of kinde for &thorn;at he ne was noht gost; ac on wike. &thorn;at o&eth;er wunder was; &thorn;at he ches two lif holi men him to fader. and to moder &thorn;e weren bo&eth;e teames ateald. and heo &thorn;e wimman was barrage<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> swo &thorn;at heo ne mihte for unkinde hauen no child. &THORN;at &thorn;ridde wunder was. &thorn;at god sende &thorn;e holi engel gabriel to &thorn;e lif holie prest zacharie. &thorn;o &thorn;e he gede<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> hegede.</NOTE> in &thorn;e temple mid his rechel fat. to rechelende &thorn;e alter. and sende him seggen &thorn;at he sholde &thorn;is holi 
<PB REF="00000163.tif" N="135"> child strene. &ETH;e holi man sah &thorn;e heg engel atte alteres <MILESTONE N="97" UNIT="p">ende. and war&eth; of-grisen; and ofdred. and te engel qua&eth; to him;<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luc. i. 13, 14.]</NOTE> and sede <I>Ne timeas zacharia. quoniam exaudita est oratio tua et elizabet vxor tua pariet tibi filium et vocabis nomen eius Iohannem . . . . . et in nativitate eius multi gaudebunt.</I> Ne beo &thorn;u zacharie noh[t] of-grisen. &thorn;u hauest longe iwist after strene and god haue&eth; herd &thorn;ine bede; and ti&eth;ed te bene. and elizabet &thorn;i spuse shal hauen a cnauechild. and him shal to name iohan. and hit shal beo &thorn;e to michel blisse. and fele shule fagenien on his burde. <I>Erit enim magnus coram domino.</I> for he shal ben michel bifore gode. <I>Et adiecit angelus explicare seriem magnitudinis iohannis contentam in quatuor. scilicet. Virtute abstinencie. Donis gracie. Officii dignitate. Et palma uictorie.</I> &THORN;e childes michelnesse sheude &thorn;e engel on fuwer &thorn;ingen. On is wi&eth;-teinge of alle lichames lustes. and iuele lastes. <I>Et uinum et siceram non bibit et cetera.</I> &THORN;at o&eth;er is un-erned giue. &thorn;at &thorn;ridde is heh wike. &thorn;at feor&eth;e is wlites<NOTE PLACE="foot">Originally <I>whtes</I>, but the second stroke of the <I>h</I> is dotted in order to serve for an <I>i.</I></NOTE> ending his michelnesse was unhiled on ten fold wise and mo. an is &thorn;at &thorn;e heuenliche fader heuenede him to engel. <I>Vt ecce mitto angelum meum et cetera.</I> O&eth;er is &thorn;at he sende &thorn;e heh engel to &thorn;e holi man &thorn;e him strene sholde. <I>Et uox</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? uxor.</NOTE> <I>tua pariet tibi filium.</I> &THORN;at &thorn;ridde is &thorn;at &thorn;e fader bicom dumb. for he ne lefde hit noht &thorn;at &thorn;e engel him sede. <I>Et eris tacens usque ad natiuitatem eius.</I> &thorn;e feor&eth;e is. &thorn;at his moder him bar si&eth;en heo was teames atold. and neure er ne was mid childe; for kinde hit hire werende<NOTE PLACE="marg">=wernede.</NOTE>. <I>Et processit in diebus suis sterilis.</I> &thorn;e fifte is. &thorn;at &thorn;o &thorn;e he was on his moder wombe get un|boren he witegede of ure helendes to cume. and of &thorn;e maidenes &thorn;e him bar get on hire swete wombe. &thorn;at is ure lafdi seinte marie. <MILESTONE N="98" UNIT="p"><I>Et exultauit infans in utero meo.</I> &thorn;e sixte is &thorn;at elizabet was liht of &thorn;e holie gost &thorn;e was on &thorn;e child &thorn;e hie mide hiede. swo &thorn;at hie ec witegede of ure helendes to cume. <I>Et unde hoc michi ut ueniat mater domini mei ad me? </I> &thorn;e seue&eth;e is &thorn;at he giaf his fader mihte to speken &thorn;e hadde dumb 
<PB REF="00000165.tif" N="137"> ben; si&eth;e he &thorn;e engel mislefde. <I>Et apertum est os zacharie et prophetauit.</I> &THORN;e egte&eth;e is &thorn;at ure drihten him bed fulcnen on watere to synbote. and fulcning beden and ec seggen <I>Super quem uideris spiritum descendentem. et cetera. Hic est qui baptizat in spiritu sancto.</I> wanne &thorn;u sest gost cumen and wunien uppe mannen he shal fulcnen on &thorn;e holie gost to sinnes for|giuenesse. &thorn;e nige&eth;e is &thorn;at &thorn;e heuenliche &thorn;remnesse was mid him &thorn;o he fulcnede ure helende. <I>Pater in uoce. Filius in homine. Spiritus sanctus in specie columbe</I>. &THORN;e fader on stefne. &thorn;e sune on mannes efene. &thorn;e holi gost on culures hewe. &thorn;e tie&eth;e is. &thorn;at michele hereword &thorn;at ure helend him gaf &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>INter natos mulierum.</I> Of alle wifes children nis non more &thorn;anne Seint iohan baptiste. &THORN;is child him self on his liflode hadde his agen michelnesse on &thorn;re wise. <I>scilicet. Absti|nencia humilitate. Paciencia.</I> On is wi&eth;teung. o&eth;er is admod|nesse. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde &thorn;oleburdnesse. he hadde mihte te witen him of alle flesliche lustes. alse &thorn;e apostel bit. <I>Abstinete uos a carna|libus desideriis que militant aduersus animam.</I> Wi&eth;-teod giu of &thorn;e flesliche lustes. &thorn;e fihte&eth; togenes &thorn;e soule. Wi&eth;teo &thorn;ine egen &thorn;at hie ne biholden non iuel ne non un-nut<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> unnitt.</NOTE> ne for&eth;en idel. Wi&eth;teo<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> &THORN;idteo.</NOTE> &thorn;i lichame fro orguil. <MILESTONE N="99" UNIT="p">and idel. and ouer mete wede. Wi&eth;teo ec &thorn;ine golliche deden mid alle; gif &thorn;u spuse ne hauest. and gif &thorn;u spuse hauest; wi&eth;teo &thorn;e on unluuede stede. and on [un]luued time. &thorn;at is &thorn;anne &thorn;u fasten shalt. o&eth;er halgen. Ne beo &thorn;u noht wuned to don hit on unluued wise ne wilful to wecchen lust &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> &THORN;er.</NOTE> to. <I>Quoniam qui sic agit uehemens amator est et proprie uxoris adulter.</I> For alle &thorn;o &thorn;e swo don; don ewuebruche on here agene spuse. he hadde ec admodnesse &thorn;o al folc herde. hwu heh. and hwu holie he was. and hwu holi lif he ladde and wenden &thorn;at hit were self crist and seden hit. and he wi&eth;-qua&eth; and sede. <I>Non sum ego christus. nec etiam dignus ut soluam corrigiam calciamentj eius.</I> ge wenen &thorn;at ich beo crist. ac ich nam noht ne for&eth;en wur&eth;e &thorn;at ich un-cnutte his sho &thorn;uong. Ne mihte he mid none worden ki&eth;en betere; &thorn;at he admod was and him seluen mece. <I>Qvia in spiritu lenitatis peccatores corripuit. et ad penitenciam uocauit.</I> Mid softnesse he castede 
<PB REF="00000167.tif" N="139"> &thorn;e sinfulle and minegede hem to sinbote. and to clene liflode. <I>Et semet ipsum prebuit exemplum.</I> and giaf hem faire forbisne of him selfen &thorn;eh he sinful ne were alse seint ambrosii sei&eth; <I>[A]ntra deserti. t. s. a. c. turmas.</I> On his guwe&eth;e he understod &thorn;at he was send into &thorn;is midden erd. to donde &thorn;refolde wike. <I>scilicet aduentum christi prenunciare. baptismum predicare. baptizare</I>. an is to ki&eth;en cristes to cume. o&eth;er is bodien fulcninge &thorn;at &thorn;ridde is fulcnen. and me&eth;ede &thorn;o his liflode <MILESTONE N="100" UNIT="p">swo &thorn;at he was bicumelich to swiche wike. <I>Ne forte cum aliis predicaret reprobus ipse fieret.</I> For &thorn;at he ne wolde noht mis leued &thorn;enne he men lerde. <I>Nam cuius uita despicitur restat ut eius predicacio contempnatur;</I> for nis &thorn;e lor&thorn;eau noht to luuene; gif his liflode is iuel. and ful. and for &thorn;i he turnde ut of &thorn;e burh into wilderne. and fro mennes wunienge to wilde deores. and ches &thorn;ere crundel to halle. and eor&eth;hole to bure bare eor&eth;e to bedde. and hard ston to bolstre. Stiue here to shurte and gret sac to curtle. Moren and wilde uni was his mete. and noht bute water his drinke. On wecche. and on swinche. and on alle wise he wan wi&eth; his hagene lichame. and &thorn;urh swiche liflode &thorn;uhte swete his lore alle &thorn;o &thorn;e hit herden. &ETH;o ne mihte his holinesse ben no lengere for-hole. ac sprong his word wide into al &thorn;e worelde and teh folc to him to heren his wise word. and to sende his wunderliche liflode. and he minede alle men to for|leten here sinnes and beten. and on sinbote understonden fulcnenge. and fele &thorn;er of him seluen fulcnede. and bi &thorn;o dages luuede herodes &thorn;e king his bro&eth;er wif; and bi-nam hire him. and Seint Iohan hit wi&eth; seide. and lettede hit bi his mihte. and te king stod eie of him. for his holinesse. and bad him swike. and he ne dorste for godes eie forleten; &thorn;at he &thorn;e king &thorn;at &thorn;eau ne binome. &ETH;o was &thorn;e king wro&eth;; and bad binden him and don him in to prisune bute he wolde his word wi&eth;teon. &thorn;o cneu seint iohan. &thorn;at gif he wolde &thorn;olen &thorn;at te king drige his unriht he mihte liuen and ben him lief and wur&eth;. ac gif he wolde folgen ri[h]twisnesse he sholde &thorn;er <MILESTONE N="101" UNIT="p">fore his lif forleten and swo dide atten ende. for &thorn;at a maiden bad te kinge his heued. and he hit bad of acken.<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> of|acsien=<I>be demanded</I>.</NOTE> and hire bitechen. and he &thorn;at e&eth;eliche dea&eth; 
<PB REF="00000169.tif" N="141"> admodliche &thorn;olede. and &thorn;er mid bigat eche lif on blisse. Nu we hauen seid &thorn;reo &thorn;ing &thorn;e we giu biheten. hwu wunderlich was his hider-cume. and hwu wrecchede his her-biwist. and hwu siker his he&eth;ensi&eth;. and wiche wise he was more &thorn;enne ani o&eth;er man of wifes bosme boren. and a wiche wise he of &thorn;is woreldes wowe wot; in to eche wele. swo mote we alle. and &thorn;ere wunen mid him abuten ende. <I>Eo prestante quem ore predicauit. et digito monstrauit. Qui. vivit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="24" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXIV. DE SANCTA MARIA MAGDALENA.</HEAD>
<P><I>Mvlier que erat in ciuitate nomine maria iam penitens uenit ad domum symonis ubi erat ihesuc. et procidens. lacrimis pedes eius rigauit. et capillis suis tersit. et oscula affixit. et unguento unxit. cuius odore domus impleta est.</I> &ETH;e lauerd Seint l. &thorn;e trenne&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Part of</I> &eth; <I>cut off in MS.</I></NOTE> &thorn;at holi godspel &thorn;e men r&aelig;d inne holie chireche sei&eth; &thorn;ar on &thorn;at ure drihten underfeng eadmodliche ane sinfulle wimman and forgiaf hire hire sinnen. for two &thorn;inge. an is muchel le&eth;&eth;e to hire sunne. o&eth;er muchel luue to him. &ETH;as word munege&eth; us &thorn;at we nime forbisne after &thorn;es wimman. and hatien. and forleten. and beten ure sinnen. and luuen and fulien ure drihten alse hie dide. Luste&eth; nu &thorn;anne and under|nime&eth; &thorn;reo &thorn;ing. on his &thorn;es wimmannes name. O&eth;er wiche wise hie hine bisohte. &thorn;ridde hwich andswere he hire giaf. <I>Nomen igitur est maria quod interpretatur stella maris</I>. Hie is ihaten alse &thorn;at holie maiden. ure helendes moder. <MILESTONE N="102" UNIT="p">englene quen marie. &thorn;at is on ure ledene se-steorre. and &thorn;e gerise&eth; wel here ei&eth;er. <I>Vtraque enim lucis sue radium. id est exemplar in mari. id est in mundo diffundit. Illa pudicicie. Ista penitencie</I>. Hur ei&eth;er alum&eth; &thorn;e se &thorn;at is &thorn;is woreld of faire forbisne &thorn;e quen &yogh;af forbisne of mai&eth;hode &thorn;at is of clennesse. &ETH;e o&eth;er of penitentence<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>. &thorn;at is of clensunge, &thorn;at is &thorn;at brin&eth; hori to clene. and muchele mo fare&eth; on &thorn;isse s&aelig;. &thorn;at is on &thorn;isse worelde. 
<PB REF="00000171.tif" N="143"> fuliende &thorn;e leome of penitence. &thorn;at is forbisne of clennesse<NOTE PLACE="foot">Evidently an error for <I>clensunge</I>.</NOTE>. &thorn;ane don &thorn;e leome of mai&eth;hod. <I>Mundus nomine maris appellatur. tum propter procellas aduersitatum tum propter affluenciam copie. tum propter reffluenciam inopie. tum quia extra nauem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> navim.</NOTE> <I>in mari non est fiducia salutis</I>. Hali boc nemme&eth; &thorn;es woreld s&aelig;. for &thorn;an &thorn;e mistliche gelimpe&eth;. hwile of wele. and wile of wawe walke&eth; &thorn;ar-onne, alse do&eth; &thorn;e u&eth;e in &thorn;ar s&aelig;. and alse &thorn;e s&aelig; ebbe&eth; and flow&eth;; alse &thorn;is woreld hwile gif&eth; wunne. and hwile hit eft binim&eth;. and alse man sone forfar&eth; in &thorn;e s&aelig; bute he on shipe be; alse fare&eth; efrich man into helle of &thorn;esse worelde bute he on chirche bie. &thorn;urh rihte gielefe. and clene liflade. and so&eth;e luue to gode. and to eche cristene mane. &ETH;es wimman hadde ec on toname magdalene. <I>quod interpretatur turris. et significat elacionis altitudinem. ante conuersionem. et contemplacionis post conuersionem.</I> &ETH;at is on ure ledene tur. and tacne&eth; hwile heinesse of oregel &thorn;e hie hadde &thorn;o hie sinne luuede. and hwile heuenliche &thorn;onc &thorn;e hie hadde &thorn;i<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> hie sunne forlet. and bette alse ure drihten sede. <I>Maria.</I> <MILESTONE N="103" UNIT="p"> <I>optimam. partem elegit que non auferetur ab ea.</I> Marie haue&eth; icore &thorn;at beste del &thorn;at is heuenliche wunienge. &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Luc. x. 43.]</NOTE> hie habbe shal abuten ende. Nu &yogh;ie habbe&eth; iherd &thorn;es wimmanes name and ec hire toname. and wat here ei&eth;er bitocne&eth;. &yogh;e here&eth; ware heo com to ure helende. and heo him to loc brohte. and awiche wise his milce bisohte. and hwu hie &thorn;are ierdede<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS. Read</I> er dede.</NOTE> &thorn;o heo hadde se swi&eth;e heo selue forsineged. &thorn;at seuen awergede gostes ware on hire &yogh;eherbere&yogh;ede. &ETH;a iherde hie seggen &thorn;at ure drihte on his larspelle sede. &thorn;at alle men sholden dea&eth; &thorn;olien. and an domes dai eft arisen of dea&eth;e and &thorn;o &thorn;e hadden here sinnes forleten and bet; o&eth;er &thorn;ar-on biuonge are hie here lif forleten. hie sholden faren to heuene. and mid ure drihten eche lif habben and blisse. and &thorn;o swo ne duden hie sholden &thorn;olien mid deflen eche pine. on helle. &ETH;a bi&eth;ohte heo on hire liflode and &yogh;e-cnew &thorn;at hie was la&eth; gode. and ladlich amang manne. and &thorn;aruore hire sinne hire bicome swi&eth;e la&eth;e and heo &thorn;ohte &thorn;at heo wolde hem forleten. and beten. &thorn;o com ti&eth;inge &thorn;at ure helende was cumen to symones huse. &thorn;a &thorn;ohte hie &thorn;at hie hine 
<PB REF="00000173.tif" N="145"> &yogh;eseche wolde and him lac bringe. and milce bidden. and nam ane box &yogh;emaked of marbelstone and hine fulde mid derewur&eth;e smerieles. and cam &thorn;ar he was and his holi fet &yogh;esohte. and sore hire sinne biwiep &thorn;at hie his fet lauede mid hire hote teres. and wipede hes &thorn;er after mid hire faire here and mid hire mu&eth;e custe. and &thorn;arafter smerede. &thorn;a war&eth; &thorn;at hus <MILESTONE N="104" UNIT="p">al ful of &thorn;a swote swote bre&eth;e. Mid swiche dede hie clensede heo seluen of ache synne. <I>Et respiciens dominus eiecit vii demonia. et dixit ei, Mulier dimittuntur tibi peccata tua.</I> &ETH;a biseh ure drihte mildeliche to hire penitence. and &yogh;eseh &thorn;at hie biterliche elche &thorn;are limene on hire seluen &thorn;e hie hadde erur mide iseneged. and hadde reu&eth;e of hire. and drof ut of hire. vij. deoflen &thorn;e ware on hire &yogh;eherbered. and &thorn;us qua&eth;. Wimman &thorn;ine sunnen &thorn;e be&eth; forgiuene. Swo beo us alle ure. <I>Eo dimittente. Qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. Amen</I>.</P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="25" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXV. DE SANCTO IACOBO.</HEAD>
<P><I>Evntes ibant et flebant mittentes semina sua. Venientes autem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. cxxvi. 6.]</NOTE> <I>uenient cum exultatione portantes manipulos suos</I>. &ETH;e holi prophete dauid &thorn;e was king of ierusalem fele hundred wintre er ure drihten man bicome and were boren of &thorn;e holi maiden ure lafdi seinte Marie. he hadde wuniende on him &thorn;e holi gost &thorn;e him dide suterliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> to understonden &thorn;at ure drihten wolde man bicumen. and ware. and wanne and of wam ben boren. and hware de&eth; &thorn;olien. and wi&eth;inne wiche firste &thorn;ar-after arisen of dea&eth;e. and hwiche wise to heuene stie. and eft to &thorn;e dome cumen. and wet<NOTE PLACE="marg">? &thorn;et.</NOTE> man him sholden on &thorn;is woreld abuten wunien. and wich lif leden. and wiche him hersumien. and wich mede &thorn;erto-genes understonden in heuenriche. and speke&eth; of ech &thorn;inge sunderlepes and in &thorn;e salmboc stundmele. and &thorn;e fewe word &thorn;e ich nu for&eth;-tegh he spec&eth; of &thorn;e holie mannen &thorn;e folgeden ure helende lichamlich[e] on eor&eth;e; alse &thorn;e louerd Seint iame was 
<PB REF="00000175.tif" N="147"> dai hit is to dai. and o&eth;re <MILESTONE N="105" UNIT="p">holie apostles. and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Euntes ibant et cetera.</I> Hie hiden wepende and sewende. and shule cumen mid blisse and mowen. he spec of &thorn;at &thorn;e sholde wur&eth;e alse &thorn;ehg hit wur&eth;en were. For &thorn;at he wiste siker &thorn;at hit wur&eth;en solde. <I>Set quo euntes; in mortem.</I> Ac wider &yogh;eden hie; fro wureld wele to lichamliche wowe. fro reste to swinche. fro hele; to unhele. fro guwe&eth;e to helde. and on &thorn;is reuliche wei hie weren walkinde forte &thorn;at hie comen to &thorn;e lichamliche dea&eth;e. <I>Quas lacrimas fundentes; tum compunctionis. tum passionis; tum peregrinacionis. tum contemplacionis.</I> Swiche teares shedden<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> shen|den.</NOTE> hie on &thorn;is reuliche wei; erest of reu&eth;e of here agene sinnes. &thorn;o &thorn;e hie erest understoden &thorn;at hie sineged hadden and &thorn;at sore bi-wiepen. and forsoken &thorn;e wereld. and eor&eth;liche wele. and turnden mid alle to ure helende. and mid wosi&eth;es betten here sinnes. and &thorn;erof milce beden. <I>Talibus lacrimis lauit Maria Magdalena pedes domini.</I> Mid swiche teres lauede ure lafdi Seinte Marie magdalene ure helendes fet. and wer&eth; hire seluen laued. and was clene. of hire fule synnes. <I>His etiam lacrimis lauit petrus maculam trine negacionis</I>. Mid swiche teares lauede Seint peter &thorn;e hore of &thorn;e fule sinne. of ure helendes andseche <I>Qvando exiuit et fleuit amare</I> &ETH;o he him understod hwu he syneged hedde<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> hadde.</NOTE>. and hit him sore reu. and he hit mid bitere teares biwiep. and mid &thorn;at wope wer&eth; clensed of &thorn;e synne. <I>INterdum autem uidentes aliquos affligi fuderunt lacrimas compassionis.</I> O&eth;erwile wanne hie segen men wanred &thorn;olien. o&eth;er on sinne <MILESTONE N="106" UNIT="p">bifallen. o&eth;er mid sorinesse bistonden. &thorn;er-of hie hadden reu&eth;e; and sore hit bi-wipen. <I>Has lacrimas dominus fudit quando lazarum suscitauit</I>. Swiche teares wep ure drihten seluen. &thorn;o &thorn;e he sah martha and marie Magdalene &thorn;o two sustres wepen for here bro&eth;res dea&eth;. and he him bed risen of his birieles. and he swo dide. and hem was sta&eth;ed wop. and turnden here wop to blisse. <I>Item dominus uidens ciuitatem fleuit super illam.</I> At o&eth;er time ure helende biheold ierusalemes bureh. and wiste alse he alle &thorn;ing wot. &thorn;at it sholde sone &thorn;ar after ben astruid. and swo was. and &thorn;erfore of his holie egen; hote teares. and minede swo us alle. and gaf 
<PB REF="00000177.tif" N="149"> forbisne of him seluen. &thorn;at we sholden biwepen ure elch o&eth;res sinne. and wosi&eth;es. and forlete lahtres. and idele songes. Swich wop is fremful to wassende mide sinnes. <I>Plerumque etiam tetido</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">? tedio.</NOTE> <I>uite presentis affecti. fudere lacrimas peregri|nationis.</I> and o&eth;er hwile &thorn;e holie men shedden here teares for lif of &thorn;is worelde for &thorn;at hem &thorn;uhte &thorn;at tis arme lif hem<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>After</I> hem <I>read</I> to longe.</NOTE> lastede. <I>Tales lacrimas fudit iob quando dicebat. Tedet anima mea uite mee</I>. wuo is mi soule &thorn;at ich bide here swo longe. Swiche teares shedde &thorn;e holie prophete. &thorn;o &thorn;e he &thorn;ese word sede. <I>Heu</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. cxix. 5.]</NOTE> <I>michi quia incolatus meus prolongatus est</I> wumme &thorn;at ich shal wunien on uncu&eth;e erde. and &thorn;at min biwist is teged here swo longe. <I>Hoc autem dixit quia non habemus hic manentem ciui|tatem. sed in celis debet esse conuersacio nostra.</I> &ETH;et seide &thorn;e holi man for &thorn;at we ben here alle on fleme. Ac ure erd is on heuene<MILESTONE N="107" UNIT="p">; gif we &thorn;ar-after auele&eth;. <I>Iustus autem cum languet desiderio patrie celestis quando fudit lacrimas contemplacionis.</I> &ETH;e riht-wise man &thorn;e mid his heorte and mid his egen bihalt into heuene. and seo&eth; &thorn;e endelese blisse. &thorn;e alle godfruhte men ben to clepede. and<NOTE PLACE="foot">Instead of 'and turne&eth; &thorn;enne . . . . . teres' the Lambeth MS. reads 'him wile sone longe &thorn;iderward and hwenne he ne mei &thorn;ider cume alse ra&eth;e se he walde; he send &thorn;ider his hate teres.' For <I>le&eth;ien</I> we ought, I think, to read <I>le&eth;en</I> (= <I>le&ocirc;&eth;an, l&icirc;&eth;an</I>), to travel, go. The translation then would run thus:&mdash;And when he greatly longeth, and he himself is unable to go [there], &amp;c. See Old English Homilies, First Series, p. 157.</NOTE> turne&eth; &thorn;enne his luue &thorn;erto. him wile sone longe &thorn;ar after. and &thorn;enne him swi&eth;e longe&eth; &thorn;ider. him seluen le&eth;ien ne mai. he sent his &thorn;oht; and his to-hope mid his hote teares. <I>Has lacrimas fudit sponsa sponso. quando dicebat. Tra[h]e me post te</I>. Swiche teares wiep &thorn;e holie spuse uppen hire spus. &thorn;o &thorn;e hie seide lauerd drah me after &thorn;e. for ich ne mai cumen to &thorn;e bute &thorn;u me helpe. <I>Vtrasque lacrimas. scilicet peregrinacionis. et contemplacionis. fudit apostolus fortassem cum dicebat. Cvpio dissolui et esse cum christo.</I> lo&eth; is me &thorn;is. Ei&eth;er &thorn;ese teares shedde ich wene &thorn;e holie apostel &thorn;o &thorn;e he seide. <I>Cvpio dissolui. et cetera</I>. Lo&eth; is me &thorn;is eor&eth;liche lif. and me longe&eth; to criste. He. iiij.<SUP>or</SUP> <I>lacrime. sunt. iiij.</I><SUP>or</SUP> <I>aque. de quibus lauari iubemur. per ysayam dicenttem. Lauamini mundi estote.</I> &ETH;es fower 
<PB REF="00000179.tif" N="151"> kinnes teares. &thorn;e ich haue here seid. ben &thorn;e fower wateres &thorn;e we shulen us one wasshen. alse ure drihten us bad. bi ysayas &thorn;e prophete &thorn;us que&eth;inde. wasshe&eth; giu; and wunie&eth; clene. <I>Lacrima autem compunc[t]ionis; amara ut aqua maris</I> &ETH;e wop &thorn;e man wepe&eth; for his agene sinne is swi&eth;e biter alse saltwater. and &thorn;ere-fore is nemmed se water. <I>Lacrima com|passionis est tepida sicut aqua niuis. que defluit ad calorem</I> <MILESTONE N="108" UNIT="p"><I>solis</I>. &ETH;e wop &thorn;e man wepe&eth; for his emcristenes wowe. cume&eth; of &thorn;e wlache heorte. alse &thorn;e sunne hete &thorn;e snow. &thorn;at he hit for-melte&eth; to watere. <I>Lacrima quidem peregrinacionis com|paratur aqua fontis. quia sicut hec ebullit de terra sic illa de cordis angustia</I>. &THORN;e teares &thorn;e man wepe&eth;. for &thorn;at him wo be&eth;. &thorn;at he wunie shal on lo&eth;e erde; ben nemmed welle water. for &thorn;at hie walle&eth; of &thorn;e heorte rotes; swo water do&eth; of welle. <I>Lacrime uero contemplacionis comparantur aqua roris. quia sicut illa nutu dei curritur ab imo in altum; ita ille emanant propter alti desiderium.</I> &THORN;e teares &thorn;e man wepe&eth; for longenge to heuene ben cleped rein water. o&eth;er deu water. for &thorn;at alse &thorn;e sunne te&eth; water fram eor&eth;e up to &thorn;e wolcne; and &thorn;er-offe cume&eth; reines. swo &thorn;e holi gost te&eth; &thorn;e mannes luue to heuene. and make&eth; &thorn;at him longed swi&eth;e &thorn;ider. and for &thorn;at longenge wasse&eth; his neb mid teares. &ETH;ese fower kinne teares wiep ure louerd Seint Iame. and on &thorn;ese fower wateres wuesh him seluen of sinnes. and siew &thorn;o on wowe; &thorn;at he shal eft on blisse mowen. <I>Que sunt semina; Qui manipuli; Uerba ueritatis. Opera caritatis</I>. &thorn;e sed &thorn;at he sew were so&eth;e wordes. and mild heorte dedes. &thorn;e blostmes &thorn;e shal eft mowen; ben. <I>Lux perpetua. Salus eterna. Letitia sempiterna.</I> &thorn;at is ilestende liht. and endelese hele. and eche blisse mid angles in heueneriche. folge we nu&thorn;e &thorn;e louerd Seint iames faire forbisne. and gon mid ure heorte. and mid ure fote ut of unbileue. in to rihte bileue. and of gode in to betere. and swo<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS.;? read</I> sowen.</NOTE> <MILESTONE N="109" UNIT="p">e&eth;ele word. and edie deden. and wepen &thorn;o fuwer kinne teares. and of &thorn;e fower wateres &thorn;e ich er embe spec; wassen us clene of ure sinnes. and hauen on us &thorn;at his name bitocne&eth;. <I>Iacobus interpretatur supplantator uiciorum.</I> Iacob on boc leden is icleped on englisse under-plantere of fule 
<PB REF="00000181.tif" N="153"> custumes. <I>et merito. supplantauit enim uicia; bene uiuendo. in se docendo bene uiuere; in aliis.</I> and rithliche<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS. Read</I> rihtlice.</NOTE> he was cleped iacob; for he under-plantede fule custumes. of him seluen; mid his clenliche liflode. Swo we agen alle to don. bo&eth;e lerede. and lewede. and mid faire lore understonden godes word. <I>Quod nobis prestet. qui secula per omnia Regnat. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="26" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXVI. DE SANCTO <I>LAURENTIO</I>.</HEAD>
<P><I>Qvi parce seminat parce et metet. et quia seminat in benedic|tionibus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[2 Cor. ix. 6.]</NOTE> <I>d. [b.] et Metet.</I> Ure louerd seinte poul hegest alre lor&thorn;ew after ure helende seluen spec&eth; on &thorn;e holi boc. and mine&yogh;e&eth; ei&eth;er hodede. and lewede to godes wordes and to weldede. <I>Specialiter quidem monens nos. ut ait gregorius ad sancte predicationis officium. Generaliter uero hos</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Originally</I> hos, <I>but the top of the</I> h <I>has been erased and it looks like</I> n.</NOTE>. <I>et illos ad salutarem obedienciam mandatorum.</I> Hodede he mine&yogh;e&eth; wel to lerende [lewede] hodede. and lewede feir and clene lif to leden and sei&eth; &thorn;at ech man shal understonden mede of his er dede. and efter &thorn;at &thorn;e he me&eth;ege&eth; nu his dede. shal eft ben me&eth;eged his mede. and &thorn;us que&eth;. Qui <I>parce seminat. parce</I>. &thorn;e man &thorn;e litel sowe&eth;; he shal litel mowen. and he &thorn;e sowe&eth; on blescinge he shal eft mowen on blescinge. &thorn;at is to seien &thorn;e man &thorn;e wel do&eth;; he wel underfo&eth;. <I>Sacra scriptura nomine semen is</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> seminis.</NOTE> <I>appellat. tria scilicet hominis progenituram dei uerbum. opus bonum.</I> holi boc nemne&eth; iwunelich &thorn;re &thorn;ing to sed. on is mannes stren. &thorn;at o&eth;er is <MILESTONE N="110" UNIT="p">godes word. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is wel dede Ure helende clepede mannes streon sed. &thorn;o he spac wi&eth; &thorn;e holi man abraham; of his strene. and seide &thorn;at swo michel mankin sholde springen of him. &thorn;at no man hit ne mihte tellen. nan more &thorn;ene men mugen tellen &thorn;e sterres<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> strerres.</NOTE> on heuene. and &thorn;us seide. <I>Suspice celum et numera stellas si potes. sic erit semen tuum.</I> Bi-hold up to heuene qua&eth; he and tel &thorn;e sterres<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> strerres.</NOTE> &yogh;if &thorn;u miht; for swich shal ben &thorn;in of spri[n]g <I>Set aduertendum est quod prudens sator obseruat. et glebe aptitudinem. et temporis oportunitatem</I>. Ac alse &thorn;e wise 
<PB REF="00000183.tif" N="155"> tilie nime&eth; &yogh;eme of two &thorn;ing &thorn;anne he sed sowe&eth;. On is we&eth;er &thorn;e eor&eth;e beo bicumeliche to &thorn;e sede. &thorn;at o&eth;er we&eth;er hit beo riht time &thorn;er to. Alse [ahte] ech criste man to don wapman. and wim|man &thorn;anne hie wilen tulien after strene. hie o&yogh;en to nime michel geme. &thorn;at hie it on<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> don on bicumeliche stede.</NOTE> stede and on rihte time Nis nefre no stede to strene bicumeliche bute hie ben bispused rihtliche to-gedere. ne hure riht time &thorn;enne men fasten shal; o&eth;er halgen. Godes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> Goges.</NOTE> word is ec sed cleped on &thorn;e faire forbisne &thorn;e ure helende seide to his apostles. &thorn;us que&eth;inde <I>Exiit qui seminat. et cetera.</I> on tilie ferde ut and sew. and sum of &thorn;e sed ful uppe &thorn;e ston. and dride &thorn;ere. and sum ful among &thorn;ornes. and forwar&eth;, and sum fel bi &thorn;e wei; and was fortreden. and fugeles it freten. and sum ful on &thorn;e gode eor&eth;e. and &thorn;at com wel for&eth;. &ETH;o beden &thorn;e holi apostles seien hem wat &thorn;e sowere bitocne&eth;. and he seide &thorn;us. <I>Semen est uerbum dei. Sator autem Christuc. omnis autem qui audit eum manebit in eternum.</I> Godes word<MILESTONE N="111" UNIT="p"> is &thorn;at sed. and crist seluen &thorn;e sowere. and he &thorn;e luueliche hliste&eth; godes lore he shal hauen eche lif on blisse. <I>Set hoc semen aliquando spargit[ur] tum ore proprio. tum ore ministrorum.</I> Ac ure helend sawe&eth; his holie word hwile &thorn;urh his hagen mu&eth; hwile &thorn;urh his apostles. and o&eth;re lor&eth;eawes &thorn;e cunnen holie boc-lore. and &thorn;ermide godes folc lere&eth;. A swiche wise spec&eth; &thorn;e heuenliche king wi&eth; ech man &thorn;e he to sende&eth; his writ. <I>In hac etiam sacione obserua agri competenciam et congruenciam.</I> and &thorn;anne folkes lor&thorn;eawes his sed sowe&eth; he oh to nime michel &yogh;eme &thorn;at he hit sowe on bicumeliche eor&eth;e. and on rihte time. &thorn;ere mennes heortes hliste&eth; luueliche godes lore &thorn;ere me of gode spec&eth;. and &thorn;ere me god wur&eth;e&eth;. &thorn;o ben bicumeliche eor&eth;e godes word on to sowende ac &thorn;o &thorn;e luue&eth; sinne and forleten nelle&eth;. o&eth;er bileued ne haue&eth;. ne understonden godes word noht ben unbicumeliche eor&eth;e to &thorn;e sede of godes wordes. Ech sunedai. and o&eth;er hegh dai is riht time to sowen &thorn;e holie sed; &thorn;at is godes word. and in chirche &thorn;er al chirche folc ohg to ben gadered. <I>Bonum opus etiam nomine semen is appelatur. tum quia seritur in futuro metetur. tum quia more frugum multiplicabitur.</I> Wel dede is cleped ec sed. for two &thorn;ing. on is. &thorn;at alse me sowe&eth; on an time. 
<PB REF="00000185.tif" N="157"> and gadere&eth; &thorn;e blostmes eft on o&eth;er. Alse man do&eth; nu his wel dede. and on &thorn;at o&eth;er woreld shal understonden eche lif; and blisse. O&eth;er is &thorn;at [alse of on sede cume&eth; fele-felde westme] alse of on e&eth;eliche dede man shal understonden fele-felde. and michele mede <I>Multa quidem sunt genera bonorum operum</I> <MILESTONE N="112" UNIT="p"><I>Set hic agitur de uno eorum. scilicet de largicione elemosinarum. unde p[ro]phetam inducit dicentem. Dispersit dedit pauperibus et cetera.</I> Fele kinne weldede ben. ac &thorn;e holie apostel mune&yogh;e&eth; here to on of hem. &thorn;at is almes-delen. and sei&eth; &thorn;at me hit shal giuen hauenlese men. and noht al on. Ac alse &thorn;e holie salmwrihte dauid sei&eth;. dele hit swo &thorn;at ech nedi &thorn;e hit biseke&eth; haue sum &thorn;ing &thorn;er-of [swo he do&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">In fainter ink above the line.</NOTE>] &yogh;if he wis beo&eth; &thorn;e hit dele&eth;. alle wel dede be&eth; fremfulle to sinbote. ac non fremefuler &thorn;anne almes-deled<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> delen.</NOTE>. <I>Quia sicut aqua extinguit ignem; ita elemosina extinguit peccatum.</I> for alse water quenche&eth; fur; alse almes quenche&eth; sinne. and &yogh;if man selle&eth; &thorn;e almes; &thorn;enne for-lest heo hire name. and hire mihte. <I>Quatuor modis uenditur elemosina et tunc inde. aut populi fauor emitur. aut pudoris molestia redi|mitur. aut recompensacio rei temporalis adquiritur. aut debitum</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">Originally debiti.</NOTE> <I>beneficii seculo</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> so|lucio.</NOTE> <I>inpenditur.</I> On fuwer wise man sulle&eth; his almes. on. is. &thorn;enne he bih&eth; &thorn;er mide here word. <I>Et hoc animi morbo laborat fere omnis homo.</I> and &thorn;is custume haue&eth; mestwat alle men. For &thorn;at welnehg ech man &yogh;ife&eth; his almesse ei&eth;er for godes luue. and for hauende hereword. and for to ben wur&eth;ed fer and ner; &thorn;e &thorn;e he cnowen is. On o&eth;er wise man sille&eth; his almes &thorn;anne he it &yogh;ife&eth; swiche men &thorn;e he wernen ne mai for he his neghebore beo&eth;. o&eth;er elles frend. and &thorn;ermide lese&eth; him ut of shame &thorn;e he hauen sholde &yogh;if he him ne &yogh;eue. On &thorn;e &thorn;ridde wise man selle&eth; his almesse. &thorn;enne he &yogh;ife&eth; swiche men. &thorn;e him do&eth;. o&eth;er don haue&eth;. wike and cher. o&eth;er don shal. and &thorn;enche&eth; &thorn;is mannes wile boht mid <MILESTONE N="113" UNIT="p">&thorn;e almesse. On &thorn;e feor&eth;e wise man sille&eth; his almes &thorn;enne he &yogh;ife&eth; swiche men &thorn;e he a&yogh;hte mid rihte to helpe; to feden. and to shruden. Alse &thorn;e man do&eth;. &thorn;e &yogh;ife&eth; his almes fader. o&eth;er moder. suster. o&eth;er bro&eth;er. o&eth;er o&eth;re swo sibbe; &thorn;at he aghte mid rihte to helpen to feden. 
<PB REF="00000187.tif" N="159"> and to shruden. and al &thorn;at man do&eth; for sunderlepes to quemen gode. alle hie quenche&eth; sinne. and &thorn;inge&eth; &thorn;e sinbetinde to ure drihten. and al &thorn;at man do&eth; on o&eth;re wise and for o&eth;re &thorn;inge &thorn;ehg hie ben don ec for godes luue. na&eth;eles hie hit sellen. and here understonden &thorn;er-of mede and nefre eft non. alse ure helende sei&eth; on &thorn;e godspelle. <I>Amen dico uobis receperunt mercedem suam.</I> To so&eth;e ich giu seie &thorn;at &thorn;o &thorn;e don here weldede for to hauen mede on &thorn;is liue ne shulen hie hauen no mede on &thorn;at o&eth;er woreld. Ac al &thorn;at man do&eth; sunderlepes for godes luue. he shal hauen eche lif on blisse. and his mede shal ben &thorn;anne garked; alse hit beo&eth; here aueled. alse ure drihten sei&eth; on &thorn;e godspelle. <I>Eadem m&edot;nsura qua mensi fueritis remicietur uobis.</I> Bi &thorn;at ilke met &thorn;e &yogh;e mete&eth; nu &yogh;iwer weldede; shal ben meten &yogh;iwer mede. &thorn;is seide &thorn;e holie apostel. alse ich er seide. <I>Qui parce seminat. parcet et metet.</I> Ech man sal eft mowen bi &thorn;an &thorn;e he nu sowe&eth;. and he &thorn;e sowe&eth; on bles|cinge. he shal eft mowen on blescinge. and &thorn;at is ech man &thorn;e luueliche lh[i]ste&eth; godes lore. and bi alle here mihte almes delen. and auelen &thorn;at men hem blescen. and for hem bidden and ure louerd iesu crist for here bene giue hem his blescinge. &thorn;at is echeliche erding. and blisse on heuene. <I>Quod nobis prestet qui secula per omnia Regnat. AMEN.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="27" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXVII. (ASSUMPTIO S. MARIE VIRGINIS.)</HEAD>
<P><I>MARia uirgo assumpta est ad ethereum thalamum. et cetera</I><MILESTONE N="114" UNIT="p">. On of &thorn;e holie writes &thorn;e ben red herinne to dai bringen us blisfulle ti&eth;inges. of an edie meiden. &thorn;e was iferen bispused &thorn;e heuenliche kinge. and sei&eth; &thorn;at he hes fette hom. Luste&eth; nu wich maiden &thorn;at is. and hwat he hatte. and hware he was fet. and hwo hire ledde. and wu. and hwider. and cunnen &yogh;if we mu&yogh;en cumen after. for &thorn;an &thorn;e we ben alle boden &thorn;ider. Of &thorn;is maiden spec&eth; &thorn;e holie boc; and sei&eth;. Hec est <I>regina</I> uirginum. <I>Regina</I> celorum. Domina engelorum. Mater et <I>filia regis</I> regum omnium. &ETH;is maiden bar ure louerd ihesu crist ure alre fader; of hire holie lichame. and nis hire mai&eth;hod &thorn;ere fore noht a|wemmed. 
<PB REF="00000189.tif" N="161"> hie is &thorn;e heuenliches kinges dohter and ec his moder. and alre maidene maide. and heuene quen. and englene lafdi<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. lasdi.</NOTE>. hire is to name maria <I>quod est interpretatum stella maris</I> &ETH;at is on englis s&aelig; sterre. &ETH;an &thorn;e safarinde men se&eth; &thorn;e sa sterre. hie wuten sone wuderward hie sullen weie holden. for &thorn;at &thorn;e storres liht is hem god lat&eth;&aelig;u. <I>Mundus mari comparabitur quia fluctus erigit. naues obruit. Ita mundus effluit; dum opes confert. refluit; dum aufert. turbine. i[d est] ultione diuina. vel fraude diabolica turbatur. Discordiarum motus concitat. ecclesiarum pacem perturbat.</I> &ETH;is woreld is cleped s&aelig;. &thorn;e flowe&eth; and ebbe&eth;. swo do&eth; ec &thorn;is woreld flowe&eth;. &thorn;anne he woreld-wunne &yogh;ieue&eth;. and ebbe&eth;; &thorn;anne hie hit eft binime&eth;. Storemes falle&eth; in &thorn;e s&aelig;. and to-worpe&eth; hit. and godes wrake cume&eth; on &thorn;is woreld to wrekende on sunfulle men here gultes. and for&thorn;&aelig;n <MILESTONE N="115" UNIT="p">onrih[t]wise men &thorn;e hem neih wunien. and binime&eth; hem hwile oref. hwile o&eth;er aihte. and hwile here hele. and hwile here ogen lif. and hwile lat te deuel hem on fele wise. and hareme&eth; hem. and shende&eth;. and wecche&eth; among hem flite. and win. and fordraue&eth; so&eth; luue. and struie&eth; rihte bileue. And alse &thorn;e sa storre shat of hire &thorn;e liht. &thorn;e lihte&eth; sa farinde men. alse &thorn;is edie maiden seinte marie. of hire holie licame shede&eth; &thorn;at so&eth;e liht. &thorn;e lihte&eth; alle brihte &thorn;inges on eor&eth;e. and ec on heuene. alse Seint Iohannes sai&eth; on his godspel. <I>Erat lux uera que. illuminat omnem hominem uenientem in hunc mundum.</I> He is &thorn;at so&eth;e liht. &thorn;e lihted alle men. &thorn;e on &thorn;is woreld cume&eth;. and aleomed ben. And for &thorn;is leome is &thorn;at holie maiden cleped sa sterre. Hie was fet of weste wunienge &thorn;ar he funden was. <I>scilicet in terra deserta in loco [h]orr[or]is et uaste solitudinis.</I> &ETH;at is to seien on weste londe. and on grisliche stede. Weste is cleped &thorn;at londe &thorn;at is longe til&eth;e atleien. and wildernesse ges<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> gef.</NOTE> &thorn;are manie rotes onne wacse&eth;. &ETH;is woreldes biwest is efned to wastene; for &thorn;at &thorn;e hit is ferren atleien holie til&eth;e. <I>Hinc ex quo ueteres emigra|uere coloni.</I> Aure se&eth;&eth;en &thorn;e ealde tilie henne wenden. &ETH;e hwile &thorn;e hie here waren. hie wenden &thorn;e eor&eth;e; and wurpen god sad &thorn;aronne. and hit wacxs. and wel &thorn;eagh. and brahte for&eth; blostmes fele and manie. Ac se&eth;en hie henen wenden; atlai &thorn;at lond 
<PB REF="00000191.tif" N="163"> unwend. and bicam waste. and was roted oueral. and swo bicam wildernesse. Nu wunie&eth; &thorn;ar inne fueles. and wilde deor. and wurmes. &ETH;is lond &thorn;e ich nu of speke. <MILESTONE N="116" UNIT="p">is &thorn;at mennisse &thorn;e nu liue&eth;. &ETH;e olde tilien waren &thorn;e holie lor&eth;ewes. prophetes. apostles. popes archebissopes. bissopes. prestes. &thorn;e holie lif ladden. &ETH;e tilien wenden &thorn;is lond &thorn;at up; &thorn;at was ar dun. &thorn;anne hie mid here wise word turneden mannes herte fram eor&eth;eliche &thorn;ankes. to heuenliche &thorn;anke. fram unrihte to rihte. fram hordom to clennesse. fram alle iuele lastes to luuien gode. and heren him. And after &thorn;at sewen on &thorn;is lond godes word for sede. and hit morede on here heorte. and weacs. and wel &thorn;ea&yogh;h. &thorn;anne &thorn;at folc godes word &yogh;ierneliche listede. and fastliche hield. and ter after here lif ladden. Ac nu is &thorn;at lond til&eth;e atlein. and ifuren was. for &thorn;o &thorn;it<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>i.e.</I> &thorn;e hit.</NOTE> sholden tilien. &ETH;o &thorn;e lor&eth;ewes of holie chireche. &thorn;e sewen &yogh;erneluker &thorn;e defles sed; &thorn;an ure louerdes ihesu crist. and mid forbisne of here fule liflode. beden men te helle and naht to heuene. Godes sed; is godes word. &thorn;e men tilien in chireche. on salmes. and on songes. and on redinges and lorspelles. and on holde bedes; &thorn;e lerde men selde and gemelesliche sowen. &ETH;e defles sed; is idel. and unnet. and iuele word. hoker. and scorn. spel. and leo&eth;. cheast. and twispeche. and curs. and leasinges. and sware. and alle swikele speches. And o&eth;re fele lerdemen speken; alse lewede. alse ure drihten seide &thorn;urh anes prophetes mu&eth;e. <I>Erit sicut populus sacerdos.</I> Prest sal leden his lif alse lewede m&aelig;n. and swo hie do&eth; nu&eth;e; and sumdel werse. For &thorn;e lewede man wur&eth;e&eth; his spuse mid clo&eth;es more &thorn;ane mid him seluen. and prest naht sis<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>i.e.</I> swo his.</NOTE> chireche &thorn;e is his spuse; ac his daie &thorn;e is his hore. awlenc&eth; hire mid <MILESTONE N="117" UNIT="p">clo&eth;es. more &thorn;an him seluen. &ETH;e chire[che] clo&eth;es ben to brokene; and ealde. and hise wiues shule ben hole; and newe. His alter clo&eth; great and sole; and hire chemise smal. and hwit. and te albe sol; and hire smoc hwit. &thorn;e haued line sward; and hire winpel wit. o&eth;er maked geleu mid saffran. &ETH;e meshakele of medeme fustane<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>The</I> e <I>is imperfect, and looks like</I> i.</NOTE>. and hire mentel grene o&eth;er burnet. &ETH;e corporeals sole; and unshapliche. hire handclo&eth;es. and hire bord clo&eth;es makede wite. and lustliche on to siene. &ETH;e caliz of tin; and hire nap of mazere. and ring of golde. 
<PB REF="00000193.tif" N="165"> And is &thorn;e prest swo muchele forcu&eth;ere. &thorn;ane &thorn;e lewede. Swo he wur&eth;e&eth; his hore more &thorn;an his spuse. Prestes ben &thorn;o. &thorn;e apostel of spec&eth;. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Quorum deus uenter est.</I> Here wombe is here crist. and alle iuele forbisne hie ippen of hem seluen. and te lewede men hem &yogh;ierneliche folegen. and te&eth; for&eth; geres after wilde deore. Sume after beore. sume after wulue. sume after o&eth;er deor. And alse &thorn;e fugeles fram &oacute; stede to o&eth;er. and ne ben nafre stedefaste. swo do&eth; &thorn;is mannisse flie&eth; fram iuele to werse. on speche. and on dede. and bringe&eth; on here heorte oregel. and wra&eth;e and onde. and hatinge. and o&eth;er iuele lastes. alse wuremes breden on wilderne &thorn;at is &thorn;is woreld. &thorn;is grisliche stede on to wunien. For here is hunger. and &thorn;urst. elde. unhale. flit. and win. eche. and smertinge. sorinesse. werinesse. and o&eth;re wowe muchel. Of swilch mai grisen men &thorn;e ani god cunnen. Eft sone on &thorn;is biwiste is muchel weste of holie mihte. Al riht is leid; and wogh <MILESTONE N="118" UNIT="p">arered alse &thorn;e wise que&eth;. <I>Nusquam tuta fides non hospes ab hospite tutus</I>. Nis nower non trew&eth;e. for nis &thorn;e gist siker of &thorn;e husebonde; ne no&eth;er of o&eth;er. <I>Non socer &aacute; nuro Ne &thorn;e aldefader of hi[s] o&eth;em. Fratrumque gratia rara est</I>. Selde leue&eth; &thorn;e bro&eth;er &thorn;at o&eth;er. <I>Filius ante diem ante diem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <I>patrinos inquirit annos</I>. &ETH;e sune wusshe&eth; &thorn;e fader dea&eth;, ar his dai cume. [I]mminet <I>exicio uir coniugis. illa mariti</I>. Wif wolde &thorn;at hire louerd dead ware. and he &thorn;at hie ware. Of &thorn;esse waste and grisliche stede was &thorn;is holi maide fet &thorn;e ich of speke. &thorn;at is ure lafdi seinte marie. and hire fette &thorn;e heuenliche king. alse &thorn;e prophete sei&eth; on his stefne. <I>Tenuisti manum dexteram meam. et cetera.</I> &ETH;u helde mi riht hond. and leddest me on &thorn;ine wille and understode me mid wurdshipe. <I>Ter ascendit. primo quidem passibus corporis ante templum ab imo quindecim graduum. usque ad summum. Secundo in templo passibus mentibus</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> mentis.</NOTE> <I>de uirtute in uirtutem. ubi uidetur deus deorum in syon. Tercio corpore. et anima assumpta in celum.</I> &THORN;reo si&eth;es ste&yogh;h &thorn;is holie maiden. erest lichamliche &thorn;o hie was &thorn;reo &yogh;ier heold. biforen &thorn;e temple on &thorn;e steire of fiftene stoples. fro ne&thorn;ewarde to uuewarde. wi&eth;ute mannes helpe. O&eth;er si&eth;es<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS</NOTE> hie steh&yogh; in &thorn;e temple gostliche. fram mihte to mihte forte 
<PB REF="00000195.tif" N="167"> &thorn;at hie alre mihtene louerd biheold alse hie hit wolde. &ETH;e &thorn;ridde si&eth;e hie steh&yogh; &thorn;is dai &thorn;o engles hire beren mid soule and mid lichame. in to &thorn;an heuenliche bure; &thorn;ar heo was wur&eth;liche <MILESTONE N="119" UNIT="p">understonden. and salomon &thorn;e wise &thorn;e wes fele hundred wintre &thorn;er bifore king in ierusalem seh&yogh; &thorn;ese wunderliche stienge. alse suterliche alse he &thorn;is dai were. and wundrede &thorn;er offe; and seide. <I>Que est ista que ascendit sicut aurora consurgens pulcra ut luna electa ut sol</I>. Hwat is &thorn;is &thorn;e astih&yogh;&eth; alse dai rieme. fair alse mone. icoren alse sunne. Vre lafdi Seinte Marie. alse wisliche alse hie &thorn;is dai was houen in to heuene. bere ure arende to ure louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;at he &yogh;ife us eche blisse on heuene. <I>Quod ipse prestare dignetur qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="28" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXVIII. DE DEFUNCTIS.</HEAD>
<P><I>Libera me domine de morte eterna in die illa tremenda, quando celi movendi sunt et terra. dum veneris judicare seculum per ignem. [D]ies illa, dies ire. calamitatis et miseri&aelig;, dies magna et amara valde.</I> &ETH;e lif holi man iob &thorn;e &thorn;e boc of spec&eth;. and sei&eth;. <I>Erat uir ille simplex et iustus. et timens deum. ac re|cedens &aacute; malo</I>. he was admod on worde. and rihtwis on dede. and godfruht on &thorn;onke. and lo&eth;les mid alle. and &thorn;erefore likede ure drihten swo wel &thorn;at he herede him ouer alle men; and seide. <I>Non est similis in terra</I>. Nis on eor&eth;e non o&eth;er his liche. &thorn;is holi man hadde &thorn;re biwistes&middot; &thorn;e forme was on michel woreld wele. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Perdidit omnem substanciam eius. filios. et filias. Caro quoque eius graui uulnere uulnerata est.</I> and ure drihten &thorn;e him swo michel luuede &yogh;af leue &thorn;e deuel to b&iacute;nimende him his oref. and his ahte. and his children. alle. and alle &thorn;e woreld winne &thorn;e he weald hadde. and &thorn;e deuel swo dide. and after &thorn;an toc his o&yogh;en lichame. <MILESTONE N="120" UNIT="p">and &thorn;er one brohte swo michel sicnesse &thorn;ureh his &thorn;re creftes. &thorn;at te lichame war&eth; bretful of wunden. and at eche wunde wul ut atter. &THORN;o ne mihte no man for stenche cumen him enden. ne his wif nolde. &thorn;e he hadde swo swi&eth;e wur&eth;ed. ac 
<PB REF="00000197.tif" N="169"> mest manne him gremede mid scorne. &ETH;e &thorn;ridde biwist he hadde on swich wele. &thorn;e was bi twifold more; &thorn;ane &thorn;e forme alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Reddidit deus iob omnia dupplicia et melior fuit eius finis principio.</I> vre drihten &yogh;iald twifoldliche iob. &thorn;at &thorn;e deuel him hadde binumen. on guwe&eth;e. and on alle &thorn;e winne &thorn;e he erur wield. and war&eth; blisfuller his ende; &thorn;ene was his biginninge. and on &thorn;e midleste biwist &thorn;e he &thorn;olede &thorn;e gimere pine he makede ane reuliche meninge. and &thorn;er one minegede alle his wrecche si&eth;es. &thorn;e he &thorn;olede on &thorn;is wrecche worelde. o&eth;er in &thorn;at o&eth;er sholde. and an hefde &thorn;o his egen to heuene. and his heorte to gode. and his honden to his breste. and sore sihte. and his heorte biet. and bed godes milce &thorn;us que&eth;<I>inde. Libera me domine et cetera.</I> Ared me louerd of eche dea&eth;e. on &thorn;e grisliche dai. &thorn;e heuene and eor&eth;e shulen quakien. of-dred. &thorn;anne &thorn;u cumest to demen al mankin mid fire. &THORN;us &thorn;e holi man him bad. and &yogh;af alle men forbisne swo to bidden. and alswo ofte swo prest singe&eth; &thorn;is bede at lich huse. he mine&yogh;e&eth; alle &eth;o; &thorn;e &thorn;er ben. hem &thorn;us to bidden. <I>Libera me domine. de morte. et cetera.</I> Ales me louerd of eche dea&eth;e. <I>Tres siquidem mortes sunt scilicet una ut supra</I><MILESTONE N="121" UNIT="p"> <I>scripsi. Vna momentanea. scilicet corporis quando ab eo recedit anima.</I> &ETH;re dea&eth;es be&eth;. on is e&eth;elich &thorn;at &thorn;ole&eth; &thorn;e lichame. &thorn;an &thorn;e sowle turne&eth; fram him. Of dea&eth;e ben alle bileffulle men of-dradde. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Metuentes non metuenda</I>. Hie habbe&eth; [drede] of &thorn;at hie no sholden. <I>Altera diuturna scilicet anime quanda declinat a iusticia.</I> &THORN;at o&eth;er dea&eth; is o&eth;e[r] hwile long. &thorn;at &thorn;ole&eth; &thorn;e soule; &thorn;ane &thorn;e licame senege&eth;. and sundre&eth; hire fram rih[t]wisnesse. ac of &thorn;is dea&eth;e ben alle rihtwise men and godfrihte of-dradde; and non o&eth;re. <I>Tercia corporis et anime simul. quando in ignem eter|num mittentur &aacute; diuina sentencia dicente. Ite maledicti et cetera.</I> &ETH;e &thorn;ridde dea&eth; is eche and endeles. &thorn;at &thorn;ole&eth; man on soule and on licame to gadere. &thorn;ane he be&eth; eft on domes dai &aacute;-risen of dea&eth;e. bute his sunnes him ben ere forgieuene. o&eth;er bette hwane ure drihten &thorn;e is bo&eth;e lif and dea&eth;. driue&eth; him fram him. to pine. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ite maledicti in ignem eternum.</I> Wite&eth; &yogh;ie awariede gostes in to eche fur. Of &thorn;is dea&eth; ben alle men 
<PB REF="00000199.tif" N="171"> ofdradde; &thorn;e on ure drihte bileue&eth;. And Iob witnede ure drihten. &thorn;at of &thorn;is dea&eth; him redde. on &thorn;e carefuldai. &thorn;an he cume&eth; almiddeneard to demen. &ETH;anne shule bo&eth;e quakien ofdradde heuene and er&eth;e. Unbileuede men ben cleped eor&eth;e. and bileffulle men ben heouene nemnede. and hie shule ben unnea&eth; boregen. <I>Tremebunt etiam angeli et archangeli.</I> &ETH;ar shulen engles and archangles quakien ofdradde. <I>Non quia conscientia sua eos accuset. sed quoniam iudicem uidebunt terribilem.</I> Engles wur&eth;en ofdradde. naht for here gultes &thorn;e none ne habbe&eth;. ac for &thorn;at hie shulen cnowen ure demendes wra&eth;&eth;e. bi his <MILESTONE N="122" UNIT="p">grimeliche lete. and bi his eifulle speche. &thorn;an ure drihten cume&eth; to demen alle mankenne. no&eth;er on heuene ne on eor&eth;e. ac bitwien two. on &thorn;e wolcne. Fur cumed biforen him alse &thorn;e prophete seide. <I>Ignis ante ipsum precedet. et inflam|mabit in circuitu inimicos eius.</I> Fur berne&eth; &thorn;e eor&eth;e and al<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. xcvi. 3.]</NOTE> &thorn;at be&eth; &thorn;ar inne. o&eth;er &thorn;ar uppe. and clense&eth; alle bileffule men of alle &thorn;e sunnes &thorn;e hie hadden forleten. o&eth;er bet. o&eth;er bigunnen to beten. and make&eth; hem seuefealde brihtere &thorn;ane &thorn;e sunne alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Fulgebunt iusti septies cplendidius quam sol.</I> &ETH;e riht|wise<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> rihtwile.</NOTE> shulle ben seuefeald brihtere &thorn;ane &thorn;e sunne. and elles naren hie naht bicumeliche to wunien in heuene. Ac &thorn;o unbileffule men &thorn;e bi here quica liue here sunnes ne forleten. ne betten. ne fastliche bote ne biheten. hie bicume&eth; in &thorn;e fure swo bloke. and swo eiseliche. and swo ateliche. &thorn;at bi hundred fealde grisluker &thorn;an ani niht &thorn;eoster. and ben &thorn;anne bicumeliche to wunien in helle mid alle deflen. &thorn;anne wur&eth; alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Deus mani|feste</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. xlix. 3.]</NOTE><I>ueniet</I>. &ETH;anne cume&eth; ure drihten openliche to bihealde alle &thorn;e &thorn;are shulle ben gaderede. <I>Ignis in conspectu eius exar|descet. et in eius. tempestas ualida</I>. And giet &thorn;anne &thorn;at fur berne&eth; biforen him. and storem be&eth; muchel al abuten him. <I>Aduocabit celum desursum et cetera.</I> &ETH;anne wule he clepien &thorn;e heuenliche men. &thorn;o ben &thorn;e lif holie. and to<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> te.</NOTE> eor&eth;eliche men; &thorn;o ben &thorn;e sunfulle. and demen elch man after his erninge. &ETH;o &thorn;e hadden on &thorn;esse liue alle here sunnes for-<MILESTONE N="123" UNIT="p"> leten. and bet. o&eth;er bigunnen to beten. and beden milce; alle he qua&eth; hem saclese; and sent hem to heuene &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Venite benedicti patris</I> 
<PB REF="00000201.tif" N="173"> <I>mei et cetera.</I> Cume&eth; ibledsede and underfo&eth; eche lif and blisse on heuene. Ac alle &thorn;o &thorn;e nabbe&eth; swo idon. he bit here unbette sennes on &thorn;onke. and on speche and on dede cumen biforen hem. and bistonden hem fastliche. and bigraden hem shameliche. and biten hem unradeliche. and hie swo don. and elch sinne &thorn;are him seluen bisei&eth;. bute hit be here forgieue. o&eth;er mid bote iheled. &ETH;anne stonde&eth; &thorn;o wreches alse &thorn;o. &thorn;e wo be&eth;. and loke&eth; up. and dun. and al abuten. and sen buuen hem godes wra&eth;&eth;e. &thorn;e hem fram him driue&eth;. and be&eth; &thorn;ar of swi&eth;e ofdradde. and no wunder nis. Hie ise&eth; bine&eth;en hem deflen &thorn;e hem grede|liche kepe&eth;. and be&eth; swi&eth;e of grisen; and ful ea&eth;e mu&yogh;en. Hie ise&eth; bisides hem swilche &thorn;e hem waren her cu&eth;e. and bie&eth; swi&eth;e of-shamede. of hem. and mid here owen sinnes &thorn;e hem swo biclepie&eth;. and ben sore ofgramede. and wi&eth; hem seluen alre sorest. for &thorn;at hie hadden swo fulliche suneged. &thorn;is be&eth; on &thorn;e daie. &thorn;e &thorn;e boc offe spec&eth;. <I>Dies illa dies ire</I>. On &thorn;e dai cume&eth; godes wra&eth;&eth;e uppen &thorn;e sinfulle. and hie be&eth; unmihti to-genes deflen. and hie be&eth; bine&eth;en hem. and &thorn;olie&eth; fulle wowe in hem. and swilch hem shal leste al &thorn;e endelese dai. &thorn;at is afre abuten ende. and gies<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> gief.</NOTE> hie wunienge hwarefe&eth;. hie tu[r]ne&eth; fram iuele to werse. and fram bitere to biterure. and fram &thorn;e dome to helle. to &thorn;e ni&eth;er wunienge. &thorn;at is ful <MILESTONE N="124" UNIT="p">of alle wosi&eth;es. for &thorn;ere hie shulen hauen shame. and grame. and &thorn;esternesse. chele. and hunger. &thorn;urst. and stench. and wurmene cheu. and wallende fir and alre wowe mest. Crist us &thorn;erwi&eth; shilde. gif his wille beo. and alle &thorn;e sinfulle &thorn;e for&eth; sende farene. and &thorn;at faren shulen. and &thorn;at men moten fore bidden. and giue us alle on heuene eche erdingstouwe. <I>Qui viuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="29" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXIX. DE SANCTO ANDREA.</HEAD>
<P><I>AMbulans ihesuc iuxta mare. galilee uidit petrum et andream fratrem eius mittentes rete in mare. et cetera.</I> &ETH;e holi godspel of &thorn;is dai spec&eth; of ure helende and of two bro&eth;ren. 
<PB REF="00000203.tif" N="175"> &thorn;at on is Seint peter and &thorn;at o&eth;er Seint andreu. and sei&eth; &thorn;at ure helende giede bi &thorn;e se. and segh &thorn;os tweie brodren in &thorn;e se on here shipe werpinde ut here fishnet in &thorn;e se. and he clepede to hem and seide. <I>Venite post me.</I> Cume&eth; after me. and folge&eth; me. and hie ne abiden noht &thorn;at o&eth;er word, ac diden alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Ad unius iussionis uocem relictis retibus et naui. secuti sunt eum.</I> At te forme worde hie forleten here net and here ship. and come to ure helende and him folgeden to here lifes ende. swo moten we alle don &thorn;e ben after hem. and bi hem clepede ure helende us him to folgen. and we muge &thorn;e e&eth;ere gif we nime&eth; michele geme and wel understonden &thorn;at ure helende was on &thorn;e londe; and &thorn;ese bre&eth;ren weren on &thorn;e se; &thorn;o &thorn;e hem clepede to him. and gif we understonden ec wat bitocne&eth; &thorn;at lond. and hwat &thorn;e se. Vte we nu bidden ure drihten. &thorn;at he wisse. and fulste <MILESTONE N="125" UNIT="p">me heuliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> heu [ful]liche <I>or</I> [heu] treowe|liche.</NOTE>to seggen wat it bitocne&eth;. and heu frem|fulliche to understonden. <I>Mare semper est in motu. et signi|ficat ruinosam ciuitatem. id est seculum. de qua dicit apostolus. Non habemus hic manentem ciuitatem et cetera.</I> &ETH;e se is eure wagiende and &thorn;ere fore unstedefast. and bitocne&eth; &thorn;e abroidene bureh &thorn;at is in swo warliche<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Or</I> werliche. <I>At first sight it looks like</I> parliche.</NOTE> stede; &thorn;at noht ne mai &thorn;er inne bileue. &thorn;at muge ani wile ileste. &thorn;at is &thorn;is wrecche woreld. &thorn;at eure is wagiende noht fro stede to stede; ac fro time to time. and &thorn;at is on fele &thorn;inge ful michel iseone. and on &thorn;e man. alre mast for me nime&eth; of him mest geme. <I>Qui fugit uelut umbra et nunquam in eodem statu permanet.</I> He is fleonde alse shadewe and ne stont neure on one stede. Ac sige&eth; eure fro &yogh;uwe&eth;e to helde. fro hele to unhele. fro wenliche to ateliche. fro lieue to lo&eth;e. fro wur&eth;e to unwur&eth;e. fro blisse to sorinesse. fro lehtre to wope. fro wele to wowe. and attan ende fro liue to dea&eth;e. <I>Qui numero cuncta trahit secum uertitque uolubile tempus.</I> and alle woreld &thorn;ing turne&eth; mid time. and sige&eth; fro one time to o&eth;er. <I>Item. Sicut tempestas mare incidens aquas turbat fluctus agitat naues subuertem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <I>temptat. sic facit in seculo superbia et ira principium.</I> Eft sone bicume&eth; in &thorn;e se storm. and werpe&eth; &thorn;at water upward and arere&eth; shures fele. and driue&eth; hem biforen him. and gif he ship finde&eth;; he fonde&eth; to drenchen hit &yogh;if he mai. Swo do&eth; in 
<PB REF="00000205.tif" N="177"> &thorn;is woreld &thorn;e oreguil and &thorn;e wra&eth;&eth;e <MILESTONE N="126" UNIT="p">of kinges. and of barones &thorn;e senden here sergantes to bringen iuele ti&eth;inges. and &thorn;er mide dreuen &thorn;at lond &thorn;at is to water nemned. and bringen on &thorn;e folkes heorte grete stormes. of ni&eth;. and of onde. and of hatienge. and on here mu&eth;e curses and werginges. and wurre&eth; uppe chirches. o&eth;er wanie&eth; hire rihtes. o&eth;er lette&eth;. o&eth;er mid alle binime&eth; &yogh;if hie mugen. alse &thorn;e storm bisinke&eth; &thorn;e ship gif he mai. <I>Singula quid referam non noui nomina quorum. More fluentis aque currunt mortalia queque.</I> Ne mai ich noht alle &thorn;ing tellen. ne ich ne can here alre name nemnen. Ac alle woreld &thorn;ing ben fleted<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS.; read</I> fletende.</NOTE> alse water erninde. <I>Item mare effluit et refluit. Similiter et seculum effluit; dum fletus multiplicat, refluit; dum mortis manu metit.</I> Eft sone &thorn;e se flouwe&eth; &thorn;e hie caste&eth; ut &thorn;at water of hire stede. into &thorn;at lond; and ebbe&eth; &thorn;anne &thorn;at water of hire stede [flowe&eth;] in to &thorn;at lond; and eft agen turne&eth;. Swo flowe&eth; &thorn;is woreld &thorn;enne men michel tuderi&eth;. and oref. and deor. and fishshes. and fugeles. and here tuder swi&eth;e wexe&eth;. and wel &thorn;ie&eth;. and go&eth; wel on hond; longe wile. and be&eth; michel blisse among mannen. and of &thorn;is flod is iseid. <I>Eleuauerunt domine flumina uocem suam.</I> &ETH;e water stormes an-hefden here stefne. for wat is folc bute fletende water. &thorn;e flitte&eth; fro &thorn;is &thorn;at was. alse water storm fro stede to stede. and eft &thorn;is worel[d] ebbe&eth;. &thorn;enne hit &thorn;at tuderinde wi&eth;-teo&eth; and cume&eth; co&eth;e o&eth;er qualm. and michel &thorn;erof felle&eth;. &ETH;anne hauen wanspedie men on heorte wowe. and on mu&eth;e woninge. and here ech &thorn;e more wowe for o&eth;res woninge. and of swiche. <MILESTONE N="127" UNIT="p">ebbinge is iseid. <I>Eleuauerunt flumina fluctus suos et cetera.</I> &ETH;e water stremes on-heueden up here undes. &thorn;at is &thorn;at folc &thorn;e sore bimurne&eth;. and swi&eth;e bimene&eth; swich unilimp. On o&eth;er wise flowe&eth; and ebbe&eth; &thorn;is woreld. To-genes sumere heo flowe&eth; &thorn;anne alle moren quiken. and eor&eth;e and trewes growen. and blouwen. and blostmen bere&eth;. Eft to-&yogh;anes wintre heo hebbe&eth; &thorn;enne alle leues fallen. and for swiche flode. and for swich ebbinge &thorn;e prophete nemme&eth; &thorn;is woreld se. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Mirabiles elationes maris. et cetera.</I> Wunderliche ben &thorn;e s&aelig;. ut sondes. and wunderful is ure louerd on &thorn;eunesse. <I>Item. in</I> 
<PB REF="00000207.tif" N="179"> <I>mari pisces maiores deuorant minores</I>. Eft-sone &thorn;e more fishes in &thorn;e se eten &thorn;e lasse; and bi hem liuen. Swo don in &thorn;is woreld &thorn;e riche &thorn;e ben louerdinges struien &thorn;e wrecche men &thorn;e ben underlinges. and na&eth;eles bi hem libben. and habbe&eth; of here swinche hundes. and hauekes. and hors. and wepnes. and fogh. and grei. and estliche metes and drinkes. and al &thorn;at hie bi ben<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>; hie hauen of here mene swinche. &ETH;e underlinges &thorn;enchen o&eth;e dai hu hie mu&yogh;en mest swinken. and spenen here flesh and here blod; on iuele swinche; mid foten and mid honden. and mid alle here hund-limes. and unne&eth;es hie winnen giet here louerdes rihttes. and hem seluen eten &thorn;e werste &thorn;at hie of eor&eth;e tilien. and giet ne wile &thorn;e louerd ben paid mid his rihcte mol. ac mid swike-dome o&eth;er mid streng&eth;e. and<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> binime&eth; his under|linge. &thorn;at he sholde biliuen. and &yogh;if he net him to &yogh;iuene &thorn;at beo&eth; <MILESTONE N="128" UNIT="p">streng&eth;e. and refloc. and brec&eth; gri&eth;. &thorn;ar he hit healde sholde. and gief he him set a speche. and mid wo&yogh;e-dome binime&eth; him his biliue. &thorn;at he haue&eth; dere boht mid his ogene sowle. <I>Et sic ultricem domini prouocat iram.</I> And &thorn;us awec&eth; to-genes him seluen godes war&eth;&eth;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>; &thorn;e sei&eth; to louerde. <I>Ne facias alii quod tibi non uis fieri</I>. Ne do &thorn;u non o&eth;er man &thorn;ing. &thorn;e &thorn;e wolde of&thorn;unche gief me hit dude &thorn;e. To &thorn;e man he sei&eth;. <I>Michi uindictam; et ego retribuam.</I> Ne wrec &thorn;u &thorn;e mid wussinge. ne mid warienge. ac heald me &thorn;e wrache. and ich him wile his iuel mid werse forgelde. <I>Item mare est amarum. similiter et seculum ab introitu usque ad exitum.</I> Eft-sone &thorn;e s&aelig; is biter. swo is ec &thorn;is woreld fram ende to o&eth;er. and alle eor&eth;eliche men &thorn;e &thorn;ar onne wunien. alse wise que&eth;. <I>Nascimur in dolore. Viuimus in labore. Morimur in merore</I>. On sore eche we hider cumen. On swunche we here wunien. In wowe we henne wite&eth;. Hliste&eth; nu for hwat. and o wilche wise. Serehful is ure burde for eues gulte to wan ure drihten sede. <I>In dolore paries filios</I>. On sorege &thorn;u shalt child kennen; and beren. and swo hie dude. and alle o&eth;er don. bute ure lafdi Seinte Marie. <I>Que peperit sine dolore saluatorem.</I> Hire ne dide no&eth;er. ne oc. ne smeart. &thorn;o &thorn;e hie bar ure louerd ihesu crist. &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. Ac elch o&eth;er wimman do&eth;. ake&eth;. and smerte&eth; sore. &thorn;an 
<PB REF="00000209.tif" N="181"> hie be&eth; mid childe bistonden. and nime&eth; hire stundmele swo bittere &thorn;rowes &thorn;at hie ne mai hire mu&eth; holden. ac shrike&eth;. and reuliche biginne&eth;. and is welneih dead. for hie go&eth; welneih to hire liues ende. and fele here lif fulliche late&eth;. &ETH;at child <MILESTONE N="129" UNIT="p">on his burde &thorn;ole&eth; ec bittere &thorn;rowe. and cume&eth; of gemere hwile in to grimme wunienge. and cu&eth; mid his wope. Ac hwanne hit be&eth; &thorn;arto wuned; hit wepe&eth; &thorn;e lasse. for &thorn;at wune be&eth;. &thorn;eih hit ne be naht swete. Ac wowe be&eth; wunsum. &thorn;eih hit ne bie naht lefsum. On &thorn;isse liue we be&eth; on balfulle swinche for adames gulte. to hwam ure drihten seide. In <I>sudore</I> uultus <I>tui uesceris pane tuo</I>. On &thorn;ine nebbes swote. &thorn;u shalt &thorn;in bred noten. swo dude erest. and we alle don after. Ilch man of his wise; note&eth; his swinhc<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> swilch se he is to iteied. Clerc on his wise. Cniht on his wise. Tilie on his wise. And ilches craftes &thorn;eau; swo he be&eth; to iteied. and to eche &thorn;at iswinch ilches mannes hund|limen alle swinke&eth;. and hersume&eth; mest; alle &thorn;o &thorn;ere wombe. &ETH;e fet up aweige&eth;. and heuie &thorn;ar onne bere&eth;. &ETH;e honde fo&eth; to alle &thorn;inge &thorn;e hire be&eth; biheue. Eien loke&eth;. and eare luste&eth; and hwat hware beo &thorn;at hire wel like&eth;. Mu&eth; fog&eth; to hire bileue. Te&eth; hine grinde&eth;. Tunge hine swolege&eth;. &ETH;rote turne&eth; hine. and Mast alle &thorn;e hund limen hersumie&eth; &thorn;e onre wombe. and alle hem &thorn;inche&eth; to litel gief<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> gies.</NOTE> hit hire wel lica&eth;. &ETH;us was adam &thorn;eu; &thorn;o godes mu&eth; cursede eor&eth;e. and for his ouerdede qua&eth; &thorn;us to him. <I>Quia comedisti ex prohibito; maledicta terra in opere tuo</I>. For &thorn;at &thorn;u ete &thorn;at ich &thorn;e forboden hadde; waried wur&eth;e [&thorn;e eor&eth;e] on &thorn;ine werke. On eor&eth;e he wrohte &thorn;o &thorn;e he his wombe fulde. and on him dude &thorn;at we<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> he.</NOTE> on us do&eth;. For we<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> he.</NOTE> one awlenc&eth; alle &thorn;e hundlimen. and welt &thorn;e sowle. and hire weldede swo mid iuele forgielde&eth;. and unwur&eth;e&eth; ure drihten; wur&eth;e&eth; &thorn;e deuel. Eft|sones. <MILESTONE N="130" UNIT="p">on wowe we of &thorn;isse liue wite&eth;. for adames gulte &thorn;e ure drihten &thorn;us to seide. <I>Si ex ligno uetito comederis. morte morieris</I>. gief [&thorn;u] etest of &thorn;e forbodene trewe. &thorn;u shalt ade&eth;e swelte. Enes he &thorn;ar-offe bot, and wear&eth; &thorn;ar mide acheked. and &thorn;ureh &thorn;at one snede wear&eth; al his ofspring acheked. &ETH;at him cam to dea&eth;e swo hit do&eth; us alle. &ETH;an &thorn;e sowle funde&eth; to faren ut of hire licame. hie tune&eth; to hire fif gaten. and penne&eth; wel faste. and 
<PB REF="00000211.tif" N="183"> here wiken hem binime&eth;. &thorn;e hie ar noteden. Eien here sene. and Earen he[re] luste. nose here sneuenge. and mu&eth; here smel. To&eth;en here grind. and tunge here speche. and alle limen hie binimed mihte<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> nihte.</NOTE> to fri&eth;ende. Gief &thorn;e licame was rih[t]wis on &thorn;isse liue. wo be&eth; &thorn;e sowle &thorn;anne hie him shal forleten. and rewliche biginne&eth;. and &thorn;us to him sei&eth;. <I>Heu dilecta michi caro. quod te ponere cogor.</I> Awi leof ware &thorn;u me. nu ich shal &thorn;e forleten. &thorn;u ware me lastful on alle &thorn;o &thorn;e ich wolde. we ware onmode godes wille to done. Hwu shal ich of-longed wi&eth;-ute &thorn;e libben. And gief<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> gief.</NOTE> &thorn;e licame be&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> bed.</NOTE> euel. lo&eth; is heo &thorn;e sowle. and hire &thorn;unche&eth; lang; &thorn;at hie on<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> om.</NOTE> him bileue&eth;. and hie &thorn;enche&eth; fastliche &thorn;ar-offe to witen. Hit &thorn;inche&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> &thorn;incher.</NOTE> hire let. for hire is lo&eth; &thorn;ar-inne. &ETH;ane biginne&eth; hie rewliche. and to &thorn;e licame swilche wordes sei&eth;. <I>Heu michi cur olidum. fueram tibi iuncta cadauer.</I> Aweilewei &thorn;u fule hold &thorn;at ich auere was to &thorn;e iteied. longe habbe ich on &thorn;e wuned. swo wo is me &thorn;e hwile. for al &thorn;at me was leof; hit was &thorn;e lo&eth;. &thorn;u ware a sele gief ich was wro&eth;. To gode &thorn;u ware slau and let. and to euele spac and hwat. Al &thorn;at god het. &thorn;e &thorn;uht[e] andsete. &thorn;at forbode &thorn;e &thorn;uhte <MILESTONE N="131" UNIT="p">swete. Iuele wurmes mote &thorn;e chewe; swo we<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>? read</I> wo.</NOTE> &thorn;e be &thorn;at tu me [ne] rewe. for &thorn;ine gulte ishal nu to pine. rotie mote &thorn;u to time. &ETH;us ware&eth; &thorn;e sowle &thorn;e licame. for &thorn;at hit haue&eth; &thorn;ar after ierned. Among &thorn;at &thorn;e sowle wite&eth;. &thorn;e licame worpe&eth; hewe. &thorn;e frendmen him biwepe&eth; gef &thorn;ar anie ben. bigeme&eth; &thorn;e licame; and forgeme&eth; &thorn;e sowle. &thorn;anne fon uncu&eth;e me[n] to &thorn;e aihte &thorn;e arure his waren. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Relinquent alienis diuicias suas.</I> Hie bileue&eth; uncu&eth;e me[n] &thorn;e aihte &thorn;e hie forleten habbe&eth;. &thorn;e man is uncu&eth; &thorn;e o&eth;er; &thorn;e nele naht him cnowen. ne helpen him gief he neod haue&eth;. &thorn;us do&eth; &thorn;e libbende frend to-genes &thorn;e liggende. Gief &thorn;e quike haue&eth; aihte &thorn;e were &thorn;e dedes &aelig;rrure. &thorn;e he him bique&eth;. &thorn;o he him seluen habben ne mihte. &thorn;e quike hem do&eth; him selue to note. and nohte deades sowle to note. Ac sei&eth; to hwam he wi&eth; speke&eth;, hwi sholde ich him luuien si&eth;en he was him seluen lo&eth;. hwi sholde ich him helpen; him self ne wolde; &thorn;o he mihte. Hwi sholde ich dele for him; &thorn;at he ne mihte bileuen. &thorn;e hwile he hise waren; he dude his wille &thorn;ar-offe. Swo ich wile 
<PB REF="00000213.tif" N="185"> mine nu hit is to me iturnd. and leren elch man to helpen him seluen &thorn;e hwile he mai. Nu ge habbe&eth; iherd &thorn;at sorehful is ure hider cume. and sorilich ure henen si&eth;. and hure he[r]|wunenge is swi&eth;e reulich. Wule nu &thorn;anne foleg seinte andreues faire forbisne. and &thorn;enchen he&eth;en to fare to siker wunienge. &thorn;ar ure helende wune&eth;. and haue&eth; us to cleped. <I>Scilicet terra promissionis. Ciuitas habitacionis. Conuersacio celestis.</I> &ETH;at is &thorn;at bihotene lond. &thorn;ar is <MILESTONE N="132" UNIT="p">on &thorn;e wunsume<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> wum|sume.</NOTE> bureh. and on &thorn;e heuenliche wunienge &thorn;ar alle englen inne wunien. &ETH;ar haue&eth; elch patriarche. and prophete and apostles. and martirs and confessors. and uirgines maked faier bode inne to wunien. swo briht se sunne. Elch bilefful man &thorn;e is &thorn;ider iboden. shal finden &thorn;are his buttle. swulc se he hit here make&eth;. mid his faire liflode. and on &thorn;e fereden of ure helende seluen. and of alle halegen. shal habben eche lif. and endelease blisse. and alle sel&eth;e and fulle muri&eth;e. &thorn;e is swo muchel and swo faier. and swo swete. alse Seint paulus sei&eth;. <I>Quod oculus non uidit. et auris non audiuit et in cor hominis non ascendit.</I> Swo muchel muri&eth;e is in &thorn;e bureh of heuene &thorn;at eie ne maig swo muchel biholden. ne [ere] lhisten ne herte &thorn;enchen. <I>Ad quam nos ducat. qui uite premia donat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="30" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXX. [ESTOTE FORTES IN BELLO.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Esto[te] fortes in bello. et pugnate cum antiquo serpente.</I> &ETH;os feawe word &thorn;e ich nu here for&eth;-teah seide ure drihten. on his holie godspelle. at sume sele &thorn;o &thorn;e he wunede licameliche on eor&eth;e. among mannen and wandrede ine &thorn;e lond of ierusalem. and mid &thorn;ese wordes munegede &thorn;o &thorn;e he wi&eth; spac; to griseliche fihte. and for &thorn;at &thorn;e &thorn;at fiht was and is arue&eth; to &thorn;olien. he bihet hem muchele mede. wi&eth; &thorn;an &thorn;at hie wolden hit admodeliche &thorn;olien. and &thorn;us qua&eth;. <I>Estote fortes in bello. et cetera.</I> Beo&eth; stronge on fihte. and fihte&eth; wi&eth; &thorn;e ealde neddre. and gef<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> ges.</NOTE> [gie] ben strengere &thorn;ane hie; gie shulle fon to mede &thorn;at endeles kineriche. <I>Quia uero diuersa hominum genera sequebantur ut audirent eum.</I> 
<PB REF="00000215.tif" N="187"> <I>et ipse sermones suos direxit. tum ad discipulos tum ad populum. tum ad hos et illos &aacute;periendum est. et quibus. et de qua fortitu|dine. et de quo bello. et de quo serpente. et de quo regno dixit.</I> Manie mannisshe folgeden ure <MILESTONE N="133" UNIT="p">drihte. to herende his wise word for to isen his wunderliche deden. and of him to habben heore bileue. and sume to fechen at him here hele. and for &thorn;i wilen segen eow hwilc mannisshe he &thorn;us munegede. Sume leien on here sunnes. and ne wolden hem naht forleten. and on &thorn;at wise mid here f&oacute; hielden. hem ne munegede he naht to &thorn;isse fihte. Ac &thorn;o he munegede. &thorn;e hadden heore sinnes forleten and bette. o&eth;er bigunnen to beten. and hem &thorn;arwi&eth; buregen and milce beden. And nameliche &thorn;e twolue apostles. and among hem &thorn;e louerd saint N. hwos dai hit is to dai. and for hwos luue we be&eth; here gadered. and &thorn;us que&eth;. <I>Estote fortes in bello. et cetera.</I> beo&eth; strange on fihte. and fihte&eth; ealde neddre. and fo&eth; eche blisse to mede. Of &thorn;e streng&eth;e &thorn;e ure drihten us to munege&eth;. spec&eth; wis|dom boc and sei&eth;. <I>Fortitudo simplicis uia domini.</I> Godes wei is strong &thorn;e ofealde man. Ofeald o&eth;er twifeald is ilch man. Of &thorn;e twifealde man spec&eth; &thorn;e louerd Seint Iame &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Uir dupplex animo inconstans est in omnibus uiis suis.</I> &ETH;e twifealde man is unstedefast on alle his spechen<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> weies.</NOTE>. Twifold o&eth;er manifold is &thorn;e man. &thorn;e nis stedefast ne on dade. ne on<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> os.</NOTE> speche. ne on &thorn;onke. ne [to-]genes gode. ne to-genes man. and &thorn;ar-fore is forloren lif and sowle. Ac &thorn;e man is ofeald. &thorn;e haue&eth; edmod &thorn;anc. and e&eth;ele speche. and edie dade. and is stedefast to-genes god and men. alse Iob was. &thorn;e wan wi&eth; &thorn;e wurse. of hwam &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Erat uir ille simplex et rectus ac timens domini. et recedens &aacute; malo</I>. He was ofeald man and rih[t]wis. and Godfriht. and strong on &thorn;e fihte &thorn;e ic offe speke. and &thorn;at streng&eth;e he hadde of godes weie. &thorn;e onne was. <I>Via domini qua uenit ad nos et nos ad eum; est misericordia et ueritas.</I> <MILESTONE N="134" UNIT="p">Godes weie &thorn;e he come&eth; one to mannen. and men to him; is mild-hertnesse. and so&eth;fastnesse. Mildhertnesse he kidde mannisse &thorn;o &thorn;e he sende his holi prophete to freurende &thorn;o forsine&yogh;ede of &thorn;is wrecche woreld, and bihet hem &thorn;at he cumen wolde. and lesen hem of eche wowe So&eth;fastnesse he cudde him; &thorn;o &thorn;e he him seluen 
<PB REF="00000217.tif" N="189"> com. and his bihese lestede. and mid his o&yogh;ene dea&eth;e al mankin alesde of eche dea&eth;e &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. &thorn;at ilke wei ogh al mankin to holden &thorn;e &thorn;enche&eth; to cumene to gode. and ki&eth;e&eth; him seluen mildhertnesse. and so&eth;fastnesse. and after his mihte. &thorn;e man ki&eth; him seluen mildhertnesse &thorn;e bi&eth;enche&eth; on his sinnen. and understant &thorn;at he haue&eth; &thorn;er &thorn;urh forloren heuene wele. and of-erned helle pine and &thorn;at sore bimurne&eth;. and &thorn;o sinnes for|lete&eth;. and to shrifte cume&eth;. So&eth;fastnesse he ki&eth; ec him seluen &thorn;enne he his sinnes alle swo shewe&eth; alse hie don weren. and noht &thorn;er-offe forleten. ne noht &thorn;at to non ne don. and &thorn;er offe bote hihat. and bi his mihte leste&eth; hit. and milce bit. and &thorn;anen-for&eth;|ward wi&eth; sinne him berege&eth;. Nu &yogh;e hauen herd to wich streng&eth;e ure drihten us to mune&yogh;e&eth;. here&eth; nu to wiche fihte we o&yogh;en &thorn;is streng&eth;e notien. &thorn;e holi man tobias sei&eth; wiche fiht &thorn;at is &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Milicia est uita hominis super terram</I>. Man|nes liflode buuen eor&eth;e is fardung. An[d] to-genes hwuch fo man agh fur&eth;ien sei&eth; &thorn;e holi apostle. &thorn;er he sei&eth;. <I>Non est nobis col|luctacio aduersus carnem carnem</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <I>et sanguinem. sed aduersus rec|tores tenebrarum.</I> We ne flite&eth; noht to-&yogh;enes flesh. and blod. ac to|&yogh;enes awere&yogh;ede gostes &thorn;e <MILESTONE N="135" UNIT="p">welde&eth; &thorn;esternesse. and on o&eth;er stede wisluker &thorn;e[r] of spec&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Caro concupiscit aduersus spiritum spirituc autem aduersus carnem. ut quecunque uultis illa faciatis</I>. &ETH;e lichame winne&eth; to&yogh;enes &thorn;e gost. and &thorn;e gost to&yogh;enes &thorn;e lichame. and swo fliten and winnen bitwenen hem. &thorn;at al &thorn;at is on unlef and unqueme. hit is &thorn;at o&eth;er iqueme. and on &thorn;is fihte is ech man strong. &thorn;e awelt is lichame. and his wille binime&eth;. and wlenc&eth; his soule. and hire wille drige&eth;. and on o&eth;re stede he sei&eth;. <I>Abstinete uos &aacute; carnalibus desideriis que mili|tant aduersus animam.</I> Wi&eth;-teo&eth; &yogh;iu &thorn;e fleshliche lustes &thorn;e flite&eth; to-&yogh;enes &thorn;e soule. and fonde&eth; hire &aacute; fele wise; mid swikele wrenchen. and feste bisette&eth;. and sore for-wunde&eth;. and beo&eth; &thorn;e sme&eth;ere him to biswikende. for &thorn;an &thorn;e &thorn;ei neh&yogh;ie wunien. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Nulla sevior</I><NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> senior.</NOTE> <I>pestis quam familaris hostis</I>. Nis non werse fo; &thorn;ene frakede fere. <I>Ab inuisibili hoste difficile cauetur assultus.</I> Arue&eth; it is wi&eth; &thorn;e fo to ber&yogh;ende. for me ne wot a wiche halfe he beo&eth;. and arue&eth; hit is &thorn;e dintes to kepende. for 
<PB REF="00000219.tif" N="191"> me ne wot hwanene he shal cumen. To swiche fihte bede&eth; ure drihten us. and &thorn;at we kiden &thorn;er one ure streng&eth;e. and at ech fihte to-&yogh;enes &thorn;e alde neddre &thorn;e bipehte eue; and adam; and al here ofspring. <I>Diabolus nominatur hic serpens propter tria. In|uidia tabescit. Sine strepitu serpit. Quod pungit ueneno afficit.</I> Neddre do&eth; &thorn;re &thorn;ing lichamliche; &thorn;e &thorn;e deuel dri&yogh;e&eth; gostliche. hie haue&eth; ni&eth;. and onde. and smu&yogh;&eth; di&yogh;eliche. and attre&eth; hwat heo prike&eth;. Swo haue&eth; &thorn;e deuel ni&eth;. and onde to men for &thorn;an. <MILESTONE N="136" UNIT="p">hem is bi-hoten &thorn;e hege sete on heuene. &thorn;e he fel of. &thorn;urgh is ore&yogh;el &thorn;erefore he cume&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> cunne&eth;?</NOTE> letten hem mid alle his widerfulle wrenches and ne wolde &thorn;at mankin hadde &thorn;at he hauen ne mai. ac wolde &thorn;at man dead were &thorn;ehg him seluen &thorn;e werse were. alse &thorn;e apostle sei&eth;. <I>Per inuidiam mors intrauit in orbem ter|rarum.</I> &ETH;urch onde com dea&eth; in to &thorn;e worelde; al umbegonge. Eft-sone. neddre smuhg&eth; di&yogh;eliche. Swo do&eth; &thorn;e werse. &thorn;enne he auint mannes heorte emti of rihte bi-leue. and of so&eth;ere luue. he seche&eth; forte &thorn;at he open fint. and di&yogh;eliche smuhg&eth; &thorn;er inne. at te e&yogh;en &yogh;if it open ben to bi-holden idel. o&eth;er unnut. atte earen &yogh;if it open ben to listen unnut o&eth;er idel. at te nose &yogh;if it beo&eth; open to snuuende unluuede bre&eth;. at te mu&eth; &yogh;if hit open beo&eth; to spekende mis. o&eth;er on ete. o&eth;er on drinke to mis don. at te shape &yogh;if hie redie ben to golliche deden. <I>He sunt autem. v. porte mortis. per quas ingreditur autor mortis ut occidat. et efferat mor|tuos.</I> attese fif gaten fare&eth; in dea&eth;es wrihte. and &thorn;er inne do&eth;; alse &thorn;e loftsongere sei&eth;. <I>Per mille meandros agitat quieta corda.</I> Mid &thorn;usendfeld wrenches he &thorn;e herte to-wende&eth; and al te seche&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;onc &thorn;e was er swo fieble. and wunde&eth; &thorn;e hertes mid hinder|fulle wrenches. and mid te shene attre &thorn;urh seche&eth; al &thorn;e soule. &ETH;us flite&eth; &thorn;e fiend wi&eth; alle men. and to fele &thorn;er-of walt to his wille. and &thorn;o ben alle unwepnede. &thorn;e ne hauen mid hwan hie hem werien. Ne ne wite wanne. ne awiche. halue ne awiche wise he hem wile bisette &thorn;anne &thorn;e he hem unwarliche his dintes giue&eth;. Ac alle <MILESTONE N="137" UNIT="p">&thorn;o &thorn;e godes wapne bere&eth;. and hem burege cunnen; hie ben boregen. Bidde we nu ure helende &thorn;at he us healde &thorn;is win. &thorn;at he geue us &thorn;o wapnes mide us to weriene; &thorn;e &thorn;e apostles offe speke&eth;. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Induite uos armatura dei. ut possitis</I> 
<PB REF="00000221.tif" N="193"> <I>stare aduersus insidias diaboli.</I> Shrude&eth; eow mid godes wapne. and werie&eth; eow wi&eth; &thorn;e defles waitinge. <I>Sumentes loricam fidei. Galeam spei. Clipeum caritatis. Gladium spirituc sancti quod est uerbum dei.</I> Habbe&eth; rihte bileue to brunie. and hope to helme. and so&eth;e luue to shelde. and godes word to swerde. <I>His armis munitus uicit dauid goliam.</I> Mid &thorn;os wapnes dauid shrude him mid &thorn;e he ouercam goliam. Swo wille crist &thorn;at we moten. and alle &thorn;ese wapnes here noten on &thorn;is fihte to-genes &thorn;e ealde neddre. &thorn;at is alre manne fo. &thorn;at we him moten ouercumen. and habbe to mede eche blisse; and &thorn;at endelese kineriche. <I>Quod nobis prestet qui secula per omnia regnat.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="31" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXXI. [ESTOTE PRUDENTES ET VIGILATE IN ORATIONIBUS.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Estote prudentes et uigilate in oracionibus.</I> &ETH;e heuenliche<NOTE PLACE="marg">[1 Pet. iv. 7.]</NOTE> keiherde sainte peter iseih &thorn;at ure elderne hadden fele fon. and we habbe&eth; alswo. &THORN;e ben alto smiele<NOTE PLACE="foot">Read <I>smiehe</I> or <I>smieliche.</I> See p. 195, l. 5, and p. 205, l. 19, where the correct reading, <I>smehe</I> or <I>smehliche</I>, is suggested.</NOTE> on swikedom. and hwatte us to biswikende. and wulled swo don bute we wur&eth;en us warre. and mugen mucheles &thorn;e e&eth;ere. gef hie finde&eth; us slepende. &ETH;ane no man us ne were&eth;. ne us seluen ne mugen. ne god nele ich adrade; bute we him &thorn;e gernere bidden. and &thorn;ar-fore &thorn;e apostel on &thorn;os feawe wordes &thorn;e ich here for&eth; tea&yogh;h; munege&eth; us to &thorn;rie &thorn;inges. On is giepshipe &thorn;at o&eth;er is wakienge. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde is bede. &thorn;us que&eth;ende. <I>Estote prudentes. et cetera.</I> Be&eth; giepe. and warre. and wakie&eth;. and <MILESTONE N="138" UNIT="p">bidde&eth; &yogh;iu to gode. &thorn;at he &yogh;iue &yogh;iu &yogh;epshipe. and warshipe &yogh;iu wi&eth; to werien. and &thorn;ese &thorn;reo &thorn;ing note&eth; ech man on two wise; wel; and wro&eth;e. Man hit note&eth; wro&eth;eliche. &thorn;e mid &yogh;epshipe bicher&eth; his emcristen. and hindre&eth; his a&yogh;ene soule. alswo do&eth; eches kinnes chapman; on eche chepinge. and talewise men &thorn;e speches driuen, and maken wrong to rihte; and riht to wronge. and alle &thorn;o; &thorn;e unriht don. and here emcristen bicharen. &thorn;e man hindre&eth; his agene soule; and dele&eth; him fro gode. and fulste&eth; 
<PB REF="00000223.tif" N="195"> him to &eth;e deuel &thorn;e is gredi uppen woreld richeise. and gredi him to pinende<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> winende.</NOTE> and &yogh;iep him to biwitiende. Swich &yogh;epshipe forbede&eth; &thorn;e apostel. &thorn;ere he sei&eth;. <I>Nolite esse prudentes aput uosmetipsos.</I> Ne beo &yogh;e noht &yogh;epe to-&yogh;ene &yogh;iu seluen. &ETH;e man is &yogh;iep to-&yogh;enes him seluen; &thorn;at is smegh o&eth;er man to bi|charren. and to bi-swiken and his a&yogh;ene wille to fremen. Alse &thorn;e fox &thorn;e mid his wrenches walt o&eth;er deor; and haue&eth; his wille &thorn;erof. &ETH;e man note&eth; wel his &yogh;iepshipe. &thorn;e birge&eth; him seluen wi&eth; his a&yogh;ene soule unfreme. and erne&eth; after his soule freme. To swich &yogh;iepshipe mine&yogh;ede hure helende his apostles. and us bi hem &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Ecce ego mitto uos et cetera.</I> &ETH;o ure helende sende hie &thorn;e weren milde alse shep among &thorn;at unbilefde folc &thorn;e wolden dreuen hem. and swo diden alse wulf do&eth; shep and seide &thorn;us. <I>Estote prudentes sicut serpentes.</I> Here ich &yogh;iu sende alse shep amang wulfes. beo&eth; &thorn;enne &yogh;iepe. and seide hem wu &yogh;iepe. alse &thorn;e neddre. &thorn;egh neddre beo iuel na&eth;eles man nime&eth; of hire &yogh;eme of gode. <I>Est equidem genus serpentum quod cum timet periculum occultat caput sub corpore. et corpus obicit periculo.</I> anes kinnes neddres is &thorn;e mid hire lichame hele&eth; hire <MILESTONE N="139" UNIT="p">heued. &thorn;ane he be&eth; of harme offered. for hire lif is on hire heued. Swo dude Iob. &thorn;e nes non abuuen eor&eth;e him ilich on almesse<NOTE PLACE="marg">? halinesse.</NOTE>. &thorn;o &thorn;e deuel him fondede. and wolde him binimen his lif. &thorn;at was ure drihte leuest of alle liuiende &thorn;ing and gief [he hadde] werred wi&eth; god alse &thorn;e deuel him to eggede. &thorn;anne hadde he forloren god &thorn;e is eche lif. Ac he notede &thorn;e naddre giapshipe. and dude his licame mid his helpe biforen his heued; to-genes &thorn;e harm &thorn;e &thorn;e deuel him dude. &thorn;o &thorn;e he brohte &thorn;e manifeald unlimpes uppen him. Erest he strepte of him his shep. &thorn;e waren his woreld winne. <I>scilicet vii milia ouium. et iiij. milia camelorum et. l. iuga boum. et quingenti asini.</I> &thorn;at waren seuen &thorn;usend shep. and &thorn;rie &thorn;usend oluontes. and half hundre giokes of ocsen. and fif hundred assen. alle &thorn;os wennen huihten his wur&eth;shipe. alse faire wedes don &thorn;e licame. <I>Sicut legitur. Tem|poralia sunt quasi quedam corporis indumenta.</I> Alse &thorn;e wise seide. Eor&eth;eliche winne ben mannes wedes. <I>Inde tulit ei. vij</I><SUP>tem</SUP> <I>filios; et iij. filias. et familiam multam nimis</I>. After &thorn;at 
<PB REF="00000225.tif" N="197"> &thorn;e deuel hadde binumen him al his strene; &thorn;at waren his seuen sunes and &thorn;rie dochtres. and al &thorn;at muchele husshipe; &thorn;e him sholde heren. &thorn;e hadde boden his streng&thorn;e to-genes his licames|lice<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> fo. <I>Cum percussit eum ulcere pessimo</I>. Si&eth;en-mest he wundede him wel neih to de&eth;e. Swo &thorn;at he ne mihte finden on al his licame hwar he his finger on sette bute uppen wunden. And on alle &thorn;ese limpes. ne untrowede neure Iob to-genes ure drihten. ac &thorn;onkede him of &thorn;an wowe. alse dude ar of &thorn;e wele. <MILESTONE N="140" UNIT="p">&thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Dominus dedit dominus abstulit sicut domino</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Job i.21.]</NOTE> <I>placuit ita factum sit nomen domini benedictum.</I> Ure louerd hit &yogh;af ure louerd it binam. hit is wor&eth;en alse ure louerd wolde he&yogh;ed. and hered beo his holi name. <I>Caput quod occultauit fides eius fuit.</I> &thorn;at heued &thorn;at he helede. wi&eth; &thorn;e deules eginge. was his rihte bileue. &thorn;at he held faste. for alse mannes heued. is he&yogh;est lime; and latteu. swo wisse&eth; rihtte bi-leue &thorn;e soule; and lede&eth; hem<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> riht to gode. <I>Est et aliud genus serpentis. quod habet in capite gemmam ne exaudiat incantantes. alteram auriculam ad lapidem applicat. Alteram postremitatis sue obturat</I>. O&eth;er kinnes neddre is ut in o&eth;er londe. &thorn;at haue&eth; on hire heued derewur&eth;e &yogh;imston. and te londes men hire bigale&eth; o&eth;er wile. and swo lache&eth;. and do&eth; of liue; for to hauen &thorn;e &yogh;imston. ac wanne &thorn;e neddre hit under&yogh;it &thorn;at hie sechen after hire. hie warne&eth; hire wi&eth; hem alse &thorn;e salm wurhte sei&eth;. <I>Sicut aspidis surde et</I><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. lviii. 4.]</NOTE> <I>obturantis. aures suas que non exaudiet uocem incantantium.</I> &thorn;e neddre seche&eth; &aacute; ston and lei&eth; hire on eare &thorn;er to. and hire o&eth;er eare pilte&eth; hire tail &thorn;er inne. and swo for-ditte&eth; ei&eth;er. &thorn;at hie ne muge heren here remenge. ne here gal. and &thorn;us atbreste&eth; hire fo. and berged hire liue. Nime we &yogh;eme of &thorn;is faier forbisne. and fol&yogh;en hire bi ure mihte. <I>[N]os sumus quasi serpentes terre cor|pore adherentes Caput nostrum fides nostra. [G]emma in capite deus in mente. Diabolus incantator. suggestio incantacio petra christi diuinitas postremitas</I><NOTE PLACE="foot">Originally <I>postremitatis</I>. By means of a strong glass a faint line appears to be drawn through <I>tremita</I>.</NOTE> <I>eius humanitas. auricula intellectus noster.</I> we bed alse &thorn;e neddre. hie smug&eth; strect bi &thorn;e eor&eth;e and we don alse. &thorn;enne we &thorn;e eor&eth;e blostmes. on corne and on ahte biseche&eth;. and welde&eth;. and note&eth;. &thorn;e neddre hire turne&eth; wile to 
<PB REF="00000227.tif" N="199"> tresle. and we don alse <MILESTONE N="141" UNIT="p">&thorn;anne we ure woreld winne swo faste bi-witen. &thorn;enne we ne mu&yogh;en atemien to wur&eth;en godes bord he&yogh;e dages ne eche dai bi ure haue helpe wrecche men. Neddre haue&eth; on hire heued derewur&eth;e &yogh;imston. and we hauen on ure bileue ure drihten. on wam we bileuen. &thorn;e is alre lemene fader. and welle of alle mihtin. Man<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> mid is gele. egged us and fonde&eth;. and for&eth;-te&eth; to idele &thorn;onke. and unnutte speche. and iuele speche. and mid wi&yogh;es bipeche&eth;. bute we &thorn;e warluker us bure&yogh;en. ac &thorn;enne we ate&eth; &thorn;at te iuele fonde&eth; us. alse ich er seide. bu&yogh;e we to &thorn;e stone &thorn;e &thorn;e apostel of spac &thorn;o he sede. <I>Petra autem erat christuc.</I> &THORN;at is ure helend crist &thorn;at is ston nemned. for his stede|fastnesse. To him we legge&eth; ure riht eare &thorn;enne we understonde&eth; &thorn;at he is so&eth; god. and &thorn;ere-fore nehleche[&eth;] us to him. and ditte&eth; swo &thorn;at eare wi&eth; &thorn;e werses lore. Ure left eare we ditte&eth; mid ure after ende. &thorn;enne we understonden &thorn;at he bi-com man for us. and noht for ure erninge. ac for his admodnesse &thorn;olede on his lichame de&eth;. and arerde us of de&eth;e. and eche lif us biget<NOTE PLACE="marg">? <I>read</I> bihet.</NOTE> gif we it here oferni&eth;. and swo ditte&eth; &thorn;e eare. and noh[t] ne hercni&eth; here gal. <I>Est et aliud genus serpentis quod cum senescit de fonte gurgitat ut uirus euomat. per lapidis artum foramen transit et pellem deponit sicque se nouum efficit.</I> O&eth;er kinnes neddre is. &thorn;enne hie be&eth; old. &thorn;urh hire &yogh;epshipe wur&eth; eft &yogh;ung. Liste&eth; nu awiche wise. &thorn;enne hie be&eth; of-&thorn;urst cume&eth; to sum welle. and drinke&eth; &aacute; draht swo michel &thorn;at heo chine&eth;. and &thorn;enne spewe&eth; hire atter. and cume&eth; to ane &thorn;urlede ston. and criepe&eth; nedlinge &thorn;ureh nerewe hole. and bileue&eth; hire hude baften hire. &thorn;enne<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> <MILESTONE N="142" UNIT="p">&thorn;anne<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> cume&eth; hire o&eth;er hude. and hie be&eth; al newe. We ben alse &thorn;e nedre hie haue&eth; longe liued; and we longe leien in sinne. Hie haue&eth; muchel atter on hire; and is lo&eth; mannen. and we hude&eth; li&eth;ere sinnen on us. for hwan we be&eth; andsete gode. Hire &thorn;urst swi&eth;e. and seche&eth; &thorn;anne welle and drinke&eth; &thorn;at hie to-chine&eth;. and hire atter aspewe&eth;. And &thorn;ane we bi&eth;enche&eth; on ure sinnes. O&eth;er hwile us luste leornie hwu we mugen ure sinnes forleten. and beten. and cumen &thorn;ar man lorspel sei&eth;. and lusten. and wur&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> wurd.</NOTE> ure heorte &thorn;anne swo sor for ure sinnes. &thorn;at wel neih hie to-chine&eth;. &ETH;anne forsake we ure sinnes mid heorte. and for-hote&eth; mid mu&eth;e. and bi ure lor&eth;ewes 
<PB REF="00000229.tif" N="201"> wissinge cume&eth; to &thorn;e stone. &thorn;e haue&eth; fif hole narewe. &thorn;at is ure helende crist. &thorn;e &thorn;olede his holie fif wunden for us. &thorn;anked wur&eth;e him. and &thorn;ar-&thorn;urh arue&eth;liche crepe&eth;; &thorn;ane we mid fif-folde pine ure sinnes bete&eth;. &ETH;e neddre bileued hire hude baften hire. and cume&eth; newe fel. and hie wur&eth; jung. and we worpe&eth; ure hewe. &thorn;ane we forlete&eth; ure fule liflode. and wur&eth;e&eth; junge on clenesse swo we waren ar &thorn;an we sinegeden. alse &thorn;e boc sei&eth;. <I>Veterem hominem exuimus. et nouum induimus.</I> We habbe&eth; don of us &thorn;e ealde man. &thorn;e us horegede alle. and don on &thorn;e newe &thorn;e clense&eth; alle. Swilch giepshipe habbe&eth; &thorn;ese &thorn;rie kenne neddre. and ure helende minegede his apostles hem to habben. and bi hem us. alse seinte peter que&eth;. <I>Estote prudentes et uigilate.</I> Be&eth; warre and wakie&eth;. <I>Alii quidem dormiunt.</I> Alii autem <I>uigilant.</I> Sume men slape&eth; faste. and sume nappe&eth;. and sume mid alle wakie&eth;. &ETH;e man slape&eth; faste. &thorn;e li&eth; on swilche sinnes &thorn;e him &thorn;unche&eth; swete. and wel like&eth;. Ac gef ure drihten hine fint &thorn;us slepende. &thorn;at is on sinne; <MILESTONE N="143" UNIT="p">ne wake&eth; he nafre ef[t]. <I>Dormitans nunc oculos claudit. nunc aperit. Sed homo qui peccatum gemit; nec tum relinquit.</I> Man &thorn;e nappe&eth; wile to heue&eth; his e&yogh;en and &thorn;enne se&eth;. and wile lei&eth; togadere and &thorn;enne noht ne se&eth;. Swo do&eth; &thorn;e sinfulle. &thorn;e his sinnes swi&eth;e bimurne&eth;. and sore bisiche&eth;. and &thorn;enche&eth; hem to forleten. and &thorn;erto funde&eth; and noht ne fol&yogh;e&eth;. and &yogh;if ure drihten hine swo fint he wile hine sende to helle. &thorn;e man &thorn;e hise nemde sinnes forleten. and bi his shriftes wissinge bet. o&eth;er on bote bifongen. he wake&eth; mid alle. To swiche wecche us mine&yogh;e&eth; ure drihten on &thorn;e godspelle. &thorn;er he sei&eth;. <I>Omnibus dico uigilate.</I> Alle bileffulle ich hote &thorn;us waken ac &thorn;e heuenliche louerd us het wakien on bede. and notien swiche bede. swo us biheue bie. Alle holie beden ben godfruhte men biheue. Ac &thorn;e ben swo fele &thorn;at hie ben arfe&eth; tellen. Na&eth;eles &thorn;u miht swo fele mid fewe biluken. and swo do&eth; ech man &thorn;enne he sing&eth; is pater noster. Ure louerd seinte peter &thorn;e us mine&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;us to &yogh;epshipe. and to wecche and us to bidden. he &thorn;inge us to ure drihten &thorn;at he us &yogh;iue swiche &yogh;epshipe and mihte &thorn;us to wakien. and us to bidden. and &yogh;ife us bene tu&eth;e. <I>Qui uiuit et regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I>
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="32" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000231.tif" N="203">
<HEAD>XXXII. SERMO IN MARCUM VIII. 34.</HEAD>
<P><I>QVi uult uenire post me abneget semet ipsum et tollat crucem suam. et sequatur me</I>. Sori mai &thorn;e man ben &thorn;e be&eth; on michele wowe. and me him more bihat. and mai and wile hit him lesten. Ac &thorn;e man mai ben bli&eth;e &thorn;e me lede&eth; fram miche wowe to michele wele. and swich blisse me bihat us alle. Alle we ben on manifolde wowe on &thorn;is worelde. for ure eldrene giltes. and ec for ure agene sinnen. <MILESTONE N="144" UNIT="p">ac ure drihten us frefre&eth; mid his admodie worden &thorn;onked wur&eth;e him. and la&eth;e&eth; us ut of ure wunsume wowe. to his michele blisse. and sei&eth; us on wiche wise. and bi wich weie we mu&yogh;en &thorn;ider cumen. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Qui uult uenire. et cetera.</I> &THORN;e man &thorn;e wile folge me forsake him seluen and bere his rode and cume after me. &thorn;o &thorn;e he fundede to faren of eor&eth;e in to heuene. he seide &thorn;os word to alle &thorn;o &thorn;e &thorn;o weren<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. &thorn;eren.</NOTE>. and si&eth;en hauen ben. and &thorn;o &thorn;e nu ben. and &thorn;o her after cumen. And alle he la&eth;e&eth; ech asume wise to endelese blisse. Ac feawe &thorn;er-offe cume&eth;. and fele bileue&eth;. for &thorn;at hem &thorn;inc&eth; iuel to forleten &thorn;at hie swi&eth;e luue&eth;. <I>Alii quidem amant peccata sua. Alii parentes. Alii uero possessiones. atque alii uoluptates. et uicia.</I> Sume luue&eth; heore sinnen. and sume heore kin. and sume here eor&eth;liche ahte. and sume here wille. and fleshliche lustes. and li&eth;ere lahtres. &thorn;o &thorn;e luuie&eth; here sinnen la&eth;e&eth; ure drihten &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Penitenciam agite apropinquabit enim regnum celorum.</I> Swike&eth; of giure sinnes. and bede&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> bete&eth;.</NOTE> hem. and bere&yogh;e&eth; &yogh;iu wi&eth; &thorn;o; and wi&eth; o&eth;ere and bidde&eth; milce &thorn;e wile &thorn;e &yogh;e mu&yogh;en. domes dai nehleche&eth;. &thorn;o &thorn;e luuie&eth; here kin. he la&eth;e&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Omnis qui relinquerit patrem et matrem fratrem et sororem aut ceteros propter nomen meum centuplum accipiet et uitam eternam possidebit.</I> Ech man &thorn;e for mine name forsake&eth; fader. o&eth;er moder suster o&eth;er bro&eth;er. o&eth;er o&eth;re. and fol&yogh;e&eth; me he shal fon &thorn;er-to-&yogh;enes hundredfeld mede. and 
<PB REF="00000233.tif" N="205"> habben lif abuten ende. &THORN;o &thorn;e luue&eth; woreld winne he la&eth;e&eth; &thorn;us que&eth;inde, <I>Qui non renu[n]ciauerit omnibus que p. non p. m. e. di.</I> No man ne mai fol&yogh;e me bute he forsake alle &thorn;e woreld winne &thorn;at he weld ahg. <I>Duobus</I> <MILESTONE N="145" UNIT="p"><I>autem modis renunciatur possessio. scilicet desinendo habere. et desinendo amare</I>. On two wise man mai forsake woreld winne. on is fersien hit fro him swo &thorn;at he it nabbe. o&eth;er is. lete swo litel &thorn;er of; &thorn;at he it noht ne luuie. hit is e&eth;eliche sinne &thorn;at man ahte welde. ac it is michel sinne; &thorn;at man ahte luuie. for &thorn;an no man ne mai luuien god and ehte. &THORN;o &thorn;e luuie&eth; here wil. and here lustes. and lehtres. la&eth;e&eth; ure drihten. &thorn;us que&eth;inde. <I>Si quis uult post me uenire et cetera.</I> Ech man &thorn;e wile cumen after me forsake him seluen. and bere his rode. and fol&yogh;e me. Hit is arfe&eth; to understonden bute me nime &thorn;e more &yogh;eme &thorn;er-to hwu man mai hine selue forsake. nime&eth; nu &yogh;eme &thorn;erto. and ich &yogh;iu wile seggen. bi godes fultume. <I>Duo sunt in homine. alterum per naturam conditum. Alterum per culpam illatum[.]</I> Two &thorn;ing ben in &thorn;e manne. on his &thorn;at clene and brehte and faire kinde &thorn;at god haue&eth; &thorn;er-on broht &thorn;ureh his smehnesse. &thorn;at o&eth;er is wilful|shipe. and lichamliche lustes. and li&eth;ere lahtres. &thorn;i ne mai no man gode fol&yogh;en ne to him cumen bute forsake. and forlete &thorn;e fule on-cume. &thorn;e &thorn;e ondfulle feond on him brohte. and hilede &thorn;at clene ichinde. and &thorn;er-on bilef &thorn;e ure drihten shop and bere his rode. <I>Tres igitur cruces sunt de quibus hic agitur. due mentis. et una corporis.</I> &THORN;re rodes ben &thorn;at ich nu of speke. two gostliche. and on lichamliche <I>Crux corporis est affliccio carnis. quando corpus membratum punitur.</I> &THORN;e lichamliche rode is &thorn;e pine &thorn;e man &thorn;ole&eth; &thorn;enne his lichame be&eth; tospred. and to-tiht on &thorn;e rode. alse ure helendes holi lichame wes. <MILESTONE N="146" UNIT="p">on &thorn;e holi rode. &thorn;o &thorn;e he &thorn;er-one &thorn;rowede alse his wille was. and hadde &thorn;ornene helm uppen his holi hafde. &thorn;e him swi&eth;e prikede. and on his honden irene nailes. and on his foten alse. and on his side was mid spere istungen. and his holi lichame to-sprad and to-tuht. and for ure gulten reuliche ato&yogh;en. Ac man mai fol&yogh;en gode and to him cumen. &thorn;eh his lichame swich pine ne &thorn;olie ne swo ne beo to-spred ne to-tuht on lichamliche rode. and 
<PB REF="00000235.tif" N="207"> &thorn;ere-fore ure drihten ne la&eth;e&eth; us noht to beren swiche rode. ac la&eth;e&eth; us to an o&eth;er. &thorn;e &thorn;is bitocne&eth; &thorn;at is cleped. <I>Carnis maceracio.</I> &THORN;at is lichames helsing<NOTE PLACE="foot">? read <I>hlensing</I>. Lambeth MS. has <I>lensing</I>.</NOTE>. Mannes lichame ihalsne&eth;<NOTE PLACE="foot">? read <I>ihlanse&eth;</I>. Lambeth MS. has <I>lense&eth;</I>.</NOTE> iwis. &thorn;enne me hine pined mid hunger. and mid &thorn;urste. and mid wecche. and mid swinche. and mid stiue wedes next &thorn;e liche and smerte smiten of smale longe &yogh;erden. and mid michele chele o&eth;er wile. &thorn;os roden moten beren alle sinfulle men. &thorn;e wile milce habben of here sinnes. &thorn;is rode is cleped on &thorn;e boc. <I>Scala peccatorum.</I> &thorn;at is sinfulle manne leddre. &thorn;e hi shulen one stien to heuene. Nu &yogh;ie hauen herd. wich is &thorn;e lichamliche rode. here&eth; nu wich is &thorn;e gostliche rode. hie haue&eth; twei names. <I>Cordis contricio et proximi compassio.</I> &THORN;at is herte sor for mannes o&yogh;ene sinne and reu&eth;e for his emcristenes wowe. &thorn;e man &thorn;e wile &thorn;is rode beren he mot cnowen &thorn;et he haue&eth; ofte and afele wise agilt mid his e&yogh;en bihelden &thorn;at he ne sholden. wile idel. wile unnut. wile ifel. and alse mid nose sneued. and mid eare list. and mid mu&eth;e agilt speken <MILESTONE N="147" UNIT="p">&thorn;at he ne sholde ofte. and afele wise. and forlete &thorn;o gode word. on his bede &thorn;e he speken sholde. and on ouerdede on ete. and on drinke &thorn;enne he ne sholde. and gif he &thorn;et &thorn;enche&eth;, and on his herte sore bimurne&eth;. &THORN;enne ake&eth; his heorte. and smerte&eth;. for his sinnes alse sholde his heued &yogh;if he hadde &thorn;er-uppe &thorn;ornene helm. and &thorn;e &thorn;ornes swi&eth;e prikeden. Eft-sone &yogh;if he &thorn;enke&eth; &thorn;at he haue&eth; agilt mid his honden ofte and a fele wise forlete almesdede. and don idel. and unut. and ifel. and mid his foten gon &thorn;enne he ne sholde. and &thorn;ider he ne sho[l]de. and seldere &thorn;ene he sholde to his chirche. and to o&eth;re holie stowen. and soriliche on his heorte bimurne&eth;. &thorn;enne ake&eth; &thorn;e heorte and smerte&eth; alse &thorn;e honden and te fet sholden &yogh;if hie mid irene nailen weren &thorn;urh stungen. Eft-sone &yogh;if he understant &thorn;at he habbe ofte agilt on golliche dedes. on untime. o&eth;er on unluuede stede. o&eth;er mid unluued loke. o&eth;er on unluued wise. and mistliche &thorn;oht ofte and a manifeld wise. and al &thorn;at sore bimurne&eth; on his heorte. &thorn;enne wile his heorte aken and smerten. alse his side sholde 
<PB REF="00000237.tif" N="209"> &yogh;if me him mid spere stunge. and &yogh;if man him seluen pine&eth; alse ich seid habbe. and &yogh;if he se&eth; his emcristene &thorn;olien wosi&eth;. and him &thorn;at on his heorte sore reuwe&eth;. and were&eth; his emcristene wi&eth; pine bi his mihte. he mai ben ure helendes cniht. for he bere&eth; his rode. Nime we &yogh;eme and bide we &thorn;at he us filste to forsakende us seluen. and &thorn;e fule on-cume &thorn;e ure fo on us brohte. and to beren ure rode. &thorn;at is ure lichames clensing and ure heorte reusinge. and swo after him cumen. and him fol&yogh;en. and mid him bileue. <I>Quod nobis prested qui uiuit et Regnat per omnia secula seculorum. amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="33" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXXIII. [SERMO IN PS. CXIX. 110.]</HEAD>
<P><I>Posuerunt peccatores laqueum michi et de mandatis tuis non</I><MILESTONE N="148" UNIT="p"><NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps.cxix.110.]</NOTE> <I>erraui</I>. &ETH;e sinfulle haue&eth; leid grune me to henten. and ich ne forlet &thorn;ine bode. Ure fo fare&eth; on hunte&eth;. and lei&eth; grune in a wilderne to henten &thorn;e deor &thorn;e wunie&eth; &thorn;er-inne. Ute we ber&yogh;en us. and bidden god &thorn;at he us filste and shilde &thorn;er-wi&eth; &thorn;at he us ne shrenche and seien mid &thorn;e prophete. <I>Custodi me &aacute; laqueo q. s. michi.</I> louerd shild me wi&eth; &thorn;at grune &thorn;at hie leid hauen me to henten. liste&eth; nu and ich &yogh;iu wile seggen. and under-nime&eth; hit on heorte. and habbe&eth; hit on minde &yogh;iu is ned michel. wi &thorn;e deuel is nemd sinful. and hunte. and &thorn;is woreld wilderne. and li&eth;ere lahtres grune. and &thorn;es men deor. &thorn;e deuel is cleped sinful for he &thorn;urh his oregel fulliche sine&yogh;ede. &thorn;o &thorn;e he sundrede him seluen fro gode. he is cleped mannes fo. for he fode &thorn;e forme man wi&eth; god. &thorn;at was adam. and al his ofspring. &thorn;at is al mankin. he is cleped hunte. for &thorn;an &thorn;e he waite&eth; ure ech. and cunne&eth; te bringen us on li&eth;ere lahtres. &thorn;e be&eth; his grunen. and &thorn;er-one hente&eth; us alse hunte driue&eth; deor to grune. o&eth;er to nette. and swo hente&eth;. and of &thorn;is hunte spec&eth; &thorn;e prophete. and sei&eth;. <I>Anima nostra sicut passer erepta de laqueo uenantium.</I> Ure soule is abroiden; of &thorn;e hunte grune. holi boc clepe&eth; &thorn;is woreld wildren for &thorn;e fewe men &thorn;e wunie&eth; [&eth;]erone &thorn;e ben temed. and wend to godes hond. his wille to don. ac alle mest hie be&eth; iwile&yogh;e&eth; and habbe&eth;<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS</I>. habbed.</NOTE> geres after wilde 
<PB REF="00000239.tif" N="211"> deore. and for is ech man efned to &thorn;e deore. &thorn;e he nime&eth; after geres. sum fox. sum wulf. sum bere. sum leun. and ech man me nemne&eth; after &thorn;an &thorn;e his geres beo&eth;. and alse &thorn;e michele deor hene&eth; &thorn;e little. and bi hem libbe&eth; on &thorn;e wilderne. Swo hene&eth;. and astru&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;e riche men &thorn;e wrecches. and na&eth;eles libbe&eth; bi hem on &thorn;is worelde. <I>In hoc deserto sunt iiii</I><SUP>or</SUP> <I>saltus quos bestie</I> <MILESTONE N="149" UNIT="p"><I>deserti frequentant scilicet corea ceruisia. forum monasterium.</I> on &thorn;is wilderne ben fu&yogh;er lages. &thorn;at mest alle wilde deor to seche&eth;. &thorn;at on is ple&yogh;e, &thorn;at oder<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> drinch. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde chep|inge. &thorn;e fer&eth;e chirche. <I>In primo saltu ponunt uenantes laqueum uanitatis. In secundo impietatis.</I> On &thorn;is fuwer la&yogh;es lei&eth; ure fo fuwer grunes us mide to henten. crist us shilde &thorn;erwi&eth; &yogh;if his wille beo. At ple&yogh;e he telde&eth; &thorn;e grune of idelnesse. for al hit is idel &thorn;at me at ple&yogh;e bihalt. and liste&eth;. and do&eth; and un|queme gode. and unbiheue &thorn;e soule. and swinch &thorn;e lichame. &thorn;ih. and shonkes. and fet oppie&eth;. wombe gosshie&eth;. and shuldres wrenchie&eth;. armes. and honden frikie&eth;. herte bi&eth;enche&eth; &thorn;at hie seggen shal on songe. Tunge and te&eth;. and lippe word shuppie&eth;. Mu&eth; sent ut &thorn;e stefne. and ech man &thorn;e &thorn;erto cume&eth; pleie to toten. o&eth;er to listen o&eth;er to bihelden. &yogh;if he him wel like&eth;. he be&eth; biseid and hent on &thorn;e on &thorn;e<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> grune of idelnesse. &thorn;e &thorn;e werse &thorn;ere haue&eth; itelded. of &thorn;is grune spec&eth; &thorn;e prophete and sei&eth;. <I>Non sedi cum concilio uanitatis et cum iniqua gerentibus non [introibo].</I> Ne held ich nefre wel mid hem &thorn;e gon to idelnesse. <I>Secundus saltus huius deserti est compotatorium.</I> &thorn;at o&eth;er la&yogh;e on &thorn;is wilderne is drinch. &thorn;ere telde&eth; &thorn;e werse &thorn;e grune of unrihte. for &thorn;ere ne do&eth; no man riht. ac ech man do&eth; &thorn;ere unriht to &yogh;enes gode and to &yogh;enes his a&yogh;ene soule. and to &yogh;enes his emcristene. To-&yogh;enes gode he do&eth; unriht. &thorn;at is his louerd. and halt his lif. and his hele. &thorn;e wile he hit haue&eth;. and do&eth; him al &thorn;at he bi be&eth;. and bid<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> him &thorn;erof beten his nede and bere&yogh;en him wi&eth; ouer dede and na&eth;eles ne wile don &thorn;at god him het. ac do&eth; &thorn;at god forbed. and do&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e deuel het, and swo unwur&eth;e&eth; god. and wur&eth;e&eth; &thorn;ene deuel. and agilt wi&eth; gode. and queme&eth; &thorn;e deuel. and forgilt heuene wele. and haue&eth; helle wowe. unriht he do&eth; ec to-&yogh;enes his soule unwille. and awlenc&eth; 
<PB REF="00000241.tif" N="213"> his lichame. <MILESTONE N="150" UNIT="p">and walt his soule. and hefie&eth; his lichame. and hene&eth; his soule. and &thorn;e lichame &thorn;e sholde ben &thorn;e soule hiht|liche bure. make&eth; hire to ateliche quarterne. and &thorn;er inne neure twiste&eth;. mid ouerdede. and untimliche drinche. &thorn;at hire beo&eth; wo &thorn;at hie sal &thorn;er-inne wunien. and &thorn;ere-fore wilne&eth; ut. Unriht heo do&eth; ec to&yogh;enes his emcristene. &thorn;enne he hine la&eth;e&eth; to drinken more. noht &thorn;e him beo wille. o&eth;er queme. ac &thorn;enne him ned were. and bringe&eth; uppen him birden more &thorn;ene [he] bere mu&yogh;e. and spille&eth; on him &thorn;at he sholde spelien wrecche men. o&eth;er ra&eth;er helden hit ut &thorn;ene men &thorn;ermide fordrenchen. and noht sheden<NOTE PLACE="marg">? shenden.</NOTE> godes shafte ne spenen on uni&eth;or. &thorn;at god shop mannen to helpe. ne swo unwur&eth;in godes handiwerc. &thorn;is beo&eth; at drinche and o&eth;er unriht inoh. &thorn;ere be&eth; ollende word. and idele lehtres. and winrede bruwes. and buwe&eth; wenliche. &thorn;e be&eth; bispeke ewe|bruche and o&eth;er unriht inoh. wicching. and swikedom. stale. and leo&eth;. and lesing. and refloc. and alle &thorn;e lu&eth;ere lastes &thorn;e man hafe&eth; &thorn;ureh deules lore. of &thorn;is grisliche grune spec&eth; &thorn;e pro|phete. and sei&eth;. <I>Cum iniqua gerentibus non introibo.</I> Nelle ich nefre gon &thorn;ider in; &thorn;ere me swich unriht drige&eth;. &thorn;e lif holi man &thorn;e wiste godes wille. swic drinch wi&eth; que&eth;. and &thorn;e lu&eth;ere wune. and &thorn;e stede &thorn;er me swo one drinke&eth;. <I>Tercius saltus huius deserti est. forum ubi ponunt laqueum malignitatis.</I> &THORN;e &thorn;ridde lage on &thorn;is wilderne is cheping. &thorn;ere telde&eth; &thorn;e werse &thorn;e grune of hindre &thorn;at is of bipeching for &thorn;enne man bipeche&eth; o&eth;er. he him make&eth; to ben bihinden. of &thorn;at he wene&eth; to ben biforen. &thorn;at is ure alre wune &thorn;e bigge&eth;. and sille&eth;. &thorn;e sullere loue&eth; his &thorn;ing dere. <MILESTONE N="151" UNIT="p">and sei&eth; &thorn;at it is wel wur&eth;. o&eth;er betere. &ETH;e beger bet litel &thorn;ar fore and sei&eth; &thorn;at hit nis noht wur&eth;. and lige&eth; bo&eth;e. &thorn;e sullere lat sumdel of his lofe. and swere&eth; &thorn;at he hit nele lasse selle. &thorn;e beggere ecne&eth; his bode and swere&eth; &thorn;at he nele more geuen. &thorn;anne cume&eth; &thorn;e werse and rune&eth; wi&eth; here ei&eth;eres &thorn;anc. and do&eth; &thorn;e sullere lasse to nimende<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> gen|ende.</NOTE> &thorn;anne he swore. and &thorn;anne &thorn;e biggere more to geuende &thorn;anne he swore. And gif hit chepinge be. &thorn;e me shule meten o&eth;er weien. &thorn;e sullere do&eth; narewere &thorn;ane he sholde. and te biggere rumluker &thorn;an he sholde. and &thorn;esse wise biswike&eth; her ai&eth;er o&eth;er. and be&eth; &thorn;anne bisaid in &thorn;e grune of 
<PB REF="00000243.tif" N="215"> hinder. On is leasing. o&eth;er is mon-o&eth;. &thorn;e &thorn;ridde swikedom. and mid &thorn;is grune hente&eth; &thorn;e werse alle &thorn;o &thorn;e sus<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS.;</I>? &thorn;us.</NOTE> bigge&eth;. and sulle&eth;.<NOTE PLACE="marg">[Ps. xxv. 5.]</NOTE> &thorn;are fore sei&eth; &thorn;e prophete. <I>Odiui ecclesiam malignantium.</I> Me is andsete &thorn;e samninge of &thorn;e hinderfulle for ich wot &thorn;at &thorn;at<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>So in MS.;</I>? &thorn;us.</NOTE> hie ben lo&eth;e god. <I>Quartus saltus huius deserti est monasterium ubi ponuntur laquei impietatis.</I> &ETH;e feor&eth;[e] lage of &thorn;isse wilderne is chireche. &thorn;are telde&eth; &eth;e werse &thorn;e grune of oregelnesse. and bisai&eth; &thorn;ar-one hwile hodede. and hwile lewede. and hwile bo&eth;e. &ETH;e hodede hente&eth; mid &thorn;is grune. hwile ofeald. hwile twifeald &thorn;anne he make&eth; &thorn;at &thorn;e hodede lat his chireche stonde wi&eth;-uten tide. &thorn;ane hit time be&eth; to done &thorn;e tiden. and alse swo ofte swo he speke&eth; in chireche &thorn;at he ne sholde. o&eth;er swike&eth; of &thorn;at he sholde. &thorn;at is &thorn;e sinfule wel tachen. and minigen &thorn;o &thorn;e ben slowe to chireche. and to weldede. &thorn;at he be snel &thorn;ar-to. and lehtrie<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> &thorn;o &thorn;e on sinne li&eth;. to forleten. <MILESTONE N="152" UNIT="p">and mid milde worde to frefrien. and eche he&yogh;e dai fede mid godes worde &thorn;e hungrie soule &thorn;e haue&eth; to witen. and alse fele &thorn;ing swo ich iteld habbe &thorn;at he ine chirche speken sholde. &yogh;if he nele o&eth;er ne can. o&eth;er ne recche&eth; mid alse fele folde grunen &thorn;e werse hine bisei&eth;. and hente&eth;. and &yogh;if he wlite&eth; mid stefne for to liken wimmannen. o&eth;er lede&eth; hem his life<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> e&yogh;en for to sechen hire loke. &thorn;enne be&eth; he laht forto leden to helle. &thorn;e lewede men hente&eth; &thorn;e werse ine chirche mid his grune on &thorn;re wise. &thorn;anne prest spec&eth; inne chirche of chirche neode and mine&yogh;e&eth; &thorn;at me niwe clo&eth;es o&eth;er elde bete. boc o&eth;er belle calch o&eth;er messe-ref. o&eth;er waferiht<NOTE PLACE="foot">? <I>Waferiht</I> = <I>wafe-rift</I> = <I>weafed-rift.</I></NOTE> o&eth;er o&eth;re clo&eth;es. &thorn;enne cume&eth; &thorn;e werse to &thorn;e mannes heorte. and wi&eth; his &thorn;onc sunderune halt &thorn;us que&eth;inde. wi sholdest &thorn;u &thorn;is finden &thorn;e noht ne fost &thorn;erof. ac he foh&eth; al &thorn;at &thorn;ere cume&eth;. he finde &thorn;is nu. Swo ne andswerede noht moyses ure drihten &thorn;o he bad him minster maken. and be hit al wel for&eth;ede. &thorn;eh he noht &thorn;er-offe fenge. alse dide sale|man &thorn;e god sende his writ to. swo hoh ech chirche socne don &thorn;enne hie nede sen. &thorn;enne &thorn;e prest &thorn;e mene&yogh;e&eth; rihtliche te&eth;ien. &thorn;enne cume&eth; &thorn;e werse to sume mannes heorte. and mine&yogh;e&eth; hine &thorn;at he swo ne do. and rune&eth; wi&eth; &thorn;e mannes &thorn;onc and &thorn;us him misrede&eth;. &yogh;if &thorn;u &thorn;e prest bitechest alle &thorn;ine te&eth;inge. nele he hit 
<PB REF="00000245.tif" N="217"> delen alse he don sholde. ac wile hit dere sellen and spenen on uni&eth;or. do &thorn;u almes &thorn;er-of. and del sum wrecche men. &thorn;us he hine bi-peche&eth; &thorn;at he chirche bireue&eth;. on &thorn;e helde la&yogh;e het ure drihten &thorn;at me ne sholde none man bitechen <MILESTONE N="153" UNIT="p">bute he were teid to menden chirche. <I>Vndecim generationes iusse sunt a domino solis leuitis decimas soluere.</I> &THORN;anne heh dai cume&eth; man hoh herien god mid rihte leue. and mid so&eth;e luue. and of &thorn;an &thorn;e god him haue&eth; lend. loc to chirche bringen. and wur&eth;in &thorn;er-mide godes bord; alse his haue be&eth;. &thorn;enne cume&eth; &thorn;e werse to sumes mannes heorte and rune&eth; wi&eth; his heorte. and do&eth; hine his loc to wi&eth; teonde. and &thorn;us que&eth; &thorn;is chirche is riche inoh. and fele men ben wrecches &thorn;e nes riche non nod. ac wrecches habben michele. wi&eth;-teo nu [h]ere &thorn;i loc and del hit wrecches. <I>Set ait in ewangelio. hec oportuit facere; et illa non omittere.</I> ei&eth;er bihoue&eth; &thorn;at man do &thorn;e wile loc to chirche bringe. and helpe wrecche me[n]. and &thorn;er-mide hine alese&eth; &yogh;if he laht be&eth;. on &thorn;e orelese grune. &thorn;enne mai he seggen mid te salm wirhte dauid. <I>Oculi mei semper ad dominum et cetera.</I> Eure beo mine e&yogh;ene opene to ure drihten. for ich triste &thorn;at he nele neng bi mine wrihte. ac for his milde wille. of &thorn;is werses grune mine fet breiden. swo do he ure alre &thorn;e liue&eth; and rixle&eth; <I>Amen.</I></P>
</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="34" TYPE="homily">
<HEAD>XXXIV. [SERMO IN ISA. XI. I.]</HEAD>
<P><I>[E]gredietur uirga de radice iesse, et cetera.</I> An gerd sal spruten of iesse more. and an blosme stien of &thorn;are more. and uppe &thorn;are blosme resten &thorn;e holie gost. On &thorn;esse fewe litele wored lotied<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> fele gode wored gif hie weren wel ioponen<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>. Ac ich ne mai ne ich ne can &thorn;osse on openi. Ac na&thorn;eles ich wille ew segge &thorn;at ich &thorn;ronne understonde &thorn;ur[h] &thorn;e mihte of &thorn;e holi gost. <I>Egredietur. et cetera.</I> &ETH;o &thorn;e heue[n]liche fader fundede to 
<PB REF="00000247.tif" N="219"> senden &thorn;ene heuenliche sune; he sende mani herendrake to cu&thorn;en &thorn;at he cume wolde And on of &thorn;o was ysaie &thorn;e prophete. on was leid to segen &thorn;os wored &thorn;at ich nou sege. and nu &thorn;e beginne on opini. &thorn;e was man wuniinde on &thorn;ese worlde mani hundred wintre are &thorn;e maiden ware iken<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>. o&thorn;er istren<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>. and spac of hire and seide wat of hire iwur&thorn;en solde also suteliche swo it wur&thorn;e were. and heuenede hire cun to more. and hire su[l]f to gerde. and hire cunebern to blosme. and seide. <I>Egredietur uirga et cetera.</I> Hered<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> nu and understonded<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> for woche &thorn;inge he nemnede hire cun to more. and hire su[l]f to gerde and hire cune bern to blosme. <I>Quem ad modum rami arboris prodeunt a stipite. et ille a radice. sic domina nostra de posteris iesse et ipsi prodierunt de ipso iesse.</I> Alse &thorn;e huuemeste bou of &thorn;e treuwe springed<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> of &thorn;e ne&thorn;emeste rote. alse sprong ure lafedi of hire helderne. and hire helderne of iesse. and alse &thorn;e uuemeste bou is sib &thorn;e ne&thorn;emeste rote. Alse sprond word<NOTE PLACE="foot">? Alse sprong [man of his elderne and] wor&eth;, &amp;c.</NOTE> &thorn;e laste man isib &thorn;e forme <MILESTONE N="157" UNIT="p">ste &thorn;e was biforn us. And for &thorn;i bed<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> alle man ibro&thorn;ren and isustren. and solden auerihc man loueien o&thorn;er. Acke nu is rewe&thorn;e. for nu is euerihc man ifo &thorn;are he solde fren<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> be. <I>Nun|quam tuta fide et cetera. Filius autem diem. et cetera. Domina nostra comparata est uirge propter .iiii</I><SUP>or</SUP><I>. que sepe inueniuntur adiuncta uirge que est recta. plana. excisis longa</I>. Vre leuedi is iuened<NOTE PLACE="foot">The MS. originally had 'the leuedi iseuedidin is iuened.'</NOTE> to gerde for foure &thorn;inges &thorn;e man find<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> ilome on gerde &thorn;at he be riht and smal and long. and sme&thorn;e. <I>Rectitudinem uirge habuit in perseueranciam uite</I>. Gerde rihtnesse he heuede on hire liflode. for he ne turnde naht on hire to doinde ne que&thorn;ende nan &thorn;er &thorn;inge &thorn;e he leten solde. <I>et Sic medio tutissima ibat</I>. And he understod holie boc lore. et cetera. <I>Si plus scirem, plus dicerem</I>.
</P>

</DIV2>
<DIV2 N="35" TYPE="homily"><PB REF="00000248.tif" N="220">
<HEAD>XXXV. A MORAL ODE.<NOTE PLACE="foot">For a translation of this poem, See Old Eng. Hom. First Series, p. 158.</NOTE></HEAD>
<LG TYPE="stanza">
<L>Ich am nu elder &thorn;an ich was a wintre and a lore.</L>
<L>Ich wealde more &thorn;an idude mi wit oh to be more</L>
<L>To longe ich habbe child iben a worde and a dade.</L>
<L N="4">&THORN;eih ibie a winter eald to jung ich am on rade.</L>
<L>Vnnet lif ich habbe ilad. and &yogh;iet me &thorn;inche&eth; ilade.</L>
<L>&THORN;an ibi&eth;enche me &thorn;ar on wel sore ime adrade.</L>
<L>Mast al ich habbe idon &iacute;s idelnesse and chilce.</L>
<L N="8">Wel late ich habbe me bi&thorn;oht bute me god do milce.</L>
<L>Fele idel word ich habbe ispeken se&eth;en ich speken cu&eth;e.</L>
<L>And fele &yogh;eunge dade idon &thorn;e me of&eth;inke&eth; nu&eth;e.</L>
<L>Alto lome ich habbe igult a werke and a worde.</L>
<L N="12">Alto muchel ic habbe ispend to litel ileid on horde.</L>
<L>Mast al &thorn;at me likede ar nu hit me mislica&eth;.</L>
<L>&THORN;e muchel fol&yogh;e&eth; his iwil him selfen he biswica&eth;.</L>
<L>Ich mihte habben bet idon. hadde ich &thorn;o isel&eth;e.</L>
<L N="16">Nu ich wolde ac ine mai for elde and for unhal&eth;e</L>
<L>Elde me is bistolen on ar ich hit iwiste.</L>
<L>Ne mai ich isien bifore me for smeche ne for miste</L>
<L>Ar&yogh;e we be&eth; to don god to juel al to &thorn;riste</L>
<L N="20">More eie stonde&eth; man of man &thorn;an him do of criste.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wel ne de&eth; &thorn;e hwile he mai wel ofte hit sal him rewen.</L>
<L>&THORN;an alle men sulle ripen &thorn;at hie ar sewen.</L>
<L>Do al to gode &thorn;at he mu&yogh;e ech &thorn;e hwile he be&eth; aliue.</L>
<L N="24">Nu lipne noman to muchel to childe ne to wiue.</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;e him selfe for&yogh;eit for wiue o&eth;er for childe</L>
<L>He sal cumen on euel stede bute him god be milde.</L>
<L>Sende god biforen him man &thorn;e hwile he mai to heuene.</L>
<L N="28">For betre is on almesse biforen &thorn;an ben after seuene.
<PB REF="00000249.tif" N="221"></L>
<L>Ne bie &thorn;e leuere &thorn;an &thorn;e self ne &thorn;i m&aelig;i ne &thorn;i mowe</L>
<L>Sot is &thorn;e is o&eth;er mannes frend betere &thorn;an his owen.</L>
<L>Ne hopie wif to hire were ne were to his wiue</L>
<L N="32">Be for him self afric man &thorn;e hwile he be&eth; aliue.</L>
<L>Wis &thorn;e him selue bi&eth;enche&eth; &thorn;e hwile he m&oacute;t libben</L>
<L>For sone wille&eth; him for&yogh;iete &thorn;e fremde and &thorn;e sibbe.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wel ne do&eth; &thorn;e hwile he mai ne sal he &thorn;an he wolde.</L>
<L N="36">For mani mannes sore iswinc habbe&eth; ofte unholde.</L>
<L>Ne solde noman don a furst ne laten wel to done</L>
<L>For mani man bihote&eth; wel &thorn;at hi for&yogh;iete&eth; sone.</L>
<L>&THORN;e man &thorn;e wile siker ben to habben godes blisse.</L>
<L N="40">Do wel him self &thorn;e hwile he mai &thorn;anne haue&eth; hes mid iwisse.</L>
<L>&THORN;e riche men wene&eth; siker ben &thorn;urch wallen and thurh dichen.</L>
<L>He de&eth; his aihte an siker stede &thorn;e hit sent to heueriche.</L>
<L>For &thorn;arf he ben of-drad of fure ne of &thorn;ieue.</L>
<L N="44">&THORN;ar ne mai hit him binime &thorn;e lo&eth;e ne &thorn;e lieue.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar ne &thorn;arf he habben care of here ne of &yogh;ielde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ider we sende&eth; and ec bere&eth; to litel and to selde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ider we solden drawen and don wel ofte and ilome.</L>
<L N="48">For &thorn;ar ne sal me us naht binime mid wrongwise dome.</L>
<L>&THORN;ider we solde &yogh;ierne drawen wolde &yogh;ie me ileuen.</L>
<L>For ne mai hit us binime no king ne no syrreue.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at beste &thorn;at we habbe&eth; her &thorn;ider we solde sende.</L>
<L N="52">For &thorn;ar we mihte finden eft. and habben abuten ende.</L>
<L>Se &thorn;e her do&eth; ani god forto haben godes ore</L>
<L>Al he hit sal eft finde &thorn;ar and hundredfealde more.</L>
<L>Se &thorn;e aihte wile holde wel &thorn;e hwile hes mu&yogh;e wealden.</L>
<L N="56">&YOGH;ieue hes for godes luue &thorn;anne do&eth; hes wel ihealden.</L>
<L>For ure swinch and ure til&eth;e is ofte wuned to swinde</L>
<L>Ac al &thorn;at we &yogh;ieue&eth; for godes luue al we hit sulen eft finden.</L>
<L>Ne sal &thorn;ar non euel ben unboht ne god unfor&yogh;olden.</L>
<L N="60">Euel we do&eth; al to muchel and god lasse &thorn;an we solden.
<PB REF="00000250.tif" N="222"></L>
<L>Se &thorn;e mast do&eth; nu to gode and se last to lothe.</L>
<L>Ei&eth;er to litel and to muchel hem sal &thorn;unche bo&eth;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar me sal ure werkes wei&yogh;en bifore &thorn;an heuen kinge</L>
<L N="64">And &yogh;ieuen us ure werkes lean after ure erninge.</L>
<L>Africh man mid &thorn;at he haue&eth; mai bugge heueriche</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;e more haue&eth; and &thorn;e &thorn;e lasse bo&eth;e iliche.</L>
<L>Alse on mid his peni se o&eth;er mid his punde.</L>
<L N="68">&THORN;is is &thorn;et wunderlukeste ware &thorn;at ani man funde.</L>
<L>And se &thorn;e more ne mai don mid his gode i&thorn;anke.</L>
<L>Alse wel se &thorn;e &thorn;e haued<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> goldes fele manke.</L>
<L>And ofte god can more &thorn;anc &thorn;an &thorn;e him &yogh;ieue&eth; lasse.</L>
<L N="72">Al his werkes and his weies is milce and rihtwi[s]nesse.</L>
<L>Litel l&oacute;c is gode lef &thorn;e cume&eth; of gode wille.</L>
<L>And e&eth;late muchel &yogh;ieue &thorn;an his herte is ille.</L>
<L>Heuene and er&eth;e he ouer sih&eth; his eien be&eth; ful brihte.</L>
<L N="76">Nis him no &thorn;ing forholen swo muchel is his mihte</L>
<L>Ne bie hit no swo derne idon ne on swo &thorn;uster nihte.</L>
<L>He wot hwat &thorn;enche&eth; and hwat do&eth; alle quike wihte</L>
<L>Nis louerd swilch is crist ne king swilch ure drihte.</L>
<L N="80">Bo&eth;e &yogh;ieme&eth; &thorn;e his bien bi daie and bi nihte.</L>
<L>Heuene and er&eth;e and al &thorn;at is biloken is in his honden</L>
<L>He do&eth; al &thorn;at his wille is awatere and alonde</L>
<L>He make&eth; &thorn;e fisses in &thorn;e sa &thorn;e fueles on &thorn;e lofte.</L>
<L N="84">He wit and wealde&eth; alle &thorn;ing and he sop alle safte.</L>
<L>He is ord abuten ord and ende abuten ende.</L>
<L>He is one afre on eche stede wende &thorn;ar &thorn;u wende.</L>
<L>He is buuen us and bine&eth;en biforen and bihinde</L>
<L N="88">&THORN;e godes wille do&eth; aihware he mai&yogh; him finde</L>
<L>Elche rune he here&eth; and he wot alle dade</L>
<L>He &thorn;urh sih&eth; elches mannes &thorn;anc wi hwat sal us to rade.</L>
<L>We &thorn;e breke&eth; godes has and gulte&eth; swo ilome</L>
<L N="92">Hwat sulle we seggen o&eth;er don ate muchele dome</L>
<L>We &thorn;e luueden unriht and euel lif ladden.</L>
<L>Hwat sulle we seggen o&eth;er don &thorn;ar &aelig;ngles be&eth; ofdradde.</L>
<L>Hwat sulle we beren us biforen mid hwan sulle we iqueme</L>
<L N="96">We &thorn;e nafre god ne duden &thorn;an heuenliche deme.
<PB REF="00000251.tif" N="223"></L>
<L>&THORN;ar sulle ben deflen swo fele &thorn;at wille&eth; us forwreien.</L>
<L>Nabbe&eth; hie no &thorn;ing for&yogh;ieten of &thorn;at hie her iseien.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at hie iseien her hie wille&eth; cu&eth;en &thorn;are</L>
<L N="100">Bute we haben hit ibet &thorn;e hwile we here waren.</L>
<L>Al hie habbe&eth; on here write &thorn;at we misduden here.</L>
<L>&THORN;eih we hes ne niseien hie waren ure iferen.</L>
<L>Hwat sullen horlinges don &thorn;es wichen and &thorn;e forsworene</L>
<L N="104">Wi swo fele be&eth; icleped swo fewe be&eth; icorene</L>
<L>Wi hwi waren hie bi&yogh;iete to hwan waren hie iborene.</L>
<L>&THORN;e sulle ben to dea&eth;e idemd and afremo forlorene</L>
<L>Elch man sal &thorn;ar biclepien himselfen and ec demen.</L>
<L N="108">Hic<NOTE PLACE="marg">?=His.</NOTE> o&yogh;en werc and his &thorn;anc to witnesse he sal temen.</L>
<L>Ne mai him noman alse wel demen ne alse rihte</L>
<L>For non ne cnowe&eth; hine alse wel buten one drihte.</L>
<L>Man wot him self best his werkes and his wille.</L>
<L N="112">Se &thorn;e last wot he sei&eth; ofte mast se &thorn;it al wot is stille</L>
<L>Nis no witnesse alse muchel se mannes o&yogh;en hierte</L>
<L>Hwo se sei&eth; &thorn;at hie be&eth; hol him self wot his smierte.</L>
<L>Elch man sal him selfen demen to dea&eth;e o&eth;er to liue.</L>
<L N="116">&THORN;e witnesse of his o&yogh;en werc to o&eth;er &thorn;an hine sal driue.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at afri man haue&eth; idon se&eth;en he cam to manne</L>
<L>Swo he hit iseie ab&oacute;c iwrite he sal hit &thorn;enche &thorn;anne</L>
<L>Ac drihte ne deme&eth; noman after his biginninge</L>
<L N="120">Ac al his lif sal ben teald after his endinge</L>
<L>&YOGH;ief &thorn;e endinge is god al hit is god. and euel &yogh;ief euel is &thorn;e ende.</L>
<L>God &yogh;ieue &thorn;at ure ende be god and &yogh;ieue &thorn;at he us lende.</L>
<L>Se man &thorn;e nafre nele don god ne nafre god lif lade.</L>
<L N="124">Are dea&eth; and dom cume&eth; to his dure he mai&yogh; him sore adrade.</L>
<L>&THORN;at he ne mu&yogh;e &thorn;anne bidden ore for &thorn;at itit ilome</L>
<L>For &thorn;i he [is] wis &thorn;e bit and bi&yogh;iet and bet bifore dome</L>
<L>&THORN;anne &thorn;e dea&eth; is ate dure wel late he bidde&eth; ore</L>
<L N="128">Wel late he late&eth; euel werc &thorn;an he hit ne mai don no more.
<PB REF="00000252.tif" N="224"></L>
<L>Senne lat &thorn;e and &thorn;u nah him &thorn;an &thorn;u hit ne miht do no more;</L>
<L>For-&thorn;i he is sot &thorn;e swo abit to habben godes ore.</L>
<L>&THORN;eih hwe&eth;ere we hit leue&eth; wel for drihte self hit sade.</L>
<L N="132">Elche time sal &thorn;e man of-&thorn;unche his misdade</L>
<L>O&eth;er ra&eth;er o&eth;er later milce he sal imete.</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;e &thorn;e her naue&eth; ibet muchel he haued to bete</L>
<L>Mani man sei&eth; hwo reche pine &thorn;e sal habben ende</L>
<L N="136">Ne bidde ich not bet bie ich alesed a domesdai of bende.</L>
<L>Litel wot he hwat is pine and litel he cnowe&eth;</L>
<L>Hwilch hit is &thorn;ar sowle wunie&eth; hwu biter wind &thorn;ar blowe&eth;.</L>
<L>Hadde he ben &thorn;ar on o&eth;er two bare tiden.</L>
<L N="140">Nolde he for almidden eard &thorn;e &thorn;ridde &thorn;ar abiden.</L>
<L>&THORN;at habbe&eth; isaid &thorn;e come &thorn;anne &thorn;it wiste mid iwisse.</L>
<L>Wo wur&eth;e sore&yogh;e seue &yogh;ier for seue nihte blisse.</L>
<L>And ure blisse &thorn;e ende haue&eth; for ende-lease pine</L>
<L N="144">Betere is wori water &thorn;an atter imengd mid wine.</L>
<L>Swines brade is wel swete swo is of wilde diere.</L>
<L>Ac al to diere he hit abui&eth; &thorn;e &yogh;ief&eth; &thorn;ar-fore his swiere.</L>
<L>Ful wombe mai lihtliche speken of hunger and of fasten</L>
<L N="148">Swo mai of pine &thorn;e not hwat is pine &thorn;e sal ilasten.</L>
<L>Hadde [he] fonded sume stunde he wolde seggen o&eth;er</L>
<L>E&eth;late him ware wif and child suster and fader and bro&eth;er.</L>
<L>Al he wolde o&eth;erluker don and o&eth;erluker &thorn;enche</L>
<L N="152">&THORN;an he bi&eth;ohte an helle fur &thorn;at nowiht ne mai quenche</L>
<L>Afre he wolde her in wo and in wane wunien</L>
<L>Wi&eth; &thorn;an he mihte helle fur biflen and bisunien.</L>
<L>E&eth;late him ware al wele and er&eth;eliche blisse</L>
<L N="156">For to &thorn;e muchele blisse cume &thorn;is murie<NOTE PLACE="foot">See Old Eng. Homilies, First Series, p. 169, l. 154.</NOTE> mid iwisse.</L>
<L>&para; Ich wulle nu cumen eft to &thorn;e dome ich eow ar of sade.</L>
<L>On &thorn;e daie and on &thorn;e dome us helpe crist and rade.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar we mu&yogh;en ben sore offerd and harde us ofdrade.
<PB REF="00000253.tif" N="225"></L>
<L N="160">&THORN;ar elch sal al isien him biforen his word and ec his dade.</L>
<L>Al sal &thorn;ar ben &thorn;anne cu&eth; &thorn;at men lu&yogh;en her and halen.</L>
<L>Al sal &thorn;ar ben &thorn;anne unwrien &thorn;at men her hudden and stalen.</L>
<L>We sullen alre manne lif icnowen alse ure o&yogh;en</L>
<L N="164">&THORN;ar sullen efninges ben to &thorn;e heie and to &thorn;e lo&yogh;e.</L>
<L>Ne sal &thorn;eih no man samie &thorn;iar ne &thorn;arf he him adrade.</L>
<L>&YOGH;ief him her of&thorn;inche&eth; his gult and bet his misdade.</L>
<L>For hem ne same&eth; ne ne grame&eth; &thorn;e sulle ben ibore&yogh;e</L>
<L N="168">Ac &thorn;o&eth;re habbe&eth; same and grame and o&eth;er fele sore&yogh;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;e dom &thorn;al<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> sal.</NOTE> ben sone idon ne last hit nowiht longe</L>
<L>Ne sal him noman mene &thorn;ar of strenc&eth;e ne of wronge</L>
<L>&THORN;o sulle habben hardne dom &thorn;e here waren hardde</L>
<L N="172">&THORN;o &thorn;e euel hielden wreche men and euel la&yogh;e arerde.</L>
<L>Elch after &thorn;at he haue&eth; idon sal &thorn;ar ben &thorn;anne idemd</L>
<L>Bli&eth;e mai he &thorn;anne ben &thorn;e god haue&eth; wel iquemd.</L>
<L>Alle &thorn;o &thorn;e sprunge be&eth; of adam and of eue</L>
<L N="176">Alle hie sulle &thorn;ider cume for so&eth;e we hit ileued.<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE></L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e habbe&eth; wel idon after here mihte</L>
<L>To heueriche hie sulle fare for&eth; mid ure drihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e deueles werkes habe&eth; idon and &thorn;arinne be&eth; ifunde</L>
<L N="180">Hie sulle fare for&eth; mid hem into helle grunde.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar hie sulle wunien abuten ore and ende.</L>
<L>Brec&eth; nafre eft crist helle dure for lesen hem of bende</L>
<L>Nis no sellich &thorn;eih hem be wo and &thorn;eih hem be unea&eth;e</L>
<L N="184">Ne sal nafre eft crist &thorn;olien dea&eth; for lesen hem of dea&eth;e.</L>
<L>&AElig;nes drihten helle brac his frend he ut brohte</L>
<L>Him self he &thorn;olede dea&eth; for hem wel diere he hes bohte.</L>
<L>Nolde hit mo&yogh;e don for mai ne suster [for] bro&eth;er</L>
<L N="188">Nolde sune don for fader ne no man for o&eth;er.</L>
<L>Vre alre louerd for his &thorn;ralles ipined he was arode</L>
<L>Ure bendes he unbond and bohte us mid his blode.</L>
<L>We &yogh;ieue&eth; unea&eth;e for his luue a steche of ure breade</L>
<L N="192">Ne &thorn;enche we naht &thorn;ar &thorn;at sal deme &thorn;e quica<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> and &thorn;e deade.
<PB REF="00000254.tif" N="226"></L>
<L>Muchel luue he us kedde wolde we hit understonde.</L>
<L>&THORN;at ure elderne misduden we habe&eth; euel an honde.</L>
<L>Dea&eth; cam in &thorn;is midden&aelig;rd &thorn;urh ealde deueles onde</L>
<L N="196">And senne and sore&yogh;e and iswinch awatere and [a] londe.</L>
<L>Vre foremes faderes gult we abuge&eth; alle</L>
<L>Al his ofsprung after him in harem is biualle</L>
<L>&THORN;urst and hunger. chele and hete and alle unhal&eth;e</L>
<L N="200">&THORN;urh dea&eth; cam in &thorn;is middeneard and o&eth;er unisal&eth;e.</L>
<L>Nare noman elles dead ne sic ne [non] unsele</L>
<L>Ac mihte libbe afremo ablisse and an hale.</L>
<L>Litel lac is gode lief &thorn;e cume&eth; of gode wille</L>
<L N="204">And e&eth;late muchel &yogh;ieue &thorn;an his herte is ille</L>
<L>Litel hit &thorn;unche&eth; maniman ac muchel was &thorn;e senne</L>
<L>For hwan alle &thorn;olie&eth; dea&eth; &thorn;e comen of here kenne</L>
<L>Here senne and ec ure o&yogh;en us mu&yogh;e sore of&thorn;unche</L>
<L N="208">For senne we libe&eth; alle her in sore&yogh;e and in swunche.</L>
<L>Se&eth;en god nam swo mukel wrache for one misdede</L>
<L>We &thorn;e swo ofte misdo&eth; we mu&yogh;en us ea&eth;e ofdrade.</L>
<L>Adam and al his ofspreng for one bare senne.</L>
<L N="212">Was fele hundred wintre an helle a pine and unwenne<NOTE PLACE="foot"><I>Read</I> helle pine and an unwenne.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e lade&eth; here lif mid unrihte and mid wronge</L>
<L>Bute hit godes milce do hie sulle wunie &thorn;ar longe.</L>
<L>Godes wisdom is wel muchel<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> mulchel.</NOTE> and alsse is his mihte</L>
<L N="216">Ac nis his mihte nowiht lasse ac bi&eth;er ilke wihte.</L>
<L>More he one mai&yogh; for&yogh;ieue &thorn;an alle folc gulte cunne</L>
<L>Self deuel mihte habben milce &yogh;ief he hit bigunne.</L>
<L>&THORN;e&thorn;e godes milche sec&eth; iwis he mai hes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Egerton MS.</I> is; <I>Lambert MS.</I> ha.</NOTE> finden</L>
<L N="220">Ac helle king is ore-leas wi&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e he mai binden.</L>
<L>Se de&eth; his wille mast he sal habbe werest mede</L>
<L>His ba&eth; sal be wallinde pich his bed barnende glede.</L>
<L>Werse he do&eth; his gode wines &thorn;an his fiendes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Egerton</I> feonde.</NOTE></L>
<L N="224">God silde alle godes friend wi&eth; swo euele friende.</L>
<L>Nafre an helle ine cam ne cumen ich &thorn;ar ne reche</L>
<L>&THORN;eih ich aches woreldes wele &thorn;are mihte feche.
<PB REF="00000255.tif" N="227"></L>
<L>&THORN;eih ich wille seggen eow &thorn;at wise men us saden</L>
<L N="228">And [a] boc hit is write &thorn;ar me hit mai rade.</L>
<L>Ic wille seggen hit &thorn;o &thorn;e hit hem self nesten</L>
<L>And warnin hem wi&eth; here unfreme &yogh;ief hie me wille&eth; hlesten.</L>
<L>Vnderstonde&eth; nu to meward eadi men and arme</L>
<L N="232">Ich wille tellen eow of helle pine and warnin eow wi&eth; harme.</L>
<L>An helle hunger and &thorn;urst euel two iferen.</L>
<L>&THORN;os pine &thorn;olie&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e ware meteni&eth;inges here.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar is woning and wop after ache strate</L>
<L N="236">Hie fare&eth; fram hate [to] chele fram chele to hate.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]an hie be&eth; in &thorn;e hate chele hem &thorn;unche&eth; blisse</L>
<L>[&THORN;]an hie cume&eth; eft to chele of hate hie habbe&eth; misse.</L>
<L>[E]i&eth;er do&eth; hem wo inoh nabbe&eth; [hie] none lisse.</L>
<L N="240">[N]iten hwe&eth;er hem do&eth; wers to nafre none wisse.</L>
<L>[H]ie walke&eth; afre and seche&eth; reste ac hie hes ne mu&yogh;en imeten.</L>
<L>[F]or &thorn;i &thorn;e hie nolde &thorn;e hwile hie mihten here senne beten.</L>
<L>[H]ie seche&eth; reste &thorn;ar non nis ac hie hies<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Lambeth MS.</I> es.</NOTE> ne mu&yogh;en ifinden.</L>
<L N="244">[A]c walke&eth; weri up and dun se water do&eth; mid winde</L>
<L>[&THORN;]at be&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e waren her an &thorn;anc unstedefaste.</L>
<L>[And] &thorn;o &thorn;e gode biheten aihte and hit him ilaste.</L>
<L>[And] &thorn;o &thorn;e god werc bigunnen and ful endin hit nolden.</L>
<L N="248">[N]u waren her and nu &thorn;ar and nesten hwat he wolden</L>
<L>[&THORN;]ar is pich &thorn;at afre walle&eth; &thorn;ar sulle wunien inne</L>
<L>[&THORN;]o &thorn;e lade&eth; here lif on werre and an unwinne.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]ar is fur &thorn;is<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read &thorn;at</I> is.</NOTE> hundredfeald hatere &thorn;an be ure.</L>
<L N="252">[N]e mai hit quenche salt water ne auene stream ne sture.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]is is &thorn;at fur &thorn;at afre barne&eth; [hit] ne mai no wiht quenche.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]ar inne be&eth; &thorn;e was to lef wreche men to swenche.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e swikele men and ful of euele wrenchen.
<PB REF="00000256.tif" N="228"></L>
<L N="256">And &thorn;o &thorn;e mihten euel don and lief hit was to &thorn;enchen.</L>
<L>&THORN;e luueden rauing and stale hordom and dru[n]ken</L>
<L>And an defles werkes bli&eth;eliche swunken.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e waren swo lease men &thorn;at mes ne mihte leuen</L>
<L N="260">Med&yogh;ierne domes men and wrongwise reuen.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e o&eth;er mannes wif was lief her o&yogh;en e&eth;late</L>
<L>And &thorn;o &thorn;e sunegeden muchel on dru[n]ken and on ate.</L>
<L>&THORN;e wreche men binomen here aihte and leide his on horde.</L>
<L N="264">&THORN;e litel lete of godes bode and of godes worde.</L>
<L>And &thorn;e his o&yogh;en nolde &yogh;ieue &thorn;ar he iseih &thorn;e niede</L>
<L>Ne nolde ihere godes men &thorn;an he sat at his biede.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e was o&eth;er mannes &thorn;ing leuere &thorn;an hit solde</L>
<L N="268">And waren al to gradi of siluer and of golde.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e untrewnesse deden &thorn;an &thorn;e he solden ben holde.</L>
<L>And leten al &thorn;at hie solden don and deden &thorn;at hie wolden.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e waren &yogh;ietceres of &thorn;is wereldes aihte</L>
<L N="272">And dude al &thorn;at &thorn;e lo&eth;e gost hem tihte to and taihte.</L>
<L>And al &thorn;o &thorn;e[n] ani wise deuel iquemde</L>
<L>&THORN;o be&eth; mid hem<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Read</I> him.</NOTE> in helle fordon and demde.</L>
<L>Bute &thorn;o &thorn;e of&eth;uhte sore [her] here misdade</L>
<L N="276">And Gunne here gultes bete and betere lif lade.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar be&eth; naddren and snaken eueten and fruden</L>
<L>&THORN;e tere&eth; and frete&eth; &thorn;o euele swiken &thorn;e ni&eth;fule and &thorn;e prude</L>
<L>Nafre sunne &thorn;ar ne sine&eth; ne mone ne storre.</L>
<L N="280">&THORN;ar is muchel godes hete and muchel godes oerre<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE>.</L>
<L>Afre &thorn;ar is euel smech &thorn;iesternesse and eie</L>
<L>Nis &thorn;ar nafre oder liht &thorn;an &thorn;e swarte leie.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar lige&eth; ateliche fiend in stronge raketeie</L>
<L N="284">&THORN;at be&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e waren mid god angles swi&eth;e heie.</L>
<L>&THORN;at be&eth; ateliche fiend and Eiseliche wihten</L>
<L>&THORN;o sulle &thorn;e wreche sowle isien &thorn;e sinegeden &thorn;urh sihte</L>
<L>&THORN;ar is &thorn;e lo&eth;e sathanas and belzebub se ealde</L>
<L N="288">Ea&eth;e he mu&yogh;en ben sore ofdrad &thorn;e sullen hes bihealde.
<PB REF="00000257.tif" N="229"></L>
<L>Ne mai non herte hit &thorn;enche ne tunge hit ne mai telle</L>
<L>Hwu muchele pine ne hwu fele senden<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Jesus MS.</I> beo&thorn;.</NOTE> in helle</L>
<L>Of &thorn;o pine &thorn;e &thorn;ar bie&eth; nelle ich eow naht lie</L>
<L N="292">Nis hit bute gamen and glie of &thorn;at man mai here drie.</L>
<L>And &yogh;iet ne do&eth; hem naht alse wo in &thorn;e lo&eth;e bende</L>
<L>Swo &thorn;at he witen &thorn;at here pine sal nafre habben ende</L>
<L>&THORN;ar be&eth; &thorn;e ha&eth;ene men &thorn;e waren la&yogh;e-lease</L>
<L N="296">&THORN;e [hem] nes naht of godes bode ne of godes hease.</L>
<L>Euele cristene men hie be&eth; here iferen</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e here cristendom euele hielden here.</L>
<L>And &yogh;iet he be&eth; awerse stede ani&eth;er<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Egerton MS.</I> on &thorn;ere; <I>Jesus MS.</I> any&thorn;e.</NOTE> helle grunde</L>
<L N="300">Ne sullen [hie] nafre cumen &uacute;t for peni ne for punde.</L>
<L>Ne mai hem no&eth;er helpe &thorn;ar ibede ne almesse</L>
<L>For naht solden bidde &thorn;ar ore ne for&yogh;ieuenesse.</L>
<L>Silde him elch man &thorn;e hwile he mai wi&eth; &thorn;os helle pine.</L>
<L N="304">[And] warnie his frend &thorn;ar wi&eth; swo ich habbe ido mine.</L>
<L>&THORN;o &thorn;e silde hem ne cunnen ich hem wille tache</L>
<L>[I]ch can ben ai&eth;er &yogh;ief isal lichame and sowle lache.</L>
<L>Late we &thorn;at god forbet alle mankenne</L>
<L N="308">And do we &thorn;at he us hat and silde we us wid senne.</L>
<L>Luue we god mid ure herte and mid al ure mihte</L>
<L>And ure emcristen alse us self swo us tached drihte.</L>
<L>Al &thorn;at me rade&eth; and singed bifore godes borde</L>
<L N="312">Al hit hange&eth; and halt bi &thorn;ese twam worde</L>
<L>Alle godes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> godel.</NOTE> la&yogh;es hie fulle&eth; &thorn;e newe and &thorn;e ealde</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;e &thorn;os two luues halt and wile hes<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Egerton MS.</I> hl.</NOTE> wel healde.</L>
<L>Ac hie bie&eth; wel arefe&eth;-heald swo ofte we gulte&eth; alle</L>
<L N="316">For hit is strong te stonde longe and liht hit is to falle.</L>
<L>Ac drihte crist &yogh;eue us streng&eth;e stonde &thorn;at we moten</L>
<L>And of alle ure gultes &yogh;ieue us cume bote.</L>
<L>We wilnie&eth; after wereldes wele &thorn;e longe ne mai ilaste</L>
<L N="320">And lege&eth; mast al ure swinc on &thorn;ing unstedefaste.</L>
<L>Swunke [we] for godes luue half &thorn;at we do&eth; for eihte.</L>
<L>Nare we naht swo ofte bicherd ne swo euele bikeihte
<PB REF="00000258.tif" N="230"></L>
<L>&YOGH;ief we serueden god half &thorn;at we do&eth; for erminges</L>
<L N="324">We mihten habben more an heuene &thorn;a[n] &yogh;ierles and kinges</L>
<L>Ne mu&yogh;e we werien na&eth;er ne wi&eth; &thorn;urst ne wi&eth; hunger</L>
<L>Ne wid<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> elde ne wi&eth; elde ne wi&eth; dea&eth; &thorn;e elder ne &thorn;e &yogh;eunger</L>
<L>Ac &thorn;ar nis hunger ne &thorn;urst. dea&eth; ne unhal&eth;e ne elde.</L>
<L N="328">Of &thorn;esse riche we &thorn;enche&eth; to ofte of &thorn;are alto selde.</L>
<L>We solden bi&thorn;enchen us wel ofte and ilome<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>MS.</I> ilomo.</NOTE></L>
<L>Hwat we be&eth; to hwan we sullen and of hwan we come.</L>
<L>Hwu litle hwile we bie&eth; her hwu longe elles hware</L>
<L N="332">Hwat we mu&yogh;en habben her and hwat we finde&eth; &thorn;are.</L>
<L>&YOGH;ief [we] waren wise men &thorn;us we solden &thorn;enchen</L>
<L>Bute we wur&eth;en us iwar &thorn;is wereld us wile drenchen</L>
<L>Mast alle men hit &yogh;ieue&eth; drinken of on euele senche.</L>
<L N="336">He sal him cunnen silde wel &yogh;ief hit him nele screnche</L>
<L>Mid al mihtin godes luue &uacute;te we us biwerien</L>
<L>[W]i&eth; &thorn;esses wreches woreldes luue &thorn;at hit ne mu&yogh;e us derien</L>
<L>Mid almesse. mid fasten and mid ibeden werie we us wid senne.</L>
<L N="340">Mid &thorn;o wapne &thorn;e god haued<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> &yogh;ieue alle man kenne.</L>
<L>[L]ate we &thorn;e brode strate and &thorn;ane weg bene</L>
<L>[&THORN;]e lat &thorn;e nie&eth;e dal to helle of manne me mai wene.</L>
<L>Go we &thorn;ane narewe pa&eth; and &thorn;ene wei grene</L>
<L N="344">[&THORN;]ar for&eth; fare&eth; wel litel folc and eche is fair and isene</L>
<L>[&THORN;]e brode strate is ure wil &thorn;e is lo&eth; te l&aelig;te</L>
<L>[&THORN;]o &thorn;e fol&yogh;e&eth; here iwil hie fare&eth; bi &thorn;are strate.</L>
<L>Hie mu&yogh;en lihtliche cumen mid &thorn;are ni&eth;er helde</L>
<L N="348">[&THORN;]urh one godelease wude to one bare felde</L>
<L>[&THORN;]a narewe pa&eth; is godes has. &thorn;ar for&eth; fare&thorn; wel feawe</L>
<L>[&THORN;]at be&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e hem silde&eth; &yogh;ierne wi&eth; achen un&eth;eawe.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]os go&eth; unea&eth;e a&yogh;ien &thorn;e cliue and a&yogh;ien &thorn;e heie hulle</L>
<L N="352">[&THORN;]os leten al here iwil for godes luue to fulle.
<PB REF="00000259.tif" N="231"></L>
<L>Go we alle &thorn;ane wei for he us wile bringe</L>
<L>Mid &thorn;o feawe faire men bifore &thorn;e heuen kinge</L>
<L>[&THORN;]ar is alre blisse mast mid angles songe.</L>
<L N="356">[&THORN;]e is a &thorn;usend wintre &thorn;ar ne &thorn;unche&eth; hit him naht longe.</L>
<L>&THORN;e last haue&eth; blisse he haue&eth; sswo<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> muchel &thorn;at he ne bit no more</L>
<L>&THORN;e &thorn;at blisse forgo&eth; hit sal him rewen sore.</L>
<L>Ne mai non euel ne non wane ben in godes riche</L>
<L N="360">&THORN;eih &thorn;ar ben wuniinges fele elch o&eth;er uniliche</L>
<L>Sume &thorn;ar habbe&eth; lasse and sume &thorn;ar habbe&eth; more</L>
<L>Elch after &thorn;at he dude her after &thorn;ane &thorn;e [he] swanc sore</L>
<L>Ne sal &thorn;ar ben bread ne win ne o&eth;er kennes este</L>
<L N="364">God one sal ben ache lif and blisse and ache reste.</L>
<L>Ne sal &thorn;ar ben foh ne grai ne cunin ne ermine</L>
<L>Ne aquerne ne metheschele<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Egerton MS. has</I> mar|tres cheole.</NOTE> ne beuer ne sabeline.</L>
<L>Ne sal &thorn;er ben na&eth;er scat ne srud ne wereldes wele none.</L>
<L N="368">Al &thorn;e blisse &thorn;e me us bihat al hit sal ben god one</L>
<L>Ne mai no blisse ben alse muchel se is godes sihte.</L>
<L>He is so&eth; sunne and briht and dai abute nihte.</L>
<L>He is aches godes ful nis him no wiht uten</L>
<L N="372">Nones godes hem nis wane &thorn;e wunie&eth; him abuten.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar is wele abuten wane and reste abuten swunche.</L>
<L>&THORN;e mu&yogh;en and nelle&eth; &thorn;ider cume hit hem mai of&thorn;unche.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar is blisse abuten trei&yogh;e and life abuten dea&eth;e</L>
<L N="376">&THORN;o &thorn;e afre sulle wunie &thorn;ar bli&eth;e hie mu&yogh;e ben ea&eth;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar is &yogh;ieu&eth; abuten elde and hale abuten unhal&eth;e</L>
<L>Nis &thorn;ar sare&yogh;e ne sor non ne nafre unisal&eth;e.</L>
<L>&THORN;ar me drihte self isien swo se is mid iwisse</L>
<L N="380">He one mai and sal al ben angles and manne blisse.</L>
<L>And &thorn;eih ne bed<NOTE PLACE="marg">So in MS.</NOTE> here eien naht alle iliche brihte</L>
<L>Hi nabbe&eth; naht iliche muchel alle of godes lihte</L>
<L>On &thorn;esse liue he naren naht alle of ore mihte</L>
<L N="384">Ne &thorn;ar ne sullen habben god alle bi one wihte.</L>
<L>&THORN;o sullen more of him isien &thorn;e luueden hine more
<PB REF="00000260.tif" N="232"></L>
<L>And more ienowen and ec witen his mihte and his ore</L>
<L>On him hie sulle finden al &thorn;at man mai to hleste</L>
<L N="388">On him he sullen ec isien al &thorn;at hie ar nesten.</L>
<L>[C]rist sal one bien ino&yogh;h alle his derlinges.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]e one is muche more and betere &thorn;an alle o&eth;er &thorn;inges.</L>
<L>[I]noh he haue&eth; &thorn;e hine haue&eth; &thorn;e alle &thorn;ing wealde&eth;</L>
<L N="392">Of him to isiene nis non s&aelig;d swo fair he is to bihelden</L>
<L>God is swo mere<NOTE PLACE="marg"><I>Jesus MS</I>. swete.</NOTE> and swo muchel in his godcunnesse</L>
<L>[&THORN;]at al &thorn;at elles was and is is fele werse and lasse.</L>
<L>[N]e mai hit nafre noman o&eth;er seggen mid iwisse</L>
<L N="396">[H]wu muchele murih&eth;e habbe&eth; &thorn;o &thorn;e be&eth; in godes blisse</L>
<L>[T]o &thorn;are blisse us bringe god &thorn;e rixle&eth; abuten ende.</L>
<L>[&THORN;]ane he ure sowle unbint of lichamliche bende</L>
<L>[C]rist &yogh;ieue us laden her swilch lif and habben her swilch ende.</L>
<L N="400">[&THORN;]at we moten &thorn;ider cumen &thorn;ane we henne wende.</L>
</LG>
<TRAILER>AMEN.</TRAILER>
